4:\"faq2\";s:4:\"type\";s:8:\"repeater\";s:12:\"instructions\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"required\";s:1:\"0\";s:10:\"sub_fields\";a:2:{i:0;a:15:{s:3:\"key\";s:19:\"field_53739e65e08eb\";s:5:\"label\";s:8:\"Question\";s:4:\"name\";s:8:\"question\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:12:\"instructions\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"required\";s:1:\"0\";s:12:\"column_width\";s:2:\"50\";s:13:\"default_value\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"placeholder\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"prepend\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"append\";s:0:\"\";s:10:\"formatting\";s:4:\"html\";s:9:\"maxlength\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"conditional_logic\";a:3:{s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"rules\";a:1:{i:0;a:3:{s:5:\"field\";s:4:\"null\";s:8:\"operator\";s:2:\"==\";s:5:\"value\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"allorany\";s:3:\"all\";}s:8:\"order_no\";i:0;}i:1;a:12:{s:3:\"key\";s:19:\"field_53739e8ce08ec\";s:5:\"label\";s:6:\"Answer\";s:4:\"name\";s:6:\"answer\";s:4:\"type\";s:7:\"wysiwyg\";s:12:\"instructions\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"required\";s:1:\"0\";s:12:\"column_width\";s:2:\"50\";s:13:\"default_value\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"toolbar\";s:4:\"full\";s:12:\"media_upload\";s:3:\"yes\";s:17:\"conditional_logic\";a:3:{s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"rules\";a:1:{i:0;a:3:{s:5:\"field\";s:4:\"null\";s:8:\"operator\";s:2:\"==\";s:5:\"value\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"allorany\";s:3:\"all\";}s:8:\"order_no\";i:1;}}s:7:\"row_min\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"row_limit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"layout\";s:5:\"table\";s:12:\"button_label\";s:7:\"Add FAQ\";s:17:\"conditional_logic\";a:3:{s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"rules\";a:1:{i:0;a:3:{s:5:\"field\";s:4:\"null\";s:8:\"operator\";s:2:\"==\";s:5:\"value\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"allorany\";s:3:\"all\";}s:8:\"order_no\";i:1;}'),(5939,717,'_dp_original','473'),(5942,110,'faq2_0_question','What is improvised theatre? What is BATS-style improv? Is it like stand-up comedy? '),(5943,110,'_faq2_0_question','field_53739e65e08eb'),(5944,110,'faq2_0_answer','<p>Simply put, improvised theatre is theatre that’s created on the spot without a script. The BATS style of improvised theatre is unique in the improv landscape -- a one-of-a-kind blend of theatre, comedy, and acting that’s quite different from stand-up or sketch comedy. BATS style has been described as radical cooperation in action.</p><p>We produce improv shows in a variety of formats. Our shortform shows (usually on Fridays), like our signature competition Theatresports, are fast-paced, exciting, and highly interactive. If you like variety and lots of different stories in one night, our Friday shows are for you.</p><p>Our longform shows (usually on Saturdays) are full-length, narrative, genre-driven stories based on audience suggestions. The experience of going to a BATS longform show is like going to a play or movie -- and because its improvised, it’s extremely engaging, if not downright hilarious.</p><p>Read more <a title=\"About Improvised Theatre\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/shows/about-improvised-theatre/\">about improvised theatre, BATS style, and forms of improv</a>.</p>'),(5945,110,'_faq2_0_answer','field_53739e8ce08ec'),(5946,110,'faq2_1_question','Will I have to get on stage and do stuff? '),(5947,110,'_faq2_1_question','field_53739e65e08eb'),(5948,110,'faq2_1_answer','<p>Not if you don’t want to. Really.</p><p>Usually, we like to draw inspiration from our audiences by asking them for suggestions to start our scenes. Occasionally, we may ask for audience members to come up on stage to participate in a scene or game. When we do, it\'s completely voluntary. We love our audience members, and we treat you the way we’d want to be treated. We’d never put you on the spot or drag you onstage.</p><p>Want to particiapte from your seat? Great! Every show has some element of audience suggestion, and we encourage you to shout it out!</p>'),(5949,110,'_faq2_1_answer','field_53739e8ce08ec'),(5950,110,'faq2_2_question','Are BATS shows appropriate for kids? '),(5951,110,'_faq2_2_question','field_53739e65e08eb'),(5952,110,'faq2_2_answer','<p>BATS has welcomed theatregoers of all ages for more than 27 years. Older kids and teens really enjoy our shows, and occasionally we\'ll perform a scene or game with them onstage (but only if they volunteer -- see the previous question).</p><p>However, please keep in mind that our shows are completely improvised and that we have no idea what the content is going to be (although it’s important to note that we don\'t go out of our way to be raunchy or explicit, or “work blue”). If our shows were rated, most would be \"PG-13.\" Ultimately, we can\'t make any guarantees regarding age appropriateness for your kids. If you’re unsure, we encourage you to come check out a show for yourself before bringing your children. If you have questions about a specific show, please email us at <a href=\"mailto:shows@improv.org\">shows@improv.org</a>.</p><p>If your kids are interested in improv, consider enrolling them in one of the BATS School of Improv’s after-school or summer <a title=\"Youth Classes\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/school/youth-classes/\">youth classes</a>.</p>'),(5953,110,'_faq2_2_answer','field_53739e8ce08ec'),(5954,110,'faq2_3_question','How are student (Sunday) shows different from Friday and Saturday shows? Are the student shows good?'),(5955,110,'_faq2_3_question','field_53739e65e08eb'),(5956,110,'faq2_3_answer','<p>They are excellent if you like funny, exciting improv at 10 bucks! During our <a title=\"Student Shows\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/shows/student-shows/\">Student Showcases</a> and <a title=\"Student Shows\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/shows/student-shows/\">Cave Matches </a>(usually on Sunday) you’ll get to see a fun show featuring the next generation of San Francisco improv for less than a movie. And though it may be true that our student improvisers are not as experienced as our Main Stage Company members, rough around the edges also means fresh and innovative. Catch tomorrow’s stars on stage at BATS. You’ll be saying you ‘saw them when.’</p>'),(5957,110,'_faq2_3_answer','field_53739e8ce08ec'),(5958,110,'faq2_4_question','I went to a show and it looks like fun. How can I perform on the BATS stage? '),(5959,110,'_faq2_4_question','field_53739e65e08eb'),(5960,110,'faq2_4_answer','<p>The <a title=\"School of Improv\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/school/\">BATS School of Improv</a> offers classes for folks with all levels of improv experience. <a title=\"Jobs &amp; Auditions\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/about-us/jobs-auditions/\">Auditions</a> for the Main Stage Company Guest Program are held once a year in April and are highly competitive.</p>'),(5961,110,'_faq2_4_answer','field_53739e8ce08ec'),(5962,110,'faq2_5_question','What\'s with the name? What does \"BATS\" stand for?'),(5963,110,'_faq2_5_question','field_53739e65e08eb'),(5964,110,'faq2_5_answer','<p>BATS Improv was founded as \"Bay Area Theatresports.\" Over the years we became known in the community and in the improv world as “BATS” -- it was everyone’s favorite shorthand for us . . . and it stuck. In 2001, we formally changed our name to \"BATS Improv.” Read more about <a title=\"History\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/about-us/history/\">BATS’s history</a>.</p>'),(5965,110,'_faq2_5_answer','field_53739e8ce08ec'),(5966,110,'faq2_6_question','Do you perform at corporate events and private parties? '),(5967,110,'_faq2_6_question','field_53739e65e08eb'),(5968,110,'faq2_6_answer','<p>Absolutely. <a title=\"BATS On-the-Go\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/onthego/\">BATS On-the-Go</a> offers <a title=\"Custom Entertainment &amp; Holiday Events\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/onthego/custom-entertainment-holiday-events/\">custom entertainment</a> and <a title=\"Training Programs\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/onthego/training-programs/\">group training</a>. We can bring a personalized improv show to your private party or can help your company build team skills, develop creativity, and improve morale with a fun, interactive, completely customized training.</p>'),(5969,110,'_faq2_6_answer','field_53739e8ce08ec'),(5970,110,'faq2_7_question','I have a suggestion, idea, or complaint. Whom do I tell? '),(5971,110,'_faq2_7_question','field_53739e65e08eb'),(5972,110,'faq2_7_answer','<p>We\'d love to hear from you! Feedback, both positive and negative, helps us offer a better theatre experience for our patrons. Drop us an email at <a href=\"mailto:shows@improv.org\">shows@improv.org</a>.</p>'),(5973,110,'_faq2_7_answer','field_53739e8ce08ec'),(5974,110,'faq2','8'),(5975,110,'_faq2','field_5383f210359a2'),(5976,110,'faq_7_question','I have extra tickets I can\'t use. Can I have a refund or exchange them?'),(5977,110,'_faq_7_question','field_53739e65e08eb'),(5978,110,'faq_7_answer','<p>Our official policy is that all sales are final and we do not offer refunds. However, if you buy tickets to a show and can’t use them (yeah, sometimes friends flake!), contact us at <a href=\"mailto:shows@improv.org\">shows@improv.org</a> and we can usually make arrangements to exchange the unused tickets for another date.</p>'),(5979,110,'_faq_7_answer','field_53739e8ce08ec'),(5980,110,'faq_8_question','When should I arrive to buy tickets at the door?'),(5981,110,'_faq_8_question','field_53739e65e08eb'),(5982,110,'faq_8_answer','<p>The Bayfront Theater box office opens at 7:30 PM for Friday and Saturday shows and 30 minutes before showtime on Sundays. Some shows do sell out — especially holiday shows, tournament finals, and SF vs. LA shows — so we recommend that you <a href=\"https://www.vendini.com/ticket-software.html?t=tix&amp;w=30f488d21474d07590852179c032e191\" target=\"_blank\">buy tickets in advance</a>. That way you’ll be guaranteed a seat.</p><p>Please note that the BATS box office and BATS Café accept cash or check only (for now -- we’re working on it).</p>'),(5983,110,'_faq_8_answer','field_53739e8ce08ec'),(5984,110,'faq_9_question','Do you have discounts for students or seniors?'),(5985,110,'_faq_9_question','field_53739e65e08eb'),(5986,110,'faq_9_answer','<p>Yes, Friday and Saturday show tickets for students (youth under 18 and college students with ID) and seniors (65 and older) are $17 at the door instead of $20. Note that there is one price for all online ticket sales: $17.</p>'),(5987,110,'_faq_9_answer','field_53739e8ce08ec'),(5988,110,'faq_10_question','Do you have group discounts?'),(5989,110,'_faq_10_question','field_53739e65e08eb'),(5990,110,'faq_10_answer','<p>Yes! BATS Improv shows are great outings for groups, and we offer discount tickets for groups of 10 or more. Read further about <a title=\"Group Sales\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/shows/group-sales/\">group sales</a> or contact <a href=\"mailto:shows@improv.org\">shows@improv.org</a> to make arrangements. For groups of 200 or more, contact us to create <a title=\"Custom Entertainment &amp; Holiday Events\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/bats-on-the-go/custom-entertainment-holiday-events/\">custom entertainment</a> at your location.</p>'),(5991,110,'_faq_10_answer','field_53739e8ce08ec'),(5992,110,'faq_11_question','Do you have package or subscription rates?'),(5993,110,'_faq_11_question','field_53739e65e08eb'),(5994,110,'faq_11_answer','<p>Yes. You can <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/e/bats-improv-show-six-pack-tickets-3601715829\" target=\"_blank\">buy a six-pack of tickets</a> for any regular weekend show and save up to $30. <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/e/bats-improv-show-six-pack-tickets-3601715829\" target=\"_blank\"><b><br /></b></a></p>'),(5995,110,'_faq_11_answer','field_53739e8ce08ec'),(5996,110,'faq_12_question','How do I use a gift certificate to buy tickets?'),(5997,110,'_faq_12_question','field_53739e65e08eb'),(5998,110,'faq_12_answer','<p>Please email <a href=\"mailto:shows@improv.org\">shows@improv.org</a> to make a reservation. Include your name and the number of tickets you will be purchasing with your gift certificate. Making a reservation guarantees you a seat even if the show sells out. On the night of the show, bring your gift certificate to the box office. Tickets with a reservation will be deducted from your gift certificate total at the advance price of $17 each.</p><p>Without a reservation, you can use your gift certificate just like cash. Please note that seating is on a space available basis and some shows do sell out. Tickets without a reservation will be deducted at the door price of $20 per ticket.</p>'),(5999,110,'_faq_12_answer','field_53739e8ce08ec'),(6000,110,'faq_13_question','I have a free pass (or other complimentary admission ticket). How do I make a reservation? Can I just show up at the door? '),(6001,110,'_faq_13_question','field_53739e65e08eb'),(6002,110,'faq_13_answer','<p><i>Use your free pass to make a reservation:</i> Please email <a href=\"mailto:shows@improv.org\">shows@improv.org</a> to make a reservation. Please include your name and the number of passes you will be using. By emailing us to make a reservation, you’ll gaurantee your seat just as if you had purchased a ticket online, even if the show sells out!</p><p><i>Use your free pass at the door:</i> Just show up at the door and you can use your free pass on a space available basis (that means we can’t accept your free pass at the door if the show has sold out).</p><p>Note that free passes are not redeemable at shows marked \"no passes\" (posted at the door and/or on the show webpage) or at special guest shows featuring non-BATS groups or players. Check the page of the show you want to attend. If it doesn’t say “no passes accepted” then you’re good to go!  </p>'),(6003,110,'_faq_13_answer','field_53739e8ce08ec'),(6004,110,'faq_14_question','Where can I go nearby to eat/drink before or after?'),(6005,110,'_faq_14_question','field_53739e65e08eb'),(6006,110,'faq_14_answer','<p>You can always grab a snack at the BATS Café before the show or during intermission, and there are plenty of bars and restaurants in the area. Check out the list of nearby restaurants on the <a title=\"Map &amp; Directions\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/about-us/map-directions/#restaurants\">Map, Directions &amp; Nearby page</a>.</p>'),(6007,110,'_faq_14_answer','field_53739e8ce08ec'),(6008,110,'faq_15_question','How do I get to the theater? '),(6009,110,'_faq_15_question','field_53739e65e08eb'),(6010,110,'faq_15_answer','<p>This <a title=\"Map &amp; Directions\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/about-us/map-directions/\">map and directions</a> should help you find us by car or public transportation. Because our theater is inside a historic army fort, there isn’t a formal street address. For GPS users, we recommend using the address of the Safeway directly across the street from the Fort Mason entrance: 16 Marina Blvd, San Francisco.</p>'),(6011,110,'_faq_15_answer','field_53739e8ce08ec'),(6012,110,'faq_16_question','Is there parking?'),(6013,110,'_faq_16_question','field_53739e65e08eb'),(6014,110,'faq_16_answer','<p>Yes – there is both paid and free parking. The Fort Mason Center parking lot -- the one closest to the theater -- is a pay lot. Depending on arrival time, we recommend parking for 2-3 hours, which is $6 Friday and $7 Saturday (a deal for parking in SF!) <a href=\"http://www.fortmason.org/aboutus/visitor-information\" target=\"_blank\">More details and parking rates</a>. Note that the lot can fill up when there are multiple events going on (particularly during Friday night’s <a href=\"http://offthegridsf.com/markets/fort-mason-center#about\" target=\"_blank\">Off the Grid</a> food truck events, which happen March to October every year).</p><p>For free parking, you can often park in the Marina Green lot, directly adjacent to Fort Mason. Be sure to read the signs for restrictions -- the lot is reserved for Yacht Harbor permit holders during certain hours, although these generally do not conflict with show times.</p>'),(6015,110,'_faq_16_answer','field_53739e8ce08ec'),(6016,110,'faq_17_question','Is the theater wheelchair accessible?'),(6017,110,'_faq_17_question','field_53739e65e08eb'),(6018,110,'faq_17_answer','<p>Yes. There is a ramp at the south side (nearest the parking lot) of the west entrance to the building (the entrance with the BATS sign) and an elevator to get to the third floor. ADA-compliant bathrooms are located across the bridge in Building C. Please contact us at <a href=\"mailto:shows@improv.org\">shows@improv.org</a> to notify us of any special needs you may have so we may accommodate them.</p>'),(6019,110,'_faq_17_answer','field_53739e8ce08ec'),(6020,717,'field_5383f4f709dbb','a:11:{s:3:\"key\";s:19:\"field_5383f4f709dbb\";s:5:\"label\";s:10:\"FAQ2 Title\";s:4:\"name\";s:10:\"faq2_title\";s:4:\"type\";s:7:\"wysiwyg\";s:12:\"instructions\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"required\";s:1:\"0\";s:13:\"default_value\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"toolbar\";s:4:\"full\";s:12:\"media_upload\";s:2:\"no\";s:17:\"conditional_logic\";a:3:{s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"rules\";a:1:{i:0;a:3:{s:5:\"field\";s:4:\"null\";s:8:\"operator\";s:2:\"==\";s:5:\"value\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"allorany\";s:3:\"all\";}s:8:\"order_no\";i:0;}'),(6023,110,'faq2_title','<h3>The BATS Improv Experience</h3>'),(6024,110,'_faq2_title','field_5383f4f709dbb'),(6027,575,'sidebar','home-set'),(6028,575,'_sidebar','field_5380e7f58e3e8'),(6029,108,'2013_3_title','<h2>Theatresports Spring Tournament</h2>\r\n<p>by Chad Jones, <i>San Francisco Chronicle,</i> March 13, 2013</p>'),(6030,108,'_2013_3_title','field_5373dc6c67a57'),(6031,108,'2013_3_article','<p>Kasey Klemm fell in love with improv at Ignacio Valley High School in Concord, where he and his buddies formed an improv league. As a graduation present, his mom got him beginning classes at Bay Area Theatresports in San Francisco.</p>\r\n<p>Sixteen years later, the company, now known as BATS Improv, is among the country\'s most prominent improv groups and Klemm is in his third year as artistic director.</p>\r\n<p>BATS Improv is coming off its best year ever. Klemm says that last year, more than 12,000 people attended BATS shows. . . .</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.sfgate.com/default/article/Theatresports-Spring-Tournament-4352446.php\" target=\"_blank\">Read the full story »</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(6032,108,'_2013_3_article','field_5373dc6c67a58'),(6033,108,'2013_4_title','<h2>Best Local Stand-Up Comics and Comedians in the Bay Area</h2>\r\n<p class=\"Body1\">by Cindy Warner, <i>CBS Local,</i> February 25, 2013</p>'),(6034,108,'_2013_4_title','field_5373dc6c67a57'),(6035,108,'2013_4_article','<p>Do you need a good laugh? There is an abundance of humor to appreciate in the Bay Area. With many comedians getting their start in San Francisco and continuing to entertain Bay Area audiences, you have multiple options to choose from….</p>\r\n<p>Come out to Bayfront Theater on Friday and Saturday nights for great comedy. <a href=\"http://www.improv.org/Home.aspx\">BATS Improv</a> features a twisted regular cast and some show-stealing guests. The troupe performs at a small and intimate theater at Fort Mason in the marina and any performance makes for a great date night….</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://sanfrancisco.cbslocal.com/top-lists/best-local-stand-up-comics-and-comedians-in-the-bay-area\" target=\"_blank\">Read the full story »</a></p>'),(6036,108,'_2013_4_article','field_5373dc6c67a58'),(6037,108,'2012_3_title','<h2>San Francisco: Witness a Completely Improvised Murder Mystery</h2>\r\n<p class=\"Body1\">by Monica Turner, <i>Stark Insider,</i> April 27, 2012</p>'),(6038,108,'_2012_3_title','field_5373dc7767a5a'),(6039,108,'2012_3_article','<p>Isn’t murder best when improvised? (should we insert OJ reference here, or would that be so-so tired, and done with?) …</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.starkinsider.com/2012/04/san-francisco-witness-a-completely-improvised-murder-mystery.html\" target=\"_blank\">Read the full story »</a></p>'),(6040,108,'_2012_3_article','field_5373dc7767a5b'),(6041,108,'2012_4_title','<h2>Give &amp; Take: Negotiation Shouldn’t Be a Tug of War – Instead, the Best Training Focuses on Building Rapport</h2>\r\n<p>by Gail Dutton, <i>Training,</i> March 27, 2012</p>'),(6042,108,'_2012_4_title','field_5373dc7767a5a'),(6043,108,'2012_4_article','<p>Employees in a negotiation training workshop are chatting happily in a company cafeteria near San Francisco. They’re not on break. They’re on assignment. Their objective: to discover three things they didn’t know—and wouldn’t have guessed—about each other. They have two minutes. . . .</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.trainingmag.com/content/give-take\" target=\"_blank\">Read the full story »</a></p>'),(6044,108,'_2012_4_article','field_5373dc7767a5b'),(6045,108,'2012_5_title','<h2>REVIEW: BATS Improvised Shakespeare with Romantic Comedy; Founder Hall as Fair Beatrice</h2>\r\n<p>by Cindy Warner, <i>Examiner.com,</i> March 11, 2012</p>'),(6046,108,'_2012_5_title','field_5373dc7767a5a'),(6047,108,'2012_5_article','<p><b>Rating: 5 stars</b></p>\r\n<p>Improvising Shakespeare last night, BATS Improv at Fort Mason took the suggested title from the audience of “Two Crows” and created a full length original romantic comedy full of Bardian plot twists with double identities and four sisters whoe father needs to marry them off royally. . . .</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.examiner.com/review/bats-improvised-shakespeare-with-romantic-comedy-founder-hall-as-fair-beatrice\" target=\"_blank\">Read the full story »</a></p>'),(6048,108,'_2012_5_article','field_5373dc7767a5b'),(6049,108,'2012_6_title','<h2>Company Spotlight: BATS Improv</h2>\r\n<p>by Lisa Drostova, <i>Theatre Bay Area,</i> March 5, 2012</p>'),(6050,108,'_2012_6_title','field_5373dc7767a5a'),(6051,108,'2012_6_article','<p>You might not think a 25-year-old company with its own 200-seat theatre would consider a few simple chairs a purchase that would significantly boost production values. But if it’s a company where the story gets made up on the fly every performance and the props are all mimed, it makes sense that BATS Improv’s recent acquisition of a matched set of chairs for the stage is a small victory. . . .</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#\" target=\"_blank\">Read the full story »</a></p>'),(6052,108,'_2012_6_article','field_5373dc7767a5b'),(6053,108,'2012_7_title','<h2>REVIEW: BATS New Year’s Eve Special Had Romantic and Tragic Comedy, Plus <i>The Outcast</i></h2>\r\n<p class=\"Body1\">by Cindy Warner, <i>Examiner, </i>January 1, 2012</p>'),(6054,108,'_2012_7_title','field_5373dc7767a5a'),(6055,108,'2012_7_article','<p>The New Year’s Eve Special directed by Tim Orr at BATS Improv at Fort Mason had a happy ending to its improvised long form “The Outcast,” an audience-suggested 1950s cold war thriller about a genius six year old who could read minds and outwitted her Russian kindnappers…</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.examiner.com/review/bats-new-year-s-eve-special-had-romantic-and-tragic-comedy-plus-the-outcast\">Read the full story »</a></p>'),(6056,108,'_2012_7_article','field_5373dc7767a5b'),(6057,719,'_edit_lock','1401594990:2'),(6058,719,'_edit_last','2'),(6059,719,'field_5383fd410a0b4','a:13:{s:3:\"key\";s:19:\"field_5383fd410a0b4\";s:5:\"label\";s:8:\"Position\";s:4:\"name\";s:8:\"position\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"radio\";s:12:\"instructions\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"required\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"choices\";a:3:{s:6:\"player\";s:6:\"Player\";s:5:\"coach\";s:5:\"Coach\";s:4:\"both\";s:4:\"Both\";}s:12:\"other_choice\";s:1:\"0\";s:17:\"save_other_choice\";s:1:\"0\";s:13:\"default_value\";s:6:\"player\";s:6:\"layout\";s:8:\"vertical\";s:17:\"conditional_logic\";a:3:{s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"rules\";a:1:{i:0;a:3:{s:5:\"field\";s:4:\"null\";s:8:\"operator\";s:2:\"==\";s:5:\"value\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"allorany\";s:3:\"all\";}s:8:\"order_no\";i:0;}'),(6061,719,'position','side'),(6062,719,'layout','no_box'),(6063,719,'hide_on_screen',''),(6064,721,'_wp_attached_file','2014/04/history-photo.jpg'),(6065,721,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:215;s:6:\"height\";i:236;s:4:\"file\";s:25:\"2014/04/history-photo.jpg\";s:5:\"sizes\";a:1:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:4: