who has clowned with Cirque du Soleil. . . .</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.examiner.com/article/bats-improv-celebrated-25th-anniversary-with-theatresports-chocolate-fountains\" target=\"_blank\">Read the full story »</a></p>'),(6075,108,'_2011_1_article','field_5373dc7d67a5e'),(6076,108,'2011_2_title','<h2>BATS Improv Celebrates 25 Years</h2>\r\n<p>by Cindy Warner, <em>Examiner.com,</em> November 11, 2011</p>'),(6077,108,'_2011_2_title','field_5373dc7d67a5d'),(6078,108,'2011_2_article','<p>BATS Improv – on November 10<sup>th</sup> celebrates their 25<sup>th</sup> anniversary. 25 years of presenting innovative improv theatre to the Bay Area. . . .</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.examiner.com/article/bats-improv-celebrates-25-years-at-fort-mason-with-theatersports-champagne\" target=\"_blank\">Read the full story »</a></p>'),(6079,108,'_2011_2_article','field_5373dc7d67a5e'),(6080,108,'2011_3_title','<h2>The (Theater)-Sporting Life: BATS Improv Turns 25!</h2>\r\n<p>by Cheryl Eddy, <em>San Francisco Bay Guardian,</em> November, 10, 2011</p>'),(6081,108,'_2011_3_title','field_5373dc7d67a5d'),(6082,108,'2011_3_article','<p>It was 1986, the year of <em>Top Gun, Dallas,</em> \"Hands Across America,\" and \"Papa Don\'t Preach.\" In San Francisco, a comedy troupe called Fratelli Bologna joined forces with Seattle Theatresports\' Rebecca Stockley, and the rest was history. Bay Area Theatresports, now known as BATS Improv, marks its 25th anniversary this year with a special show Saturday . . .</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.sfbg.com/pixel_vision/2011/11/10/theater-sporting-life-bats-improv-turns-25\" target=\"_blank\">Read the full story »</a></p>'),(6083,108,'_2011_3_article','field_5373dc7d67a5e'),(6084,108,'2011_4_title','<h2>Happy Birthday! BATS Improv Celebrates 25 Years</h2>\r\n<p>by Salinda Tyson, <em>San Francisco Examiner,</em> November 10, 2011</p>'),(6085,108,'_2011_4_title','field_5373dc7d67a5d'),(6086,108,'2011_4_article','<p>Bay Area Theatresports Artistic Director Kasey Klemm has overcome his fear of improvisation.</p>\r\n<p>The actor, who began taking classes when he was 17 and joined BATS just before turning 21, admits, “Improv happens in the moment. No one knows where it’s going. It is scary at first. But after enough times on the ledge, it’s more than scary; it’s exhilarating.” . . .</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.sfexaminer.com/sanfrancisco/happy-birthday-bats-improv-celebrates-25-years/Content?oid=2185572\" target=\"_blank\">Read the full story »</a></p>'),(6087,108,'_2011_4_article','field_5373dc7d67a5e'),(6088,108,'2011_5_title','<h2>REVIEW:<i> Improvised Hitchcock</i> at BATS Improv Is More Than a Killer Tribute</h2>\r\n<p class=\"Body1\">by Alan Scherstuhl, <i>SF Weekly,</i> October, 14, 2011</p>'),(6089,108,'_2011_5_title','field_5373dc7d67a5d'),(6090,108,'2011_5_article','<p>For all the laughs it generates, perhaps the most impressive thing about BATS Improv’s feature-length Improvised Hitchcock show is the moments of genuine tension. Seriously….</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://blogs.sfweekly.com/exhibitionist/2011/10/improvised_hitchcock_at_bats_i.php\" target=\"_blank\">Read the full story and watch the video »</a></p>'),(6091,108,'_2011_5_article','field_5373dc7d67a5e'),(6092,108,'2011_6_title','<h2>How to Make It in San Francisco: BATS Improv Review</h2>\r\n<p>by Guillermo Paz, <em>Series and TV,</em> July 25, 2011</p>'),(6093,108,'_2011_6_title','field_5373dc7d67a5d'),(6094,108,'2011_6_article','<p>As I wrote already, I´ve been touring the US to visit the top entertainment destinations. In this first trip I had the chance to visit Los Angeles, New York and San Francisco (There’s still a lot of cities to go to). . . .</p>\r\n<p>Well, it´s time to talk a little bit more about San Francisco; and the BATS Improv crew. . . .</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://seriesandtv.com/how-to-make-it-in-san-francisco-bats-improv-review/6744\" target=\"_blank\">Read the full story »</a></p>'),(6095,108,'_2011_6_article','field_5373dc7d67a5e'),(6096,108,'2011_7_title','<h2>Stuck in a Routine and a Little Bored? Try Improv!</h2>\r\n<p>by Richard Scheinin, <em>San Jose Mercury News,</em> July 9, 2011</p>'),(6097,108,'_2011_7_title','field_5373dc7d67a5d'),(6098,108,'2011_7_article','<p>There’s birthday party energy in Steve Fogel’s San Carlos living room. Shouting! Squealing! Only the noisemakers aren’t kids. They’re grown-ups, 16 responsible adults pretending to toss an invisible ball of electricity around a circle. \"Zip! Zap! Boing!\" they shout, feigning shock (literally) or heavy exertion or winking Marx Brothers surprise as the electric \"ball\" moves this way and that. . . .</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.mercurynews.com/ci_18432909\" target=\"_blank\">Read the full story »</a></p>'),(6099,108,'_2011_7_article','field_5373dc7d67a5e'),(6100,108,'2011_8_title','<h2>Giants Hold Team Tryouts: BATS On-the-Go Team Visits AT&amp;T Park</h2>\r\n<p><em>KNTV (NBC Bay Area) News,</em> March 25, 2011</p>'),(6101,108,'_2011_8_title','field_5373dc7d67a5d'),(6102,108,'2011_8_article','<p>On March 25, 2011, the BATS On-the-Go team visited AT&amp;T Park to help train potential stadium staff. The high profile training was captured by NBC Bay Area television and later broadcast on the 6 o\'clock news. The trainees were trying out for positions as stadium promoters during SF Giants games. Trainers included BATS Company members Barbara Scott, Laura Derry, Regina Saisi, and OTG Director Chris Sams. </p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.nbcbayarea.com/news/breaking/Giants_Hold_Team_Tryouts_Bay_Area-116008979.html\" target=\"_blank\">Read the full story and watch the video »</a></p>'),(6103,108,'_2011_8_article','field_5373dc7d67a5e'),(6104,498,'field_538413eff57a9','a:13:{s:3:\"key\";s:19:\"field_538413eff57a9\";s:5:\"label\";s:4:\"2010\";s:4:\"name\";s:4:\"2010\";s:4:\"type\";s:8:\"repeater\";s:12:\"instructions\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"required\";s:1:\"0\";s:10:\"sub_fields\";a:2:{i:0;a:12:{s:3:\"key\";s:19:\"field_538413eff57a