no\";i:0;}'),(6451,717,'rule','a:5:{s:5:\"param\";s:13:\"page_template\";s:8:\"operator\";s:2:\"==\";s:5:\"value\";s:16:\"showfaq-page.php\";s:8:\"order_no\";i:0;s:8:\"group_no\";i:1;}'),(6452,408,'faq3_title','<h2>Class Locations, Directions, Parking, Accessibility</h2>'),(6453,408,'_faq3_title','field_5386232fed654'),(6454,408,'faq3_0_question','Where is my class? '),(6455,408,'_faq3_0_question','field_53862335ed656'),(6456,408,'faq3_0_answer','<p>Class locations are noted on the online class schedule and will appear in your registration confirmation email from the BATS office.</p><p>Most BATS classes are held at Fort Mason Center in San Francisco\'s Marina District, either in the Bayfront Theater (Building B, 3rd Floor) or other classroom locations in the Fort Mason Center. Locations will be posted at the entrance to the Bayfront Theater at the time of your class.</p><p>BATS also holds classes in spaces at Studio 210 in San Francisco’s Mission District and the Cubberley Community Center in Palo Alto.</p><p>See <a title=\"Map &amp; Directions\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/about-us/map-directions/\">Map, Directions &amp; Nearby</a> for directions, parking, public transportation, and safety info, and a list of nearby restaurants.</p><p><a href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/map.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-614 size-full\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/map.jpg\" alt=\"map\" width=\"215\" height=\"283\" /></a><a title=\"BATS Improv map\" href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/place/BATS+Improv+Theatre/@37.80666,-122.431736,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m2!3m1!1s0x808580de5d16d545:0x48b36832e74af2b7\" target=\"_blank\">BATS Center for Improvised Theatre</a><br />Bayfront Theater<br />B350 Fort Mason Center<br />San Francisco</p><p><a href=\"http://goo.gl/maps/ikQQJ\" target=\"_blank\">Studio 210</a><br />3435 Cesar Chavez Street<br />San Francisco</p><p><a href=\"http://goo.gl/maps/UU71J\" target=\"_blank\">Cubberley Community Center</a><br />4000 Middlefield Road<br />Palo Alto</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>'),(6457,408,'_faq3_0_answer','field_53862335ed657'),(6458,408,'faq3_1_question','Where can I park?'),(6459,408,'_faq3_1_question','field_53862335ed656'),(6460,408,'faq3_1_answer','<p>See <a title=\"Map &amp; Directions\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/about-us/map-directions/\">Map, Directions &amp; Nearby</a>.</p>'),(6461,408,'_faq3_1_answer','field_53862335ed657'),(6462,408,'faq3_2_question','Are you near public transportation?'),(6463,408,'_faq3_2_question','field_53862335ed656'),(6464,408,'faq3_2_answer','<p>See <a title=\"Map &amp; Directions\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/about-us/map-directions/\">Map, Directions &amp; Nearby</a>.</p>'),(6465,408,'_faq3_2_answer','field_53862335ed657'),(6466,408,'faq3_3_question','Are your classrooms wheelchair accessible?'),(6467,408,'_faq3_3_question','field_53862335ed656'),(6468,408,'faq3_3_answer','<p>The Bayfront Theater and classrooms in Fort Mason are wheelchair accessible. There is a ramp at the south side (nearest the parking lot) of the west entrance to the building (the entrance with the BATS sign) and an elevator to get to the third floor. ADA-compliant bathrooms are located across the bridge in Building C.</p><p>Unfortunately, Studio 210 is not wheelchair accessible.</p><p>The Cubberley Community Center in Palo Alto is wheelchair accessible.</p><p>Please contact us at <a href=\"mailto:registrar@improv.org\">registrar@improv.org</a> to notify us of any special needs you may have so we can accommodate them.</p>'),(6469,408,'_faq3_3_answer','field_53862335ed657'),(6470,408,'faq3_4_question','Can I bring my dog? '),(6471,408,'_faq3_4_question','field_53862335ed656'),(6472,408,'faq3_4_answer','<p class=\"Body1\">We regret that no animals are allowed in class except service animals.</p>'),(6473,408,'_faq3_4_answer','field_53862335ed657'),(6474,408,'faq3','5'),(6475,408,'_faq3','field_53862335ed6