\"orientation\";i:1;}}'),(19835,1521,'extra_image_1','1519'),(19836,1521,'_extra_image_1','field_52f273e29b5db'),(19837,1521,'extra_image_2','1518'),(19838,1521,'_extra_image_2','field_52f27616cf901'),(19839,1521,'extra_image_3','1520'),(19840,1521,'_extra_image_3','field_52f27626cf902'),(19841,1521,'position','player'),(19842,1521,'_position','field_5383fd410a0b4'),(19843,1521,'extra_text','Company, Coach'),(19844,1521,'_extra_text','field_538aa44d3d9dc'),(19845,1521,'sidebar','shows-set-four'),(19846,1521,'_sidebar','field_5380e7f58e3e8'),(19847,1521,'right_column','<h1>Q &amp; A</h1>\r\n<p><strong>What was your first BATS show?<br /> </strong>The first show we ever did, and I was in it. We performed in the theater in the basement of 25 Van Ness. It was a sold-out match against a team from Seattle. The exciting energy far exceeded the skills of the performers. (I\'m told a video of it exists somewhere!)</p>\r\n<p><strong>What are your favorite formats?<br /> </strong>Theatresports™, Gorilla Theatre, the Harold, and the Life Game</p>\r\n<p><strong>Best moment on the BATS stage?<br /> </strong>Before we had a permanent theater space, we would rent theaters as needed; occasionally the stage would already have a set on it. On one such occasion, I remember standing up on a platform about 10 feet above the stage, and in the course of a scene I told fellow improviser Tim Ereneta that he couldn\'t get me down from there. Whereupon he and the other improvisers lifted me up, formed a human chain and passed me along (in slow motion) down to the stage floor. You never know what will happen on an improv stage.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Any improv advice?<br /> </strong>Improvisation is a world of limitless opportunities and an absence of rules.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What are your artistic Influences?<br /> </strong>The theatre training I received at Boston University, <em>Impro</em> by Keith Johnstone, and reading about Dario Fo</p>\r\n<p><strong>Favorite movies?<br /> </strong>Marx Brothers\' <em>A Night at the Opera </em>and <em>Mon Oncle</em> with Jacques Tati</p>\r\n<p><strong>Favorite music?<br /> </strong>Country</p>'),(19848,1521,'_right_column','field_52f276e1f1ba0'),(19849,1522,'_wp_attached_file','2013/11/ben3.jpg'),(19850,1522,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:192;s:6:\"height\";i:113;s:4:\"file\";s:16:\"2013/11/ben3.jpg\";s:5:\"sizes\";a:1:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:16:\"ben3-150x113.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:150;s:6:\"height\";i:113;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:10:\"image_meta\";a:11:{s:8:\"aperture\";d:8;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:20:\"Canon EOS 5D Mark II\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:1400532671;s:9:\"copyright\";s:6:\"©2014\";s:12:\"focal_length\";s:2:\"50\";s:3:\"iso\";s:4:\"2000\";s:13:\"shutter_speed\";s:4:\"0.01\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";i:1;}}'),(19851,1523,'_wp_attached_file','2013/11/ben2.jpg'),(19852,1523,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:192;s:6:\"height\";i:113;s:4:\"file\";s:16:\"2013/11/ben2.jpg\";s:5:\"sizes\";a:1:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:16:\"ben2-150x113.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:150;s:6:\"height\";i:113;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:10:\"image_meta\";a:11:{s:8:\"aperture\";d:7.0999999999999996447286321199499070644378662109375;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:20:\"Canon EOS 5D Mark II\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:1400526393;s:9:\"copyright\";s:6:\"©2014\";s:12:\"focal_length\";s:2:\"35\";s:3:\"iso\";s:4:\"2000\";s:13:\"shutter_speed\";s:6:\"0.0125\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";i:1;}}'),(19853,1524,'_wp_attached_file','2013/11/ben1.jpg'),(19854,1524,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:236;s:6:\"height\";i:236;s:4:\"file\";s:16:\"2013/11/ben1.jpg\";s:5:\"sizes\";a:1:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:16:\"ben1-150x150.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:150;s:6:\"height\";i:150;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:10:\"image_meta\";a:11:{s:8:\"aperture\";d:8;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:20:\"Canon EOS 5D Mark II\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:1400532758;s:9:\"copyright\";s:6:\"©2014\";s:12:\"focal_length\";s:2:\"50\";s:3:\"iso\";s:4:\"2000\";s:13:\"shutter_speed\";s:4:\"0.01\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";i:1;}}'),(19855,1525,'extra_image_1','1523'),(19856,1525,'_extra_image_1','field_52f273e29b5db'),(19857,1525,'extra_image_2','1522'),(19858,1525,'_extra_image_2','field_52f27616cf901'),(19859,1525,'extra_image_3','1524'),(19860,1525,'_extra_image_3','field_52f27626cf902'),(19861,1525,'position','player'),(19862,1525,'_position','field_5383fd410a0b4'),(19863,1525,'extra_text','Company, Coach'),(19864,1525,'_extra_text','field_538aa44d3d9dc'),(19865,1525,'sidebar','shows-set-four'),(19866,1525,'_sidebar','field_5380e7f58e3e8'),(19867,1525,'right_column','<h1>Q &amp; A</h1>\r\n<p><strong>What do you like about improv?<br /> </strong>I love making up stories with friends.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What was your first BATS Show?<br /> </strong>It was a Theatresports™ show on July 17, 2009. I was on a team with Tim and Regina. My notes from that night say that I felt confident . . . and a bit shaky in the improv skills department.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Your first improv class?<br /> </strong>My first class was with Improv Jones in Providence, RI, in 2005 (I think). A great actor/improviser named Mauro Hantman was the teacher.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What are your favorite formats?<br /> </strong>I like everything . . . but longform stories with a small cast have been making me especially happy lately.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Best moment on the BATS stage?<br /> </strong>I don’t think I can identify a best, but Barbara, Kasey, Ethan, and I played a scene recently about a blind date that was a lot of fun. I had to find a reason for my character to leave for a moment because I was laughing so much.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What has improv taught you about life?<br /> </strong>Listen. Be bold. Make mistakes. Look for the good in other people.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Any improv advice?<br /> </strong>Listen to the story and do what it wants you to do. Make your partner look good.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Who are your artistic influences?<br /> </strong>That’s a big question. I feel like I’m influenced every time I see someone perform.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Favorite movies?<br /> </strong>I really like all the great TV that’s being made right now. <em>Deadwood, The Wire, Friday Night Lights, Breaking Bad, Game of Thrones, </em>and <em>Mad Men</em> are all favorites.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Favorite music?<br /> </strong>I like a little bit of everything. I think there are great songs in every musical genre.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Favorite play?<br /> </strong>Anything being done by GAMM Theatre in Rhode Island. It’s a wonderful company where I learned a lot about scripted theatre.</p>'),(19868,1525,'_right_column','field_52f276e1f1ba0'),(19869,1526,'_wp_attached_file','2014/04/ethan3.jpg'),(19870,1526,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:192;s:6:\"height\";i:113;s:4:\"file\";s:18:\"2014/04/ethan3.jpg\";s:5:\"sizes\";a:1:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:18:\"ethan3-150x113.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:150;s:6:\"height\";i:113;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:10:\"image_meta\";a:11:{s:8:\"aperture\";d:8;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:20:\"Canon EOS 5D Mark II\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:1400530101;s:9:\"copyright\";s:6:\"©2014\";s:12:\"focal_length\";s:2:\"50\";s:3:\"iso\";s:4:\"2500\";s:13:\"shutter_speed\";s:4:\"0.01\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";i:1;}}'),(19871,1527,'_wp_attached_file','2014/04/ethan2.jpg'),(19872,1527,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:192;s:6:\"height\";i:113;s:4:\"file\";s:18:\"2014/04/ethan2.jpg\";s:5:\"sizes\";a:1:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:18:\"ethan2-150x113.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:150;s:6:\"height\";i:113;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:10:\"ima