ning to your character, and let the stakes be high.','Rafe Chase, company member','','publish','open','open','','rafe-chase-company-member','','','2014-05-23 11:00:54','2014-05-23 18:00:54','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=quotes&#038;p=100',72,'quotes','',0),(101,2,'2013-12-28 14:33:03','2013-12-28 21:33:03','','quote1','','inherit','open','open','','quote1','','','2013-12-28 14:33:03','2013-12-28 21:33:03','',100,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/quote1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(103,2,'2013-12-28 16:44:35','2013-12-28 23:44:35','Do as much Improv as you can. Be loud.','Dave Dennison, company member','','publish','open','open','','dave-dennison-company-member','','','2014-05-23 11:00:50','2014-05-23 18:00:50','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=quotes&#038;p=103',71,'quotes','',0),(104,2,'2013-12-28 16:44:29','2013-12-28 23:44:29','','quote2','','inherit','open','open','','quote2','','','2013-12-28 16:44:29','2013-12-28 23:44:29','',103,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/quote2.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(107,2,'2013-12-30 14:44:50','2013-12-30 21:44:50','<h1>BATS Main Stage Company &amp; Coaches</h1>\r\n<p><strong>The BATS Main Stage Company</strong> is an ensemble of highly skilled actors specializing in spontaneity. Recognized as San Francisco’s premiere improvised theatre troupe, the BATS Company includes some of the country’s most talented improv actors — many of whom have shaped the artform of improvised theatre. Each is a master of the <a title=\"About Improvised Theatre\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/shows/about-improvised-theatre/\">BATS style of improv</a>, artistically expressing the hilarity, and poignancy, of the human condition.</p>\r\n<p><strong>All the coaches at BATS School of Improv</strong> are seasoned teachers and improvisers, with years of experience guiding students from improv basics to the intricacies of stagecraft and genre scene work. Our coaches specialize in creating a safe, constructive environment while using our teaching techniques to maximize learning and growth. Each is an approachable master of the <a title=\"About Improvised Theatre\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/shows/about-improvised-theatre/\">BATS style of improv</a>, artistically expressing the hilarity, and poignancy, of the human condition.</p>\r\n<p><a title=\"Shows\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/shows/\">See the show schedule »</a></p>','Company Members & Coaches','','publish','open','closed','','company-members-coaches','','','2015-02-27 12:44:39','2015-02-27 20:44:39','',6,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?page_id=107',51,'page','',0),(108,2,'2013-12-30 14:45:09','2013-12-30 21:45:09','<h1>Press &amp; Awards</h1>\r\n<p>For media requests, please contact <a href=\"http://www.hamiltoninkpr.com\" target=\"_blank\">Hamilton Ink</a> via <a href=\"mailto:stephanie@hamiltoninkpr.com\">email</a> or phone (415) 381-8198.</p>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignright wp-image-497\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/awards2014.png\" alt=\"awards\" width=\"120\" />Awards</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><b>Best Theater Company 2014 – <em>SF Bay Guardian: Best of the Bay</em></b></li>\r\n<li>Best Theater Company 2013 – <em>SF Bay Guardian: Best of the Bay</em></li>\r\n<li>Highly Recommended 2013 – <em>Frommer’s Travel Guide</em></li>\r\n<li>SFIF O.C.I.C Award 2013 – <em>San Francisco Improv Festival</em><em></em></li>\r\n<li>Best Theater Company 2012 – <em>SF Bay Guardian: Best of the Bay</em></li>\r\n<li>Highly Recommended 2012 – <em>Frommer’s Travel Guide</em></li>\r\n<li>Highly Recommended 2011 – <em>Frommer’s Travel Guide</em></li>\r\n<li>Highly Recommended 2010 – <em>Frommer’s Travel Guide</em></li>\r\n<li>Best Theater Company 2009 – <em>San Francisco Chronicle: Bay List</em></li>\r\n<li>Best Comedy Troupe 2008 – <em>SF Weekly: Best of San Francisco</em></li>\r\n<li>Best Theater Company 2007 – SF Bay Guardian: Best of the Bay</li>\r\n<li>Best First Date Spot 2007 – SF Bay Guardian: Best of the Bay</li>\r\n<li>BATS Improv Day: Nov. 10, 2006 - Declared by the City of San Francisco</li>\r\n<li>Best Theater Company 2006 – SF Bay Guardian: Best of the Bay</li>\r\n<li>Best First Date Spot 2006 – SF Bay Guardian: Best of the Bay</li>\r\n<li>Most Spontaneous Date Night 2006 – <em>7 x 7 Magazine</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','Press & Awards','','publish','open','closed','','press-awards','','','2014-12-10 23:49:51','2014-12-11 07:49:51','',6,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?page_id=108',50,'page','',0),(109,2,'2013-12-30 14:45:21','2013-12-30 21:45:21','<h1><img class=\"alignright wp-image-489 size-full\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/about-it.jpg\" alt=\"about-it\" width=\"215\" height=\"323\" />About Improvised Theatre &amp; BATS-Style Improv</h1>\r\n<h3>What is “improvised theatre” anyway?</h3>\r\n<p>Simply put, improvised theatre is theatre that’s created on the spot without a script.</p>\r\n<h3>What is BATS-style improv?</h3>\r\n<p>The BATS style of improvised theatre is unique in the improv landscape — a one-of-a-kind blend of theatre, comedy, and acting that’s quite different from stand-up or sketch. We pioneered this form of theatre more than 27 years ago, and it continues to evolve as we do.</p>\r\n<p>The BATS style of improv has been described as radical cooperation in action. Our ensemble of actors seamlessly works together to create a rich, theatrical world inhabited by truthfully acted, well-developed characters. The result is a unique and thrilling theatre experience that stands toe-to-toe with scripted work. The collaborative imagination can go places the solitary imagination cannot.</p>\r\n<p>At BATS Improv, we’re all about the story, not jokes. We don’t have stock characters or established bits. Instead, we aim to create theatre that tells a story collaboratively and spontaneously. You may find yourself touched enough to cry. More likely, you’ll laugh until you cry. Everything you see at BATS is created on the spot and in the moment. It’s real. It’s funny. It’s theatre.</p>\r\n<p class=\"nomobile\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>See BATS in action →</strong></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-490\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/about-it2.jpg\" alt=\"about-it2\" width=\"215\" height=\"159\" />What is “shortform” improv?</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Our shortform shows (usually on Friday), like our signature competition Theatresports<sup>TM</sup>, are fast-paced, exciting, and highly interactive. This form of improvised theatre is filled with scenes, songs, games, and lots of audience suggestions and participation. In our shortform shows, our actors generally get a new suggestion before each scene, and each scene, song, or game is its own complete story. If you like variety, high energy, and lots of different stories in one night, our Friday shows are for you.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">What is “longform” improv?</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Our longform shows (usually on Saturday) are full-length, narrative, genre-driven stories based on audience suggestions. We present our longform shows in a variety of genres and styles throughout the year. In our longform shows, our actors generally get several suggestions at the beginning of the show and use those suggestions as their inspiration in creating a single story that unfolds like a play or a film. BATS longform shows are an exhilarating and impressive form of improvised theatre created and developed by our own <a title=\"Company Members\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/shows/company-members/\">Main Stage Company</a> actors.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">What is Theatresports? What is the Harold? What is . . . ?</h3>\r\n<p>We use many different shortform and longform formats throughout the year as the structure for the games and stories we create. Some involve rules and mechanisms to help us unlock greater creativity; others are more genre, or theme, driven. And many were developed here at BATS by our own company members!</p>\r\n<h4><a name=\"shortform\"></a><strong>Shortform</strong></h4>\r\n<p><strong>Theatresports<sup>TM</sup></strong> — <em>Our signature improv competition<br /></em>Theatresports is a fast-paced, exciting, and highly interactive night of improvised theatre competition, complete with Olympic-style judges. For each tournament, the BATS Main Stage Company splits into several teams. Every Friday during the tournament, two teams face off by performing scenes, games, and even musical numbers – all completely improvised and inspired by your suggestions. The team with the most points is declared the winner and moves one step closer to the championship match.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Director’s Cut!</strong><i> – Fast-paced improv, served raw, with consequences<br /></i>In Director’s Cut! six improv directors do battle to bring their passion to life. To do so, they’ll need to get the work they want from their fellow improvisers by directing them – live in the moment. Actors can even be tossed out of a scene and replaced! If the director succeeds and creates a “hit,” you, the audience, can reward them with a star, but if they “flop,” you get to demand better by punishing them on the spot (no, really – a recent punishment required company member Ken Robertson to give his cell number to the entire audience so that they could text him to shape up). This is not just theatre, it’s theatre with consequences!</p>\r\n<p><strong>DuoProv</strong><i> – Our newest improv competition<br /></i>In the first half of DuoProv, three teams of two improvisers -- each representing their favorite genre -- compete for the right to have the whole cast perform their genre in the second half. Each show is completely improvised and completely unique. Come root for your favorite genres and improvisers!</p>\r\n<p><strong>The Harold</strong><i> – Classic free-form improvisation<br /></i>Completely based on your suggestions, our cast of talented improvisers create scenes, play games, and improvise songs as they seamlessly weave together a magical night of improvised theatre. There is no structure, there are no rules, and anything can happen! The Harold, popularized in Chicago improv circles, is considered by many to be the \"grand-daddy of all improv formats\" and was invented by Del Close right here in San Francisco! Now, BATS Improv is proud to bring the Harold back home. </p>\r\n<p><strong>Super Scene</strong><i> – Six genres in one night<br /></i>Super Scene is a fast-paced, rip-roaring theatre competition featuring five directors creating five unique, completely improvised stories, each with a unique tone or genre, But there’s a catch – stories unfold one scene at a time, round by round. After each round, the audience gets to choose which stories continue on and which story is eliminated. This process continues, and the scenes evolve, until the final round, where only one story remains and the SUPER SCENE is performed.</p>\r\n<h4><a name=\"longform\"></a><strong>Longform</strong></h4>\r\n<p><strong>Double Feature™</strong><i> – Two stories, four actors<br /></i>A cast of four talented improvisers (and one musician) spontaneously create two distinct stories, unique in genre, tone, and character – each story inpired by an original title supplied by the audience. The improvisers develop these stories scene by scene, seamlessly alternating storylines. Double Feature’s unique structure heightens the moment, and the fun, by requiring the improvisers to play multiple characters as they bounce back and forth between stories. Created by Company Member Rafe Chase, Double Feature is one of BATS most popular shows.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Family Drama</strong><i> – And you thought your family was hilariously weird!<br /></i>Family Drama uniquely blends the compelling narrative of a three-act stage play with the excitement and surprise of improvisation. Like many traditional American plays, the story will unfold in real time, on a single set, and with each actor portraying only one character. But this drama is completely improvised – the only thing the actors know is that their characters are somehow related and that they are getting together for the holidays. The audience selects the title for the show, which inspires the relationships, themes, and stories. Everything else is created right in front of your eyes!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Improvised Holiday Musical</strong><i> – Perfect for the family<br /></i>Snuggled between Christmas and New Year’s, our Holiday Musical is completely improvised fun for the whole family! Set during the holidays and inspired by your suggestions, our actors will create a full-length musical that will warm your heart and fill your belly with laughter.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The Naked Stage</strong><i> – Improvised theatre, pure and uncut<br /></i>The charm and power of classic American theatre meets the exciting, unpredictable nature of improvisation. We can\'t tell you what will happen or what the play will be about (since we won\'t know until we\'re doing it), but it\'s sure to be some of the most crisp, theatrical, and side-splitting theatre ever created without a script!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Improvised Shakespeare, Film Noir, Western, Broadway Musical, Murdery Mystery, other genre<br /></strong>No, we haven’t found previously unpublished works of The Bard, Raymond Chandler, Sergio Leone, Rogers &amp; Hammerstein, or Agatha Christie — but you’ll think we did! Starting with a title chosen by you, our skilled company creates a full-length play in the style and language of the genre. From Improvised Downton Abbey to Improvised Trek, these themed shows are among our most popular.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>What? More questions?</h3>\r\n<p>Have more questions about BATS shows, how to plan your visit, or anything else related to our shows? Check out <a title=\"Shows\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/shows/\">Shows &amp; Schedule</a> and <a title=\"Show FAQs\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/shows/show-faqs/\">Show FAQs</a>. If they don’t give you what you need, feel free to <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"mailto:shows@improv.org\">contact us</a>.</p>\r\n','About Improvised Theatre & BATS-Style Improv','','publish','open','closed','','about-improvised-theatre','','','2014-06-12 09:23:28','2014-06-12 16:23:28','',6,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?page_id=109',49,'page','',0),(110,2,'2013-12-30 14:45:31','2013-12-30 21:45:31','<h1>Frequently Asked Questions About BATS Improv Shows</h1><h3>Logistics: Showtimes, Tickets, Directions, Parking</h3>','Show FAQs','','publish','open','closed','','show-faqs','','','2014-05-31 08:53:06','2014-05-31 15:53:06','',6,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?page_id=110',56,'page','',0),(111,2,'2013-12-30 14:45:41','2013-12-30 21:45:41','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-492\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/group1.jpg\" alt=\"group1\" width=\"332\" height=\"236\" />Group Tickets</h1>\r\n<p>What do birthday parties, family reunions, conventions,  co-worker cliques, corporate morale building, sports teams, youth groups, bachelorette parties, and marching bands have in common?</p>\r\n<p>Someone who makes a duck face while taking a selfie? <em>Maybe.</em></p>\r\n<p>They love group outings to a BATS Improv show? <em>Definitely.</em></p>\r\n<p>A BATS performance is a terrific outing for any group of folks who want to have fun, and we’ve happily hosted every kind of group you can think of at one time or another. If you’re looking for a dysfunctional family stress-fest or corporate PowerPoint snoozapalooza, try elsewhere. At BATS, everyone gets to enjoy themselves while doing things they rarely have the opportunity or freedom to do. Whoever said “you can’t please everyone” never booked a group event at BATS.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-493\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/group2.jpg\" alt=\"group2\" width=\"127\" height=\"134\" />Buy Six Tickets and Save</h3>\r\n<p>Purchase a six-pack of tickets for $90 (a savings of $30 over door price). Come to six shows on your own, or bring a friend to three, or treat two-thirds of the Supreme Court to one, or (you get the picture).</p>\r\n<p>Available at the Bayfront Theater box office or <a title=\"Gift Certificates\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/school/gift-certificates/\">online</a>.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-494\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/group3.jpg\" alt=\"group3\" width=\"215\" height=\"155\" />Groups of 10-200</h3>\r\n<p>Tickets for groups of 10 or more start at just $14 each. When you purchase 10+ tickets through our website, you will automatically receive a group discount.</p>\r\n<p>BATS\' <a title=\"Bayfront Theater Rentals\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/bats-on-the-go/bayfront-theater-rentals/\">Bayfront Theater</a> can accommodate groups of 10 to 200.  For more information about group rates or if you have a particularly large group attending a show, please email <a href=\"mailto:shows@improv.org\">shows@improv.org</a> or call (415) 474-6776.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-495\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/group4.jpg\" alt=\"group4\" width=\"215\" height=\"155\" />Groups of 200+</h3>\r\n<p>For groups of more than 200 people, <a title=\"BATS On-the-Go\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/bats-on-the-go/\">BATS On-the-Go</a> specializes in custom off-site performances. Our custom entertainment is the antidote for bad cover bands, awkward icebreaker games, and other event fails. Inspired by your group’s ideas, our improv professionals will create a personalized show that turns your party into an engaging, unforgettable occasion.</p>\r\n<p>We\'ll work with you to develop the perfect program for your group — from short scenes, stories, and songs to a complete improvised murder mystery to Theatresports<sup>TM</sup>, our knock-down-drag-out improv rumble!</p>\r\n<p>All of our shows are 100% unscripted and unplanned. Whatever the theme, the show is a journey that brings people together through shared fun, laughter, and creativity.</p>\r\n<p>Please email <a href=\"mailto:otg@improv.org\">otg@improv.org</a> or call (415) 474-6776 to learn more about the custom entertainment we can provide your group.</p>\r\n<hr />','Group Tickets','','publish','open','closed','','groups','','','2015-09-28 16:37:21','2015-09-28 23:37:21','',6,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?page_id=111',55,'page','',0),(112,2,'2013-12-30 14:45:56','2013-12-30 21:45:56','<h1>Gift Certificates</h1><p>Tickets to BATS Improv shows and classes make great gifts! Gift certificates can be purchased in any amount and can be used just like cash at BATS Improv toward classes, shows, books, or merchandise.</p><p>Not sure exactly what BATS gift to give? These certificates are our most popular:</p><p>[content_block id=535]</p><p>[content_block id=538]</p><p>[content_block id=540]</p><hr /><h3>Purchase a Gift Certificate in any amount</h3><p>Enter the amount of your gift below and click <strong>Order Now</strong>. <br />[content_block id=552]</p><hr /><h3>Gift Certificate FAQs</h3><p><strong>How do I use a gift certificate to buy tickets? How do I use my ticket six-pack?<br /></strong>Please email <a href=\"mailto:shows@improv.org\">shows@improv.org</a> to make a reservation. Include your name and the number of tickets you will be purchasing with your gift certificate. Making a reservation guarantees you a seat even if the show sells out. On the night of the show, bring your gift certificate to the box office. Tickets with a reservation will be deducted from your gift certificate total at the advance price of $17 each. (Note that if you have a ticket six-pack, both reserved tickets and door tickets will be deducted at $15 each.)</p><p>Without a reservation, you can use your gift certificate just like cash. Please note that seating is on a space available basis and some shows do sell out. Tickets without a reservation will be deducted at the door price of $20 per ticket. (Note that if you have a ticket six-pack, both reserved tickets and door tickets will be deducted at $15 each.)</p><p><strong>How do I use a gift certificate to pay for a class?<br /></strong>Please email <a href=\"mailto:registrar@improv.org\">registrar@improv.org</a> to enroll and pay for your class with a gift certificate. Include your name and the class name, instructor, and starting date. The class tuition will be deducted from your gift certificate total. Any balance due will need to be paid at the time of enrollment to guarantee your place in the class.</p><p><strong>How do I use a gift certificate to purchase books or merchandise?<br /></strong>Gift certificates may be used to buy books or BATS merch in person at the Bayfront Theater or in a BATS School of Improv class only. If you have specific questions, please email <a href=\"mailto:registrar@improv.org\">registrar@improv.org</a>.</p><hr />','Gift Certificates','','publish','open','closed','','gift-certificates','','','2014-05-30 15:34:44','2014-05-30 22:34:44','',6,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?page_id=112',54,'page','',0),(113,2,'2013-12-30 14:46:06','2013-12-30 21:46:06','<p><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-470\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/student-shows.jpg\" alt=\"student-shows\" width=\"332\" height=\"236\" /></p><h1>Student Shows</h1><p>Our student shows present the talented new improvisers from the <a title=\"School of Improv\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/school/\">BATS School of Improv</a>. Most Sundays, our students hone their craft during <strong>Student Showcases</strong>,<strong> Sunday Cave Matches</strong>,<strong> Theatresports™ Tournaments</strong>, and other special shows.</p><p>You’ll see a fun show featuring the next generation of San Francisco improv for less than a movie! And though it may be true that our student improvisers are not as experienced as our Main Stage Company members, rough around the edges also means fresh and innovative. Catch tomorrow’s stars on stage at BATS. You’ll be saying you ‘saw them when . . . ’</p><p><strong>All shows are $10 at the door (no advance sales). All shows are at 7:00 PM unless otherwise noted.</strong></p><p><a href=\"#student-shows-schedule\">See the Student Show schedule »</a></p><hr /><h3>Sunday Student Shows</h3><p>Our <strong>Student Showcases</strong> each feature an ensemble of BATS students who have been training together on performing a specific genre or format.</p><p>Our <strong>Sunday</strong> <strong>Cave Matches</strong> feature ensembles that are a mix of students, company members, and coaches. Each team has 38 minutes to do whatever they like. At the end of the night the audience votes on their favorite ensemble. The winner is crowned champion and returns to face a new challenger the following week.</p><p>Our <strong>Sunday</strong> <strong>Theatresports</strong> shows feature teams of BATS students facing off in our signature improv theatre competition series of improvised scenes, songs, and games. </p><p><span style=\"color: #b22b05;\"><strong>Want to try improv yourself?</strong></span> Think you’ve got what it takes to perform in a student show? Student shows are open to current students of <a title=\"School of Improv\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/school/\">BATS School of Improv</a>. <strong>Not a student?</strong> We offer classes for every age and every level. <a title=\"Foundation 1\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/school/foundation-1/\">Beginner classes</a> start every month.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>','Student Shows','','publish','open','closed','','student-shows','','','2014-06-01 03:03:54','2014-06-01 10:03:54','',6,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?page_id=113',53,'page','',0),(114,2,'2013-12-30 14:46:41','2013-12-30 21:46:41',' 