2014-04-09 14:13:27','2014-04-09 21:13:27','','give-button','','inherit','open','open','','give-button','','','2014-04-09 14:13:27','2014-04-09 21:13:27','',15,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/give-button.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(324,2,'2014-04-09 14:13:30','2014-04-09 21:13:30','','support-button','','inherit','open','open','','support-button','','','2014-04-09 14:13:30','2014-04-09 21:13:30','',15,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/support-button.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(325,2,'2014-04-09 14:13:32','2014-04-09 21:13:32','','support1','','inherit','open','open','','support1','','','2014-04-09 14:13:32','2014-04-09 21:13:32','',15,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/support1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(326,2,'2014-04-09 14:13:35','2014-04-09 21:13:35','','support2','','inherit','open','open','','support2','','','2014-04-09 14:13:35','2014-04-09 21:13:35','',15,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/support2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(327,2,'2014-04-09 14:13:37','2014-04-09 21:13:37','','support3','','inherit','open','open','','support3','','','2014-04-09 14:13:37','2014-04-09 21:13:37','',15,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/support3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(328,2,'2014-04-09 14:13:40','2014-04-09 21:13:40','','support4','','inherit','open','open','','support4','','','2014-04-09 14:13:40','2014-04-09 21:13:40','',15,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/support4.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(332,3,'2014-04-10 12:47:35','2014-04-10 19:47:35','<h1>Jason Leal</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Company Member </strong>since 2014</p>\r\n<p>Jason has been studying improv and performing since 2002. He has had the privilege of performing with some of the Bay Area’s best improvisors and ensembles.</p>\r\n<p>Jason hails from Fresno but pretends he’s a San Francisco native. He also knows all the words to Poco’s 1979 hit “Crazy Love.”</p>','Jason Leal','','publish','open','open','','jason-leal','','','2014-12-18 18:36:56','2014-12-19 02:36:56','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=actors&#038;p=332',18,'actors','',0),(333,3,'2014-04-10 12:45:21','2014-04-10 19:45:21','','jasonLeal_236x236','','inherit','open','open','','jasonleal_236x236','','','2014-04-10 12:45:21','2014-04-10 19:45:21','',332,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/jasonLeal_236x236.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(335,3,'2014-04-10 13:45:45','2014-04-10 20:45:45','<h1>Ethan Karson</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Company Member </strong>since 2014</p>\r\n<p>A native of Massachusetts, Ethan Karson has been an improv performer for more than ten years. He trained in Los Angeles with Cynthia Szigeti, who also taught Conan O\'Brien and Lisa Kudrow. He was a member of the main stage sketch and improv companies at the Acme Comedy Theatre, where he wrote as well as acted.</p>\r\n<p>Ethan joined the BATS community as a student in 2009 and played in Cave Match teams in 2011 (“Live Studio Audience,” an improvised sitcom) and 2012 (\"The No. 1 Ladies Improv Agency,\" an improvised pirate adventure). His first appearance on the BATS main stage was as a company guest, beginning in 2012.</p>\r\n<p>Ethan performed with Pixar\'s in-house improv troupe the IMPROVibles for five years and now works as a software engineer at Twitter.</p>','Ethan Karson','','publish','open','open','','ethan-karson','','','2014-12-18 17:56:03','2014-12-19 01:56:03','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=actors&#038;p=335',19,'actors','',0),(336,3,'2014-04-10 13:43:50','2014-04-10 20:43:50','','ethan_236x236','','inherit','open','open','','ethan_236x236','','','2014-04-10 13:43:50','2014-04-10 20:43:50','',335,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/ethan_236x236.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(345,2,'2014-04-11 10:10:25','2014-04-11 17:10:25','<p>“I recommend BATS training to any organization that wants to have creative people that cooperate and cooperative people that create, assuming they can stand the fun.”</p>\r\n<p class=\"quoted\">— Randy Nelson, Dean of Pixar University, Pixar Animation Studios</p>','Quote 1','','publish','closed','closed','','quote-1','','','2014-05-27 20:05:26','2014-05-28 03:05:26','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=content_block&#038;p=345',0,'content_block','',0),(348,2,'2014-04-11 10:57:53','2014-04-11 17:57:53','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-766\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/OTG_Custom_Training_IMG_4671.jpg\" alt=\"OTG_Custom_Training_IMG_4671\" width=\"332\" height=\"221\" />About our Training and Workshops</h1>\r\n<p>Every organization benefits from having creative, adaptable employees with fine-tuned communication, leadership, and collaboration skills. The only question becomes, “How can they best learn these skills — while having a great time?” We added that last part because it’s what sets our trainings apart, and what makes them so effective. </p>\r\n<p>BATS\' Improv @ Work will create a training fully customized to your organization’s needs — from enhancing communication skills to team building to creative risk taking, for large or small groups, three hours to multi-day.</p>\r\n<p><a title=\"Workshops &amp; Pricing\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/onthego/workshops-pricing/\">See a list of sample workshops »</a></p>\r\n<p>We can also work with your organization to design ongoing and resident trainer programs to extend the principles you have learned to other groups and departments, or to create an episodic or ongoing series for your team.</p>\r\n<p>We can bring the training to your organization or an off-site facility, or hold it at our very own 200-seat Bayfront Theater.</p>\r\n<p>Provide your team with experience in successful collaboration with Improv @ Work. Pixar, Kaiser Permanente, YouTube, and many others have. <a title=\"What Our Clients Say\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/bats-on-the-go/what-our-clients-say/\">See what they had to say »</a></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Why should my organization do an improv training?</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">\"Survival is ultimately dependent on the ability to change and evolve.\"</span> </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">— Charles Darwin</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">“Improv skills are life skills, and work skills.\"</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">— BATS Improv</p>\r\n<p>Business today moves fast, and adaptable individuals and teams have the advantage. Whether you work for a Fortune 500, a tech startup, or a social justice nonprofit, your team must be able to adapt, create, communicate, and collaborate. </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Improv teaches vital skills for coping in a dynamic world. The skills we use to improvise together -- listening, spontaneity, focus, flexibility, resilience, intelligent risk taking -- help people work better together.</li>\r\n<li>Improv is a perfect model for creative collaboration. We can unlock the vast creativity and innovative power of small teams, departments, and whole organizations.</li>\r\n<li>Improv gives you powerful communication tools. We can deliver successful methodologies for creating stories, narratives, and dialogue -- the type of communication that has the power to inspire team members and compel customers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The principles and skills of improvisation are identifiable, learnable, and repeatable. And BATS On-the-Go can teach them to you.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Skills Covered in BATS On-the-Go Group Training</h3>\r\n<p class=\"Body1\"><strong>Teamwork / Collaboration</strong> <br />Teamwork and collaboration are healthy practices for any organization, yet most work groups have too little experience with them to be good team players. Our improv training will strengthen your team’s dynamics, build rapport and trust, and harness the power of making your teammates look good.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Body1\"><strong>Communication</strong> <br />Stories help you present ideas. Common stories strengthen teams. Beyond talking and listening, our improv trainings will help you deliver and receive messages and use body language and nonverbal communication cues to enhance your story.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Body1\"><strong>Brainstorming / Unlocking Creativity</strong><br />Sometimes the best ideas come not by working independently in isolation but by allowing thoughts, hypotheses, and even fancies to bubble up as you and your team play off each other’s contributions. Collaborative, creative problem solving often starts with a blue sky brainstorming session. Our improv training will teach you to express your ideas without self-judgment and learn new ways to listen, think expansively, and build on the ideas of others.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Body1\"><strong>Spontaneity / Flexibility</strong><br />Successful leaders and companies have something in common with improvisers: We are adaptable, attentive risk takers capable of responding in the moment. Our improv training will help you learn to be present in order to assess the situation, think on your feet, and respond more effectively. </p>\r\n<p class=\"Body1\"><strong>Leadership</strong><br />Organizations need skilled leaders to function effectively. Our improv training will build awareness, commitment, positive approach, risk taking, empathy, and shared control to enhance your ability to contribute to your team\'s vision and success. </p>\r\n<p class=\"Body1\"><strong>Focus / Presence</strong><br />Being present and staying in the moment are critical to effective communication, collaboration, and leadership. Our improv training will teach your group methodologies for staying focused, even under pressure.</p>\r\n<p class=\"Body1\"><strong>Intelligent Risk Taking</strong><br />The quality of our stories, and our work, is improved by daring to risk mistakes. In accepting and embracing mistakes, we co-create a greater story. Taking risks fuels creativity, and applying collaborative creativity leads to innovation. Failing gloriously, early and often, good-naturedly, and graciously leads to greater future successes. </p>\r\n<p class=\"Body1\"><strong>Negotiation</strong><br />Improv is essentially an ongoing negotiation between players. Our improv training will improve your negotiation and creative problem solving skills by providing you with the tools for listening, inquiry, reading nonverbal cues, connection, trust, thinking on your feet, confidence, creativity, imagining possibilities, and being present (in the moment and with others).</p>\r\n<p class=\"Body1\"><strong>Resilience</strong><br />Resilient teams bounce back from unexpected setbacks, or any type of unexpected outcome. Our improv training wil help your group build confidence, manage expectations, respond quickly and positively to change and challenge, and stay calmly energized under pressure.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>We’d love to help your organization build these skills while having fun!</h3>\r\n<p>Contact us to learn how BATS On-the-Go’s programs can be customized for your needs. Don’t worry if you’re not sure what you want or what training might work best — we’re happy to walk you through all the options, and brainstorm a couple more. Improvising fun solutions is what we do best! </p>\r\n<p><strong>BATS On-the-Go</strong><br /><strong><a href=\"mailto:OTG@improv.org\">OTG@improv.org<br /></a></strong>(415) 474-6776</p>','Group Training','','publish','open','open','','group-training','','','2015-11-01 03:01:54','2015-11-01 11:01:54','',13,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?page_id=348',31,'page','',0),(349,2,'2014-04-11 10:59:33','2014-04-11 17:59:33','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-773\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/otg-1.jpg\" alt=\"otg-1\" width=\"332\" height=\"221\" />Custom Performance &amp; Holiday Events</h1>\r\n<p>By definition, improvisation <em>is</em> custom entertainment. It cannot be reproduced, no matter how often our audiences may suspect something we perform is scripted. BATS Improv provides entertainment that is customized for YOU, and allows YOUR TEAM to share the spotlight! Our cast can incorporate your employees, family members, friends, colleagues — any willing volunteers, that is — into the show to make it a memorable experience for everyone.</p>\r\n<p>BATS Improv provides customized, hilarious, interactive entertainment for holiday parties, too. Contact us for more information or to book a BATS ensemble and secure the date of your choice, any day of the week.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Some of our most popular formats include:</h3>\r\n<p><strong>BATS Improv Trio<br /></strong>Amaze the people at your gathering with a one-of-a-kind improv performance — just for them!</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>3 performers</li>\r\n<li>30-minutes to 1 hour of short scenes, stories, and songs inspired by audience suggestions</li>\r\n<li>Lots of audience participation and variety<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Theatresports™ Main Event<br /></strong>Two teams compete in a full-length performance of <a title=\"About Improvised Theatre\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/shows/about-improvised-theatre/#shortform\">Theatresports</a>, our signature format.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>6 performers</li>\r\n<li>90-minutes to 2 hours, with intermission, of short scenes, stories, and songs based on audience suggestions</li>\r\n<li>Lots of audience participation and variety<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-774\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/otg-2.jpg\" alt=\"otg-2\" width=\"215\" height=\"143\" />Theatresports™</strong> <strong>Shorts<br /></strong>Two teams compete in an abridged version of <a title=\"About Improvised Theatre\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/shows/about-improvised-theatre/#shortform\">Theatresports</a>, our signature format.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>6 performers</li>\r\n<li>30 minutes to 1 hour of short scenes, stories, and songs based on audience suggestions</li>\r\n<li>Lots of audience participation and variety<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Long-form Genre Show<br /></strong>Our world-famous long-form genre shows will make your group ask \"How much of that was actually improvised?!\" The answer is always \"All of it!”</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We offer completely improvised musicals and plays in the style of Shakespeare, Westerns, Film Noir, Science Fiction, and many other genres. Content can be personalized to include references to your event, guest of honor, industry, personnel, and more. And all formats incorporate suggestions and ideas that are generated by your audience.</li>\r\n<li>Number of performers and length vary</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><em>Each program is individually created and custom designed for each client. Performance pricing will vary based on length and complexity of show, number of performers, and distance from San Francisco city limits. </em></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-776\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/otg-3.jpg\" alt=\"otg-3\" width=\"332\" height=\"221\" />Add a Training Component</h3>\r\n<p>Improv is about more than making people laugh -- it’s about collaboration, listening, unlocking creativity, spontaneity, intelligent risk taking, and focus. You can add a workshop component to any of our shows to help your group strengthen these skills while having a great time. BATS On-the-Go will create a <a title=\"Training Programs\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/onthego/training-programs/\">group training</a> fully customized to your event. </p>\r\n<p>And you can even be your own party’s entertainment! Our <strong>Improv Class &amp; Team Performance </strong>workshop prepares your team to perform an improv show of your own after just one day\'s training.  <a title=\"Workshops &amp; Pricing\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/onthego/workshops-pricing/\">See more workshop options »</a></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>We’d love to collaborate with you to create an entertaining, unique, unforgettable event!</h3>\r\n<p>Contact us to learn how BATS On-the-Go’s programs can be customized for your needs. Don’t worry if you’re not sure what you want or what show might work best -- we’re happy to walk you through all the options, and brainstorm a couple more. Improvising fun solutions is what we do best!</p>\r\n<p><strong>BATS On-the-Go</strong><br /><strong><a href=\"mailto:OTG@improv.org\">OTG@improv.org<br /></a></strong>(415) 474-6776</p>','Custom Entertainment & Holiday Events','','publish','open','open','','custom-entertainment-holiday-events','','','2015-11-01 02:51:52','2015-11-01 10:51:52','',13,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?page_id=349',29,'page','',0),(350,2,'2014-04-11 11:00:06','2014-04-11 18:00:06','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-778\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/theatre1.jpg\" alt=\"theatre1\" width=\"332\" height=\"221\" />Bayfront Theater Rentals </h1><p>Located along the San Francisco waterfront in the historic Fort Mason Center between Fisherman\'s Wharf and the Golden Gate Bridge, the 200-seat Bayfront Theater is the ideal place to hold a performance, conference, or gathering. The theater features a modern proscenium, auditorium-quality seating, a concessions stand with cafe seating, and both on- and off-stage wheelchair accessibility.</p><p>Performer and house manager amenities include a green room, two dressing rooms, a fully built-out ticket counter, a light booth with sound and light board, and a newly upgraded lighting grid.</p><p><a title=\"Map &amp; Directions\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/about-us/map-directions/\"> Map, Directions &amp; Nearby »</a></p><hr />\r\n<p><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-779\" style=\"margin: 0 0 20px;\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/theatre2.jpg\" alt=\"theatre2\" width=\"32%\" /> <img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-780\" style=\"margin: 0 2% 20px;\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/theatre3.jpg\" alt=\"theatre3\" width=\"32%\" /> <img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-781\" style=\"margin: 0 0 20px;\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/theatre4.jpg\" alt=\"theatre4\" width=\"32%\" /></p><h3>About Fort Mason Center</h3><p><a href=\"http://www.fortmason.org\" target=\"_blank\">Fort Mason Center</a> is located in the historic piers and buildings of Lower Fort Mason in San Francisco\'s Marina District. This former military base offers the opportunity to experience Bay Area culture in a unique environment, focusing on the visual and performing arts, humanities, education, ecology, and recreation.</p><p>A National Historic Landmark and part of the Golden Gate National Recreation Area, the Center houses more than 40 nonprofit organizations and is the setting for more than 15,000 meetings, conferences, performances, and special events, attended by 1.5 million visitors each year.</p><p>Fort Mason Center has <a href=\"http://www.fortmason.org/aboutus/visitor-information\" target=\"_blank\">paid parking</a>. Marina Green along the water, a short walking distance, has a free lot.</p><p>On Friday evenings, Fort Mason Center hosts <a href=\"http://offthegridsf.com/markets/fort-mason-center\" target=\"_blank\">Off the Grid</a>, a food and music event featuring varied cuisine from Bay Area restaurants and food trucks.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Contact Us</h3><p>To request more information about renting the Bayfront Theater, including available dates and a rate quote, please contact us.</p><p><strong>BATS Improv</strong><br />(415) 474-6776<br /><a href=\"mailto:BATS@improv.org\">BATS@improv.org</a></p>','Bayfront Theater Rentals','','publish','open','open','','bayfront-theater-rentals','','','2014-05-31 15:38:02','2014-05-31 22:38:02','',13,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?page_id=350',28,'page','',0),(351,2,'2014-04-11 11:00:48','2014-04-11 18:00:48','<h1>What Our Clients Say</h1><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">I recommend BATS training to any organization that wants to have creative people that cooperate and cooperative people that create, assuming they can stand the fun.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– Randy Nelson, Dean of Pixar University, Pixar Animation Studios</p><hr /><p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Our whole team was talking about how the session exceeded our expectations. [It\'s] a unique activity that is meaningful and fun. In [my coworker\'s] Will\'s words, the session was \'a really rare combo of fun and relevance not often experienced in team off sites. Our trainer was terrific.\'</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">I hugely appreciated all of the pre-work and thought that went into the session. You are clearly tremendous professionals, and I am so glad that this resource is available for teams!</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– Joanne Yun, YouTube Google</p><hr /><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">It was a very successful program. [The BATS trainers] energized the group. Their exercises brought us together as clinicians in ways we had not experienced before.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– Dr. Scott Abramson, Kaiser Permanente Medical Group </p><hr /><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">BATS Improv provided SAP with a great team building session! The team building exercises were listed as one of the highlights at our 2-1/2 day off-site meeting. [The trainers] were professional, funny, and encouraging. The group laughed a lot and learned how to communicate better.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– Marie Goodell, SAP</p><hr /><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">[BATS] exceeded our expectations. It was nothing but enjoyable for everyone.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– Foote Cone &amp; Belding </p><hr /><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">I wanted to let you know how completely amazed and delighted our entire office was with Friday\'s training sessions. Everyone had a wonderful time, we learned a lot, and we got to know each other really well, which was the primary goal of our day. There have been many many comments about what a great teacher [the trainer] is, and how people truly enjoyed the day (and they want to know when we can do it again).</span></p><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Thank you for helping us set it up, and thank you for your hard work in making it all happen.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– Paula Jenkins, Tribal DDB San Francisco</p><hr /><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">We got a lot of benefit out of the session. [Our BATS trainer] was great to work with, was very comfortable with our group, and I felt like we were able to cover a lot of ground in the short time we were together. The energy he brought in helped us all get engaged and really interact in a whole new way with each other. It was very illustrative of how our small team works and collaborates, and inspired us to do more.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">The evening of improv was a great way to cap the night and reinforced the lessons of open and helpful communication. Really happy with how things worked out. Hope we can do it again soon.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– Tim Gnatek, Blue Practice, Inc.</p><hr /><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">BATS On-the-Go was recommended as a good team building exercise by two different colleagues. . . . I liked how the training progressed throughout the afternoon, starting very simple and non-threatening, to getting more adventurous and fun. . . . I would recommend this as a unique team-building opportunity that is different from our typical events. Very good for experienced team members who think they have “seen it all.”</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– On-the-Go client (from anonymous survey) </p><hr /><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">It got everyone out of their shell and thinking quickly.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– On-the-Go client (from anonymous survey)</p><hr /><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">I had seen one of your Main Stage shows and loved it, so . . . when looking for entertainment for our holiday party, I decided to look you up to see if you guys did private functions. . . . I had a specific vision for format and everyone was really great with working with my requests and incorporating the venue into the performance. . . . Everyone was so great to work with and the show was fantastic! Really great experience the whole way through. You guys are so incredibly great at what you do, in every aspect from planning to performance!</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– On-the-Go client (from anonymous survey) </p><hr /><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">[What did I like most about the On-the-Go training?] Seeing the preconceived notions fall away as we did the various things the trainer requested us to do. . . . It was a great experience and really made our retreat memorable.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– On-the-Go client (from anonymous survey)</p><hr /><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">[What did I like most about the On-the-Go training?] The ability to relate to my co-workers in a completely different way from the day-to-day routine that everyone is used to. . . . [Would I recommend it?] Absolutely -- great value, totally new way for colleagues to get to know one another outside of the workplace, and left everyone talking and recounting memories of the event for days/weeks afterward.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– On-the-Go client (from anonymous survey)</p><hr /><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">[What did I like most about the On-the-Go training?] The debrief discussion after each exercise that ties the exercise back to an aspect of workplace behavior (e.g., collaboration, risk-taking). . . . [The On-the-Go director] was amazingly patient and customer-focused in our planning discussions!!</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– On-the-Go client (from anonymous survey)</p><hr /><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">[The trainer] was amazing and able to adapt his training exercises the morning of his presentation based on the information about our group and the current focus of our training. It was so impressive.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– On-the-Go client (from anonymous survey)</p><hr /><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">They made potentially awkward situations very safe feeling, allowing people to stretch outside of their comfort zone. . . . I have recommended the program and will continue to do so.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– On-the-Go client (from anonymous survey)</p><hr /><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">[What did I like most about the On-the-Go training?] The design support I received from [the On-the-Go director] in coming up with activities that built the specific skills I was focusing on. . . . Dynamic and effective way to learn, especially as it relates to how you present yourself under stress. . . . Look forward to working together soon!</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– On-the-Go client (from anonymous survey)</p><hr /><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">[The On-the-Go director] listened to what I wanted and communicated this to the trainers.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– On-the-Go client (from anonymous survey)</p><hr /><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">[The entertainment team] understood the audience (especially kids) and enabled participants and observers all to enjoy.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– On-the-Go client (from anonymous survey)</p><hr /><p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"> </span></p>','What Our Clients Say','','publish','open','open','','what-our-clients-say','','','2014-05-30 18:11:04','2014-05-31 01:11:04','',13,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?page_id=351',27,'page','',0),(352,2,'2014-04-11 11:02:11','2014-04-11 18:02:11',' ','','','publish','open','closed','','352','','','2015-11-10 19:53:58','2015-11-11 03:53:58','',13,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?p=352',7,'nav_menu_item','',0),(353,2,'2014-04-11 11:02:11','2014-04-11 18:02:11',' ','','','publish','open','closed','','353','','','2015-11-10 19:53:58','2015-11-11 03:53:58','',13,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?p=353',6,'nav_menu_item','',0),(354,2,'2014-04-11 11:02:11','2014-04-11 18:02:11','','Custom Performance<br>& Holiday Events','','publish','open','closed','','354','','','2015-11-10 19:53:58','2015-11-11 03:53:58','',13,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?p=354',5,'nav_menu_item','',0),(355,2,'2014-04-11 11:02:11','2014-04-11 18:02:11','','About our Training & Workshops','','publish','open','closed','','355','','','2015-11-10 19:53:58','2015-11-11 03:53:58','',13,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?p=355',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(356,2,'2014-04-14 14:01:54','2014-04-14 21:01:54','<h1><a href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/support_volunteer_company-players-05.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-757\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/support_volunteer_company-players-05.jpg\" alt=\"support_volunteer_company-players-05\" width=\"332\" height=\"221\" /></a>Volunteer at BATS</h1>\r\n<p>First off, we love, and need, our volunteers. <br /><strong>THANK YOU!!!</strong></p>\r\n<p>Volunteers are a critical part of the BATS Improv community and essential to our continued success as a nonprofit theatre. (You know we are a nonprofit, right?) Moreover, volunteering at BATS is fun and easy, gives you a behind-the-scenes look into live theatre, and is a great way to meet people who love improv as much as you do!</p>\r\n<p>Our volunteers come from all walks of life. Everyone is welcome. We have new volunteer opportunities every week, so no long-term commitment is required (though once you start, you might get hooked).</p>\r\n<p>Come, join the fun! Become a BATS volunteer and play a part in the only company in San Francisco that’s been blazing the improv trail since 1986. Here’s how.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Volunteer at a Show</h3>\r\n<p>As a Show Volunteer, you’ll see the show you support for free, plus get a free pass to come back and see another show on us. What’s more, you’ll get a unique behind-the-scenes experience at BATS Improv.</p>\r\n<p>Volunteer duties may include</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Ushering and greeting patrons</li>\r\n<li>Working the BATS Cafe</li>\r\n<li>Scorekeeping during Theatresports<sup>TM</sup> tournaments</li>\r\n<li>House Manager support</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://eepurl.com/TbPn\" target=\"_blank\">Sign up for our Show Volunteer Mailing List »</a></p>\r\n<p>You’ll get information on upcoming shows plus a link where you can sign up to volunteer on specific dates. It takes less than a minute, and you can unsubscribe at any time.</p>\r\n<p>If you have any additional questions about volunteering, please email <a href=\"mailto:BATS@improv.org\">BATS@improv.org</a> <br />or call <strong>(415) 474-6776</strong>.</p>','Volunteer','','publish','open','open','','volunteer','','','2015-01-21 11:54:27','2015-01-21 19:54:27','',15,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?page_id=356',13,'page','',0),(358,2,'2014-04-14 14:03:02','2014-04-14 21:03:02','<h1><a href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/support_foundation_IMG_0139.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-756\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/support_foundation_IMG_0139.jpg\" alt=\"support_foundation_IMG_0139\" width=\"332\" height=\"221\" /></a>Foundation &amp; Corporate Support</h1><p>BATS Improv is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit, and like most arts nonprofits, we rely on foundation and corporate support to subsidize our programming and community outreach work. Income earned from our loyal base of audience members, students, and group training &amp; entertainment clients regularly does cover more than 70% of our operating budget -- an impressive percentage these days -- but we would be grounded without the generous funding over the years from the following. Thank you!!!</p><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.sfgfta.org\" target=\"_blank\">Grants for the Arts</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.hewlett.org\" target=\"_blank\">William and Flora Hewlett Foundation</a></li><li>Richard A. Karp Charitable Foundation</li><li>eBay Foundation</li><li><a href=\"http://www.storynet.org\" target=\"_blank\">National Storytelling Network</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.sfartscommission.org\" target=\"_blank\">San Francisco Arts Commission</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.thesisters.org\" target=\"_blank\">The Sisters of Perpetual Indulgence</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.wattisfoundation.org\" target=\"_blank\">Phyllis C. Wattis Foundation</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.wellsfargo.com/about/charitable/index.jhtml\" target=\"_blank\">Wells Fargo Foundation</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.zellerbachfamilyfoundation.org\" target=\"_blank\">Zellerbach Family Foundation</a></li></ul>','Foundation Support','','publish','open','open','','foundation-support','','','2014-05-30 00:25:35','2014-05-30 07:25:35','',15,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?page_id=358',12,'page','',0),(360,2,'2014-04-14 14:04:11','2014-04-14 21:04:11','<h1>Why I Support BATS</h1><p class=\"Body1\"> </p><p class=\"Body1\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Love BATS with all my heart - makes my life better.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– BATS supporter (from anonymous survey)</p><hr /><p class=\"Body1\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">People describe BATS as a church because of the incredibly strong sense of community. . . . There is a very strong sense of belonging at BATS.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– BATS supporter (from anonymous survey)</p><hr /><p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">There’s something really magical there.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– BATS supporter (from anonymous survey)</p><hr /><p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">It\'s like therapy for normal people. You become a better human being. Plus it\'s lots of fun.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– BATS supporter (from anonymous survey)</p><hr /><p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Improv at BATS has changed my life.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– BATS supporter (from anonymous survey)</p><hr /><p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">You\'ll leave feeling better than when you arrived.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– BATS supporter (from anonymous survey)</p><hr /><p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">BATS does important work in the community.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– BATS supporter (from anonymous survey)</p><hr /><p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">[BATS] helps people look at life in a new &amp; unique way.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– BATS supporter (from anonymous survey)</p><hr /><p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">It surprises me that such great quality is not for profit.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– BATS supporter (from anonymous survey)</p><hr /><p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Keep making your partner look good. Community is what it\'s all about!</span></p><p style=\"text-align: right;\">– BATS supporter (from anonymous survey)</p><hr /><p>&nbsp;</p>','Why I Support BATS','','publish','open','open','','why-i-support-bats','','','2014-05-30 18:10:09','2014-05-31 01:10:09','',15,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?page_id=360',11,'page','',0),(361,2,'2014-04-14 14:04:35','2014-04-14 21:04:35',' ','','','pub