event started a chain reaction that eventually resulted in a BA in Theatre from UC San Diego and an MFA in Creative Writing from UC Riverside.</p>\r\n<p>Since 2003, Andy has improvised professionally with Flash Family and the Un-Scripted Theater Company, where he had the opportunity to train and perform in both shortform and narrative longform shows.</p>\r\n<p>He has been a busy improvisation coach since 2001, leading courses for ImprovWorks, UC Riverside, American Conservatory Theater, Cal Shakes, Un-Scripted Theater Company, and BATS Improv. Some of his most rewarding work has been with young people in San Mateo, where he is a coach of two high school improvisation teams, including the team with which he first performed as a teenager.</p>','Andy Sarouhan','','publish','open','open','','andy-sarouhan','','','2015-09-23 13:59:03','2015-09-23 20:59:03','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=actors&#038;p=729',44,'actors','',0),(731,2,'2014-05-27 16:33:30','2014-05-27 23:33:30','','andySarouhan_236x236','','inherit','open','open','','andysarouhan_236x236','','','2014-05-27 16:33:30','2014-05-27 23:33:30','',729,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/andySarouhan_236x236.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(732,2,'2014-05-27 16:35:40','2014-05-27 23:35:40','<h1>Patricia Pearson</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Guest Coach</strong></p>\r\n<p>Improv has been a big part of Patricia\'s life since 1999 when she started taking classes at Sue Walden\'s Improv Works. She came to BATS Improv in 2004 and has been here ever since, learning, teaching, and performing as a Sunday Player, a member of “The Crew,” and a Cave Match performer.</p>\r\n<p>Improv has had a profound effect on her life. Though naturally an introvert, Patricia found that improv opened up her extroverted side. As a child in New York City, Patricia was accepted to the prestigious High School of the Performing Arts but was too shy to attend. That is no longer the case.</p>\r\n<p>Patricia\'s performing side is now completely open and ready to jump on stage at a moment’s notice. She loves to share this revelation with fellow introverts so they can develop their extroverted side without giving up their cherished introversion!</p>\r\n<p>Improv singing became a favorite almost immediately upon starting improv. Patricia has loved it ever since, singing many an improv song on the BATS stage. She teaches improv singing with the wonderful David Norfleet both at BATS and privately. She is certified in teaching Fitzmaurice Voicework®, which focuses on breath and body for authentic and emotionally connected performing. Patricia brings this deeper work to her improv singing classes at BATS Improv.</p>\r\n<p>Patricia continues to study acting with Bobby Weinapple at Seydways Studio, practicing Stretch Work, which adds to her emotionally connected performing and teaching.</p>\r\n<p>Patricia has twice produced, directed, and performed in her original format “Over the Moon and Under the Beds: Faerie Tales from Our Heads,” dark-leaning improvised fairy tales for grown-ups.</p>\r\n<p>She is a part of Fully Improvised, an ensemble dedicated to longform genre work, performing genres that include Improvised Stephen Sondheim and Improvised David Mamet. She has also been a part of the musical group YesSing.</p>\r\n<p>Performing in schools in San Francisco has also been a very rewarding part of her improv experience along with performing with the BATS Main Stage Company in several shows, most recently Improvised Downton Abbey.</p>\r\n<p>Patricia believes that the world would be a far better place if everyone learned improv and the lessons of improv -- listening, taking care of your fellow players, valuing what they have to offer, and bringing the possibility of playfulness to everything you do.</p>','Patricia Pearson','','draft','open','open','','patricia-pearson','','','2014-11-22 19:51:23','2014-11-23 03:51:23','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=actors&#038;p=732',43,'actors','',0),(733,2,'2014-05-27 16:35:34','2014-05-27 23:35:34','','patriciaPearson_236x236','','inherit','open','open','','patriciapearson_236x236','','','2014-05-27 16:35:34','2014-05-27 23:35:34','',732,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/patriciaPearson_236x236.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(734,2,'2014-05-27 16:42:03','2014-05-27 23:42:03','<h1>Lisa Safran</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Coach </strong>since 2013</p>\r\n<p>Lisa Safran began studying theatre at the ACT Young Conservatory. She went on to train at Jean Shelton Studios and then attended the American Academy of Dramatic Arts. Shortly after returning to San Francisco, Lisa began studying improvisation with Jim Cranna. She went on to perform with several improv groups around the Bay Area until she shifted her attention to stand-up comedy for several years, performing at odd little clubs around the U.S. and Canada.</p>\r\n<p>Lisa began teaching elementary school and developed programs for children that used improvisation to support literacy, which really took form while teaching overseas in Thailand. In 2007, Lisa returned to San Francisco and joined the improvisation troupe the Too Many Larrys! and also began studying at BATS Improv.</p>\r\n<p>In 2010 Lisa began presenting her findings on improvisation and literacy at conferences and published, <em>Reading and Writing Come Alive: Using Improvisation to Build Literacy</em>. In 2011, she founded Improv Consultants, a group of creative professionals who provide engaging and enjoyable experiential programs for educators, businesses, and organizations using improvisation.</p>\r\n<p>Lisa is a self-taught musician and in 2010 produced <em>Dreams That Matter,</em> a CD of original music performed by her band the Bitter Mystics. She is currently collaborating with David Norfleet on an album of children’s music.</p>\r\n','Lisa Safran','','publish','open','open','','lisa-safran','','','2014-06-01 12:13:09','2014-06-01 19:13:09','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=actors&#038;p=734',41,'actors','',0),(735,2,'2014-05-27 16:41:45','2014-05-27 23:41:45','','LisaSafran_236x236','','inherit','open','open','','lisasafran_236x236','','','2014-05-27 16:41:45','2014-05-27 23:41:45','',734,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/LisaSafran_236x236.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(736,2,'2014-05-27 16:45:45','2014-05-27 23:45:45','<h1>David Norfleet</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Guest Music Coach </strong></p>\r\n<p>Since 1991, David Norfleet has been improvising music with companies around the U.S. and Canada. During the day, he composes and produces music for film, television, multimedia, installations, and anything else he can think of.</p>\r\n<p>From 1995 to 1998 David was active in New York\'s improv, live theatre, and performance art scene. He transplanted himself to San Francisco to start his own music/sound studio, Seal Rock Music.</p>\r\n<p>David\'s music and audio clients include Pixar, Dreamworks, Comedy Central, National Geographic, Intel, the city of San Francisco, MasterCard, and National Public Radio.</p>\r\n','David Norfleet','','publish','open','open','','david-norfleet','','','2014-06-01 08:43:55','2014-06-01 15:43:55','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=actors&#038;p=736',34,'actors','',0),(737,2,'2014-05-27 16:45:37','2014-05-27 23:45:37','','david-norfleet_236x236','','inherit','open','open','','david-norfleet_236x236','','','2014-05-27 16:45:37','2014-05-27 23:45:37','',736,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/david-norfleet_236x236.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(748,2,'2014-05-28 07:09:21','2014-05-28 14:09:21','','map_batsTheater','','inherit','open','open','','map_batstheater','','','2014-05-28 07:09:21','2014-05-28 14:09:21','',301,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/map_batsTheater.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(749,2,'2014-05-28 07:10:33','2014-05-28 14:10:33','','map_studio210','','inherit','open','open','','map_studio210','','','2014-05-28 07:10:33',