453','','','2014-05-28 16:48:38','2014-05-28 23:48:38','',682,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/OTG_Workshops_IMG_4453.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(783,2,'2014-05-28 17:39:43','2014-05-29 00:39:43','<h1>BATS Improv Main Stage Company Alumni</h1><p>Ed Alter</p><p>Gary Barth</p><p>Kurt Bodden</p><p>Dave Bushnell</p><p>Curt Butz</p><p>James Campbell</p><p>Lex Chesler</p><p>Richard Dupell</p><p>Tim Ereneta</p><p>Jennifer Fairbanks*</p><p>Cully Fredrickson</p><p>Naomi Freier</p><p>Amos Glick</p><p>Carol Hazenfield</p><p>John X. Heart</p><p>Ellen Idelson*</p><p>Stephen Kearin</p><p>Dan Klein</p><p>Rachel Klem</p><p>Kat Koppett</p><p>John Kovacevich</p><p>Drew Letchworth</p><p>Tony Lijphart</p><p>Kirk Livingston</p><p>Brian Lohmann</p><p>Bob Martin</p><p>Dan O\'Connor</p><p>Jay Parks</p><p>Larry Pisoni</p><p>Greg Proops</p><p>Reed Kirk Rahlmann</p><p>Rich Ross</p><p>Pamela Stoneham</p><p>Chris Thompson</p><p>Sylvia Tucker</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>* deceased</p>','BATS Alumni','','publish','open','open','','alumni','','','2014-05-28 17:40:25','2014-05-29 00:40:25','',300,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?page_id=783',22,'page','',0),(785,2,'2014-05-28 18:49:05','2014-05-29 01:49:05','<h1><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-786 size-full\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/chet-headshot_236x236.jpg\" alt=\"chet-headshot_236x236\" width=\"236\" height=\"236\" />Chet Anderson</h1><p>Chet has been Managing Director at BATS Improv since 2010. He had worked at BATS in various roles since 2003, including as On-the-Go Trainer and Program Associate and as Lighting Improviser for hundreds of Company shows. Chet first came to BATS as a student in 2002, and now performs in the Sunday Cave Match series at BATS and with Secret Improv Society.</p><p>Before taking the position of BATS Managing Director, Chet served as Program Director for the Greater Bay Area Make-A-Wish Foundation, Programs and Volunteers Manager for the Tech Museum of Innovation, Anti-Bias Educator for the Anti-Defamation League, Grant Writer for the Santa Clara County Office of Education, and Human Resources Specialist at Sun Microsystems.</p><hr /><h1>Q &amp; A</h1><p><strong>What was your first BATS Show?<br /></strong>2002. Spontaneous Broadway. The chosen song was Love in the Carpool Lane from the musical Commuter Hell. John and Barbara were exes working in the same office.</p><p><strong>What do you like about improv?</strong><br />Aside from the fact that I still remember the plot details of a show 12 years ago, I love the way that it relies on a perfect combination of spontaneity and collaboration.</p><p><strong>What was your first improv class?</strong><br />2002. Intermediate with Kasey Klemm.</p><p><strong>What are your favorite formats?</strong><br />Directors Cut. It encourages such playfulness and bold offers from the actors, along with a wonderful variety of audience interactions.</p><p><strong>Why should people do improv?</strong><br />Have fun. Meet people. Develop skills. Create theatre!</p>','Chet Anderson','','publish','open','open','','chet-anderson','','','2014-05-30 18:08:13','2014-05-31 01:08:13','',14,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?page_id=785',16,'page','',0),(786,2,'2014-05-28 18:48:50','2014-05-29 01:48:50','','chet-headshot_236x236','','inherit','open','open','','chet-headshot_236x236','','','2014-05-28 18:48:50','2014-05-29 01:48:50','',785,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/chet-headshot_236x236.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(788,2,'2014-05-29 06:01:45','2014-05-29 13:01:45','<h1>Chris Sams</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Coach</strong> since 2005</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\';\">Chris Sams served for eight years as Director of BATS Improv\'s <em><span style=\"font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\';\">On-The-Go</span></em> corporate training programs.  He joined the BATS School of Improv coaching staff in January 2005. He enjoys teaching all levels of series classes (from Foundation to Scene Work to Performance) and specialty classes such as Improv for Business, Performance Games, the Harold, and Theatresports. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\';\">Chris delights in using improvisational theater technique as a trainer-facilitator with BATS Improv\'s <em><span style=\"font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\';\">On-The-Go</span></em> program to teach communication, adapting to change, quick thinking, creativity, leadership, presence, storytelling, and team building. Chris has led workplace workshops for more than eighty companies and corporate teams, including UC Berkeley Haas Center for Executive Education, UCSF Cancer Center, McKinsey &amp; Co., Genentech, SAP, Gap, Facebook, Google, Salesforce, Virgin America, Yahoo!, and ZS Associates.  His professional background is in non-profit management.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\';\">Chris has performed improv in a variety of groups and settings, including All-Star shows and BATS’ Sunday Player shows since 2002.  He has guested with Un-Scripted Theatre Company to host more than 50 performances of <em><span style=\"font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\';\">You Bet Your Improvisor</span></em><em><span style=\"font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; font-style: normal;\">  Chris represented </span></em><em><span style=\"font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; font-style: normal;\">BATS Improv at</span></em><em><span style=\"font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\';\"> CATS (California Theatresports) Tournament </span></em>and <em><span style=\"font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\';\">Laughstock </span></em>in Ventura, CA.  He debuted and directed <em><span style=\"font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\';\">The Blank Show</span></em> at BATS Improv, where he hosts the improvised game show on select Sundays.  Recently, he’s appeared on the BATS stage on various Cave Match teams, including <em><span style=\"font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\';\">Fire and Ice, the Flux Capacitors, </span></em>and<em><span style=\"font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\';\"> the Hand Models of #YOLO County.</span></em></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Chris Sams','','publish','open','open','','chris-sams','','','2014-06-11 16:02:34','2014-06-11 23:02:34','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=actors&#038;p=788',42,'actors','',0),(789,2,'2014-05-29 06:01:29','2014-05-29 13:01:29','','chrisSams_236x236','','inherit','open','open','','chrissams_236x236','','','2014-05-29 06:01:29','2014-05-29 13:01:29','',788,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/chrisSams_236x236.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(790,2,'2014-05-29 07:04:44','2014-05-29 14:04:44','','about_ourvision_IMG_4873','','inherit','open','open','','about_ourvision_img_4873','','','2014-05-29 07:04:44','2014-05-29 14:04:44','',296,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/about_ourvision_IMG_4873.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(793,2,'2014-05-29 07:07:13','2014-05-29 14:07:13','','about_ourvision2_IMG_4873','','inherit','open','open','','about_ourvision2_img_4873','','','2014-05-29 07:07:13','2014-05-29 14:07:13','',296,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/about_ourvision2_IMG_4873.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(794,2,'2014-05-29 07:34:54','2014-05-29 14:34:54','','school_quotes_IMG_2975','','inherit','open','open','','school_quotes_img_2975','','','2014-05-29 07:34:54','2014-05-29 14:34:54','',407,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/school_quotes_IMG_2975.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(796,4,'2014-05-29 11:19:02','2014-05-29 18:19:02','<p><strong>Opening weekend of our 20th Annual Summer Improv Festival! </strong></p>\r\n<p>Secrets. Rivalries.  Romance.  - Enter the world of a privileged but troubled estate in the early 20th century in this completely improvised period story told in the style of Downton Abbey. You won\'t see Sybil, Matthew, or Violet, but rather new characters created on the spot by our world-class improvisers — each inspired by your suggestions.</p>','Improvised<br>Downton Abbey','','draft','open','open','','improvised-downton-abbey','','','2015-06-22 13:20:10','2015-06-22 20:20:10','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=special&#038;p=796',22,'special','',0),(798,4,'2014-05-29 11:22:21','2014-05-29 18:22:21','<p><strong>Celebrating the 25th Anniversary of Improvised Shakespeare in San Francisco!</strong></p>\r\n<p>In 1989 BATS Improv performed the very first full-length Improvised Shakespeare in San Francisco (and perhaps the entire West Coast).  Celebrate the 25th anniversary of this landmark performance with two nights of Improvised Shakespeare as part of our 2014 Summer Improv Festival.</p>\r\n<p>Shakespeare didn’t write these stories — but you’ll think he did! Starting with a title chosen by you, the audience, our merry band of improvisers will create a full-length play in the style and language of The Bard.  No two shows are ever the same, but every show is a great night of improvised Shakespearean theatre. What are you waiting for? Get thee to the theater and experience the magic that is BATS Improvised Shakespeare.</p>\r\n<p><a title=\"Review: Improvised Shakespeare\" href=\"http://www.examiner.com/review/bats-improvised-shakespeare-with-romantic-comedy-founder-hall-as-fair-beatrice\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Read the 5-Star Review from Examiner.com</strong></a></p>','Improvised Shakespeare','','draft','open','open','','shakespeare','','','2015-06-22 13:18:55','2015-06-22 20:18:55','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=special&#038;p=798',15,'special','',0),(799,4,'2014-05-29 11:59:31','2014-05-29 18:59:31','<div class=\"header-title-description\"><span id=\"event-title\" class=\"regular bigText highContrastColor\">BATS Improv joins forces with our friends from <a href=\"http://improtheatre.com\" target=\"_blank\">Impro Theatre, LA</a> for a one-night-only improvised musical spectacular!  You (yes,you) will play the role of an elite theatre investor who is about to back Broadway\'s next big hit.  </span></div>\r\n<div class=\"header-title-description\"> </div>\r\n<div class=\"header-title-description\"><span id=\"event-title\" class=\"regular bigText highContrastColor\">In the first half, you\'ll </span><span class=\"light bigText highContrastColor\"> meet our fictionally-famous cast of Broadway superstar who \"audition\" new musicals by improvising a song from titles you supply before the show.  Then, you\'ll vote with your (fictional) pocketbook - by texting your investment to the show you most want to see. The show with the most investors is then turned into a complete musical in the second half, including a reprise of the winning song! <em>And of course, everything is completely improvised!</em></span></div>','Spontaneous Broadway','','draft','closed','open','','spontaneous-broadway','','','2015-08-09 01:17:15','2015-08-09 08:17:15','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=special&#038;p=799',9,'special','',0),(815,7,'2014-05-30 10:30:36','2014-05-30 17:30:36','','June','','draft','open','open','','june','','','2015-06-30 21:19:22','2015-07-01 04:19:22','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=sunday&#038;p=815',4,'sunday','',0),(820,2,'2014-05-30 13:49:44','2014-05-30 20:49:44',' ','','','publish','open','closed','','820','','','2015-11-10 19:55:09','2015-11-11 03:55:09','',6,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?p=820',16,'nav_menu_item','',0),(822,2,'2014-05-30 16:11:29','2014-05-30 23:11:29','','about_ourvision_candid-on-stage','','inherit','open','open','','about_ourvision_candid-on-stage','','','2014-05-30 16:11:29','2014-05-30 23:11:29','',296,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/about_ourvision_candid-on-stage.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(824,2,'2014-05-31 12:16:43','2014-05-31 19:16:43',' ','','','publish','open','open','','824','','','2014-05-31 12:16:43','2014-05-31 19:16:43','',6,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?p=824',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),(827,2,'2014