,(866,4,'2014-05-31 22:03:22','2014-06-01 05:03:22','','warp-speed-web313','','inherit','open','open','','warp-speed-web313-2','','','2014-05-31 22:03:22','2014-06-01 05:03:22','',634,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/warp-speed-web3131.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(870,4,'2014-05-31 23:15:08','2014-06-01 06:15:08','','shakespeare-web313','','inherit','open','open','','shakespeare-web313','','','2014-05-31 23:15:08','2014-06-01 06:15:08','',798,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/shakespeare-web313.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(872,4,'2014-05-31 23:25:36','2014-06-01 06:25:36','','downton-web313','','inherit','open','open','','downton-web313','','','2014-05-31 23:25:36','2014-06-01 06:25:36','',796,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/downton-web313.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(877,4,'2014-06-01 00:32:38','2014-06-01 07:32:38','','battle-la-web313','','inherit','open','open','','battle-la-web313','','','2014-06-01 00:32:38','2014-06-01 07:32:38','',476,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/battle-la-web313.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(879,4,'2014-06-01 01:07:37','2014-06-01 08:07:37','<p>Without a doubt this is one of our most popular events of the year!  There\'s always a special energy in the house for the Grudge Match, so if you only see one Theatresports match this year, see this one!</p>\r\n<p>The Clowns (Paul Killam, Rebecca Stockley, Rebecca Poretsky), winners of this year\'s <a href=\"http://www.improv.org/friday/theatresportstradeking-of-the-hill/\">King of the Hill Theatresports</a> tournament, will represent BATS Improv against our rivals (okay, frenemies) from down south - LA\'s <a href=\"http://improtheatre.com\" target=\"_blank\">Impro Theatre</a> (Brian Lohmann, Floyd Van Buskirk, and Paul Hungerford).</p>\r\n<p>Theatresports is an improv comedy competition where two teams face off - improvising scenes, songs, and games, all based on audience suggestions - to win points from the judges and hearts of the audience. At the end of the night, the team with the most points wins - taking home the coveted SF/LA Improv Cup - and bragging rights for the next year.  </p>','SF vs. LA Theatresports&trade;','','draft','closed','closed','','annual-grudge-match','','','2015-08-09 01:17:09','2015-08-09 08:17:09','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=special&#038;p=879',8,'special','',0),(885,4,'2014-06-01 01:39:51','2014-06-01 08:39:51','<p>Fate, bad choices and audience suggestions will lead to a woman’s conviction in this depression era tale of life behind bars, complete with hardened inmates, sadistic guards and hot house passions.</p>','Women\'s Prison Drama','','draft','open','open','','mens-prision-drama-womens-prison-drama','','','2015-06-22 13:19:24','2015-06-22 20:19:24','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=special&#038;p=885',18,'special','',0),(889,4,'2014-06-01 02:46:15','2014-06-01 09:46:15','<p>Embracing Bertolt Brecht\'s ideas of Epic Theatre, we use your suggestions to create a new piece of musical theatre that defies convention, format, and even linear story-telling, while still staying firmly rooted in human experience. The result is a compelling and fearless theatre that unflinchingly tackles contemporary socio-political issues.</p>\r\n<p>This show includes a Q&amp;A talkback session with the actors immediately following the final bow. We feel this talkback session is an important part of the experience and we encourage everyone to stay.  Time for the talkback session has been factored in to the total run time of the show.</p>\r\n<p>What\'s more, we\'re embracing Brecht\'s ideal by knocking down economic barriers to both shows this weekend. Advance tickets are <strong>Pay What You Like</strong> and are available for <strong>$0, $5, $10, $15</strong>, and the regular price of $17.</p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"color: #d9541e;\"><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Group Tickets\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/groups/\"><strong>Group tickets</strong> start at just $14 each!</a><br /><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Gift Certificates\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/gift-certificates/\">You can also give this show as a gift with a </a><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Gift Certificates\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/gift-certificates/\"><strong>BATS Gift Certific</strong><strong>ate</strong>.</a> </span></em></p>','Theatre on the Edge','','draft','open','open','','on-the-edge','','','2015-08-23 23:33:45','2015-08-24 06:33:45','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=special&#038;p=889',5,'special','',0),(892,4,'2014-06-01 02:53:41','2014-06-01 09:53:41','<p>Genre is king a Pulp Playhouse!  Enjoy eight puply, tawdry, and lurid tales inspired by your suggestions and narrated by characters just as large as the stories they tell. Expect bigger-than-life heroes, prettier-than-pretty girls, and unexpected consequences.  <em>BATS Improv is proud to be bringing Pulp Playhouse back to stage after a 20 hiatus.  Special thanks to format creator Brian Lohmann.</em></p>','Pulp Playhouse','','draft','open','open','','scripted-monologues-lead-to-outrageous-improvised-stories','','','2015-06-22 13:19:33','2015-06-22 20:19:33','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=special&#038;p=892',19,'special','',0),(894,4,'2014-06-01 03:05:33','2014-06-01 10:05:33','<p>At BATS, we love stories. And sometimes the most moving, hilarious, heartfelt, or heartbreaking stories are the true ones. Each of our lives are wonderful and unique and strange and sad and funny. We\'re all walking around with our stories tucked into our back pockets every day, as we go about our daily business.</p>\r\n<p>In San Francisco Secrets, our talented cast of actors will use improvisation to explore secretes anonymously submitted by you and other San Franciscans.  Serious secrets will be treated with respect and more lighthearted secrets will be treated…. well… more lightheartedly.  You can expect drama, comedy, and sincerity.  <br /> <br />Everyone is walking around with stories tucked in back pockets…. share your secrets with us… a dream, an inspiration, a failure, a hope… anything you\'d like.<br /><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1sEnL5ttZko3Vvy3YhmXIMD0AsJ-CdJUWm0R0RM3d9sQ/viewform\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1219 size-full\" src=\"http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/share.jpg\" alt=\"share a secret\" width=\"240\" height=\"80\" /></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><a title=\"Share a Secret\" href=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1sEnL5ttZko3Vvy3YhmXIMD0AsJ-CdJUWm0R0RM3d9sQ/viewform\" target=\"_blank\"><br />Submit your secrets online using this link</a></strong></span> <br /><em>(you\'ll get a $5 off coupon code when you do).</em>  <br /><br /></p>\r\n<p> <iframe src=\"//player.vimeo.com/video/101184022\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1sEnL5ttZko3Vvy3YhmXIMD0AsJ-CdJUWm0R0RM3d9sQ/viewform\" target=\"_blank\">Share your secret anonymously</a>. You may see yours on stage, but you won\'t have to tell anybody it\'s yours. :)</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>BATS Improv thanks to Roy Danger and our friends at the <a href=\"http://www.hideouttheatre.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Hideout Theater</a> in Austin, TX for their generosity in sharing their experience with their own secrets show, Austin Secrets.</em></p>','San Francisco Secrets','','draft','open','open','','secrets','','','2015-06-22 13:19:40','2015-06-22 20:19:40','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=special&#038;p=894',20,'special','',0),(896,4,'2014-06-01 03:09:46','2014-06-01 10:09:46','<p>Sweeping landscapes! Epic desires! Life, death, and everything in between! Watch as our own band of imps, sell swords, royalty, and mystics create an improvised re-imagining of the Game of Thrones world right before your very eyes. Experience the excitement as an amazing array of never-before-seen characters risk everything for family, love, and the power of the Iron Throne. The summer is long… <em><strong>Improv is Coming.</strong></em></p>','Improvised<br>Game of Thrones','','draft','closed','open','','gameofthrones','','','2015-06-22 13:19:48','2015-06-22 20:19:48','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=special&#038;p=896',21,'special','',0),(898,4,'2014-06-01 03:26:18','2014-06-01 10:26:18','<p><strong>Friday, July 31 at 8 PM<br /></strong><strong>Saturday, August 1 at 8 PM<br /></strong><strong>Sunday, August 2 at 2pm (Matinee performance)</strong><strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.vendini.com/ticket-software.html?t=tix&amp;e=7ae7b4412541021dd520dc55da97d400\"><img class=\"alignleft\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/themes/responsive/core/images/buy-tickets-button.png\" alt=\"Buy Now\" width=\"104\" height=\"30\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><b><i>“Legendary is the American trio of 3 FOR ALL, and rightly so.” —Theaterkrant Amsterdam</i></b></p>\r\n<p>3 FOR ALL — the internationally and critically acclaimed improvisers — Rafe Chase, Stephen Kearin and Tim Orr — return to BATS\' Bayfront Theater with 3 more hysterical performances of completely spontaneous improv!<br /> <br />The wildly popular trio is known for their unique blend of intensely dramatic and outrageously funny, completely improvised scenes based on audience suggestions. Their high-stakes improv has thrilled audiences since they hit the stage in 1996 and they continue to play to sold-out houses and rave audience reviews in the San Francisco Bay Area as well as Los Angeles, New York, Chicago, Austin, Atlanta, Finland and Amsterdam.</p>\r\n<p>3 FOR ALL starred in two improvised feature films, Suckerfish and Security, as well as collaborating on their own completely improvised CD. Individually, their improv expertise is highly sought after for animation inspiration and character development (DreamWorks Animation), voice acting (The Sims, and Sims 2.0, Madagascar 2, Kung Fu Panda and Kung Fu Panda 2, Mars Needs Moms, Megamind), TV characters (How I Met Your Mother, Jonas LA) teaching and performing improvisation in the United States (American Conservatory Theater, Stanford University, Cirque Du Soleil) and internationally (Amsterdam, Beirut, Helsinki, Israel, Leuven, London, Paris, Saudi Arabia, Stockholm). Individually and as the amazing ensemble 3 FOR ALL, Chase, Kearin and Orr are widely recognized as 3 of the hottest improvisers on the scene today.</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/uupDwqD_luI?list=PLy-4F-zA-bkYIXCTJgz-219wjBwRwqnu_\" width=\"420\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p><em>This 3 FOR ALL performance is produced by Eastman Productions &amp; Improv Playhouse of San Francisco in association with BATS Improv.</em></p>','3 FOR ALL<br><i>Special Guests</i>','','draft','open','open','','3fa','','','2015-08-03 14:49:16','2015-08-03 21:49:16','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=special&#038;p=898',7,'special','',0),(903,4,'2014-06-01 03:37:13','2014-06-01 10:37:13','<p>After the zombie-apocolypse, survial is everything.  Drawing inspiration from the \"zombie rules\" of The Walking Dead, our ensemble creates a never-before-seen episodic zombie horror survival thriller.  Each week is it\'s own satisfying show, with a larger story arch that builds weeks to week.  Miss last week\'s show?  Don\'t worry, we\'ll catch you up on everything you need to know!  Who will live?  Who will die?  Who has what it takes to survive?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','The Improvised Dead','','draft','open','open','','zombie','','','2015-08-20 21:00:12','2015-08-21 04:00:12','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=saturday&#038;p=903',8,'saturday','',0),(906,4,'2014-06-01 03:47:28','2014-06-01 10:47:28','<p>Celebrate Halloween with our annual, completely improvised, frightfully-delightful, feature-length musical!  Things may start out normal enough, but soon emotions will run high and everything will become a matter of life and death!  As always, everything will be made up on the spot - our talented cast of actors will take inspiration from your suggestions, as well as classic horror films like Alien, Poltergeist, and The Exorcist.  </p>\r\n<p><strong>Come in costume and get a free non-alcoholic beverage from concessions!</strong></p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"color: #d9541e;\"><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Group Tickets\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/groups/\"><strong>Group tickets</strong> start at just $14 each!</a><br /><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Gift Certificates\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/gift-certificates/\">You can also give this show as a gift with a </a><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Gift Certificates\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/gift-certificates/\"><strong>BATS Gift Certific</strong><strong>ate</strong>.</a> </span></em></p>','Halloween Horror Musical','','draft','open','open','','halloween-horror-musical','','','2015-11-01 02:30:02','2015-11-01 10:30:02','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=special&#038;p=906',4,'special','',0),(911,4,'2014-06-01 05:11:55','2014-06-01 12:11:55','<p>Each night of DuoProv, three pairs of improvisers put it all on the line by playing as a team of two - that’s right only two players per team! Witness our dauntless improvisers as they face the challenge of taking BATS stage with only their imaginations to rely on. What characters will be created? What stories will unfold? Join us and find out! As each Duo digs, the unexpected will happen.</p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"color: #d9541e;\"><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Group Tickets\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/groups/\"><strong>Group tickets</strong> start at just $14 each for groups of 10+</a><br /><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Gift Certificates\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/gift-certificates/\">You can also give this show as a gift with a </a><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Gift Certificates\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/gift-certificates/\"><strong>BATS Gift Certific</strong><strong>ate</strong>.</a> <strong><br /></strong></span></em></p>','DuoProv','','draft','open','open','','duoprov','','','2015-08-20 12:41:45','2015-08-20 19:41:45','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=friday&#038;p=911',9,'friday','',0),(914,4,'2014-06-01 05:20:34','2014-06-01 12:20:34','<p>Family Drama uniquely blends the compelling narrative of a three-act stage play with the excitement and surprise of improvisation.  Like many traditional American plays, the story will unfold in real time, on a single set, and with each actor portraying only one character.</p>\r\n<p>This hilarious drama is also completely improvised...the only thing the actors know is that their characters are somehow related and that they are getting together for the holidays.  The audience selects the title for the show, which inspires the themes, relationships, stories, etc.  Everything else is created right in front of your eyes!<i><b><br /></b></i></p>\r\n<p><strong>Parental Advisory:</strong> Due to possible adult themes and language, this show may not be suitable for children. </p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"color: #d9541e;\"><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Group Tickets\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/groups/\"><strong>Group tickets</strong> start at just $14 each!</a><br /><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Gift Certificates\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/gift-certificates/\">You can also give this show as a gift with a </a><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Gift Certificates\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/gift-certificates/\"><strong>BATS Gift Certific</strong><strong>ate</strong>.</a> <strong><br /></strong></span></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Family Drama','','publish','open','open','','familydrama','','','2015-11-16 17:09:43','2015-11-17 01:09:43