tudents maximum<br /> <strong>Tuition:</strong> $329</p>','F1 - Foundation 1 with Andy Sarouhan 6/26/14 PA','','publish','open','open','','f1-foundation-1-with-andy-sarouhan-62614-pa-2','','','2014-06-02 12:27:12','2014-06-02 19:27:12','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/?post_type=class&#038;p=933',0,'class','',0),(940,4,'2014-06-01 15:56:19','2014-06-01 22:56:19','','song-homework','','inherit','open','open','','song-homework','','','2014-06-01 15:56:19','2014-06-01 22:56:19','',696,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/song-homework.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(941,4,'2014-06-01 16:09:12','2014-06-01 23:09:12','','joshua-bio-236','','inherit','open','open','','joshua-bio-236','','','2014-06-01 16:09:12','2014-06-01 23:09:12','',696,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/joshua-bio-236.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(943,4,'2014-06-01 18:21:05','2014-06-02 01:21:05','','theater-dark-July4-web313','','inherit','open','open','','theater-dark-july4-web313','','','2014-06-01 18:21:05','2014-06-02 01:21:05','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/theater-dark-July4-web313.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(944,4,'2014-06-01 18:32:14','2014-06-02 01:32:14','','theater-dark-July4-web313','','inherit','open','open','','theater-dark-july4-web313-2','','','2014-06-01 18:32:14','2014-06-02 01:32:14','',0,'http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/theater-dark-July4-web3131.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(947,4,'2014-06-01 23:10:07','2014-06-02 06:10:07','<h1>Music Bootcamp<br /> 3 Half-Days; Aug. 29-31<br /> Fri, Sat, Sun, 10:00 AM - 1:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">SOLD-OUT; CLICK ON \"SIGN UP\" BUTTON TO ADD TO WAIT LIST </span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Fri-Sun, August 29, 30, 31 2014<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Tuition: $229</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Schedule: </strong>10am - 1pm<strong><br /></strong>Friday, Saturday, and Sunday August 29, 30, and 31<br /><strong>Class size: </strong>12 students maximum<br /><strong>Class length:</strong> 3 hours  daily (9 hours total)<br /><strong>Prerequisite:</strong> <span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 13px;\">Foundation 3 and above with some prior improv song experience. </span>If you have any questions about your registration eligibility, please contact Regina Saisi at regina@improv.org <br /> </p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"color: #222222; font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 13px;\">Get ready to sing your heart out!  This three-session workshop is designed for improvisors who are comfortable with improvised singing and want to develop their song-making skills to reach even greater heights of musical improvisation.  Lisa Rowland and Joshua Raoul Brody will team up to run you through exercises to practice solos, duets and group songs, as well as a capella singing.  Specific topics will include directing endings, finding choruses, practicing different formats of big group numbers, and what it takes to create a full sound with others whether a capella or accompanied. You\'ll leave the class with an expanded set of tools for making fantastic songs every time.</span></p>\r\n<div style=\"font-family: TimesNewRomanPSMT;\"> </div>','Summer 2014 - Music Bootcamp with Lisa Rowland and Joshua Raoul Brody','','publish','open','open','','fs-music-bootcamp-with-lisa-rowland-and-joshua-raoul-brody','','','2014-08-13 16:47:03','2014-08-13 23:47:03','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=947',0,'class','',0),(949,4,'2014-06-01 23:32:28','2014-06-02 06:32:28','<h1>Advanced Improvised Brecht</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Sundays, 2:30 - 5:30pm<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule:</strong> Sundays September 13, 20, 27, and October 4th from 2:30-5:30pm <br /><strong>Performances:</strong> Two performances - Sunday, October 4th, 6pm and 7:15pm<br /><strong>Class size: </strong>12 students maximum<br /><strong>Class length:</strong> 12 hours of instruction total<br /><strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Studio level with significant performance experience. <br />**Please email Dean Regina Saisi at <a href=\"mailto:regina@improv.org\">regina@improv.org</a> to confirm eligibility BEFORE registering.**<br /><strong>Tuition:</strong> $239</p>\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-GB\">Bertolt Brecht was a hugely influential and unique 20th century German poet, playwright, theatre director, and Marxist.</span></p>\r\n<p>His ideas of the “Epic Theatre” provide a true treasure chest of theatrical  improvisation. Brecht\'s theory behind Epic Theatre aims at tackling social and political issues to be negotiated between stage and audience. What may sound brainy and exhausting is in fact quite entertaining, interactive, and up-to-date. “Heavy entertainment”!</p>\r\n<p>This workshop introduces theory of Epic Theatre, its dramatic structures, as well as the use of “Alienation-Effects”.</p>\r\n<p> Some of the themes, tools, and structures of the genre you\'ll play with in this workshop include:</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-GB\">-          using a </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\">narrator</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-GB\">-          using a </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\">chorus</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-GB\">-          playing with </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\">slow motion and speed up motion</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-GB\">-          </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\">slapstick</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-GB\">-          </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\">actor leaving the character</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-GB\">-          </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\">monologues</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-GB\">-          </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\">signs/placards</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-GB\">-          </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\">light</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-GB\">-          </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\">echoing</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-GB\">-          </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\">exploring the basic conflict (good/evil) as a platform</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-GB\">-          using </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\">characters as representatives of societal structures and groups</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-GB\">-          </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\">finding the other side (opposite) in characters</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang=\"EN-GB\">-          discovering different kinds of </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\">endings which includ open questions, unclear, ambiguous…, final character tableau</span></p>\r\n<p>Our wonderful guest coach is an improviser and coach joining us from Berlin, the epicenter of Brecht\'s artistic work.</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><em><span lang=\"EN-GB\">Theatre should not be judged on whether it satisfies the habits of its audience but rather on whether it is able to change them!</span></em></p>\r\n<p align=\"right\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\"><em>- Bertolt Brecht</em></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Advanced Improvised Brecht (15-09-2182)','','publish','open','open','','summer-2014-improvising-brechts-epic-theatre','','','2015-08-11 15:30:04','2015-08-11 22:30:04','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=949',0,'class','',0),(950,4,'2014-06-01 23:46:55','2014-06-02 06:46:55','<h1>Stage Combat and Intimacy<br /> 1-Day; Aug. 24<br /> Sun, 10:00 AM - 6:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Sunday, August 24, 2014<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Tuition: $149</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule:</strong> 10am-6pm, Sunday, August 24th (with a 1-hour lunch break)<br /> <strong>Class size:</strong> 12 students maximum<br /> <strong>Class length:</strong> 8 hours of class, 7 hours of instruction total</p>\r\n<p>Prerequisite: Proficient in improv basics and prior performance experience necessary. If you have any questions about your registration eligibility, please contact Regina Saisi at <a title=\"FS – Improv Singing: Rhythm and Style with David Norfleet and Patricia Pearson\" href=\"mailto:regina@improv.org\">regina@improv.org</a></p>\r\n<p>Tired of ham-handed sex scenes and fight scenes that go nowhere? Practice using sexual tension and stage combat techniques to enhance theatrical moments that might otherwise miss the mark. Dress comfortably. No heels. No knives. No bad breath.</p>','Summer 2014 - Stage Combat and Intimacy with Diane Rachel','','publish','open','open','','summer-2014-stage-combat-and-intimacy-with-diane-rachel','','','2014-06-04 10:38:36','2014-06-04 17:38:36','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=950',0,'class','',0),(951,4,'2014-06-01 23:55:48','2014-06-02 06:55:48','<h1>Special Effects<br /> 1-Day; Aug. 23<br /> Sat, 10:00 AM - 6:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>SOLD-OUT; CLICK ON \"SIGN UP\" BUTTON TO ADD TO WAIT LIST </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Saturday, August 23, 2014<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule:</strong> 10am-6pm, Saturday, August 23rd (with a 1-hour lunch break)<br /> <strong>Class size:</strong> 12 students maximum<br /> <strong>Class length:</strong> 8 hours of class, 7 hours of instruction total<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Foundation 3 and above.  If you have any questions about your registration eligibility, please contact Regina Saisi at <a title=\"FS – Improv Singing: Rhythm and Style with David Norfleet and Patricia Pearson\" href=\"mailto:regina@improv.org\">regina@improv.org</a></p>\r\n<p>In this intensive, we will focus on using non-verbal offers to create scenes that have the special effects which often appear in movies. We\'ll practice using our body, voice, and imagination to create ghosts, gods, beasts, violence, cartoon-ish malleability, religious experiences, flight, telepathy, telekinesis, teleportation, phasers-on-stun, and anything else your brain can cook up.  Sign up, and add this interesting dimension to your improv play!</p>','Summer 2014 - Special Effects with Ben Johnson','','publish','open','open','','summer-2014-special-effects-with-ben-johnson','','','2014-07-02 14:59:23','2014-07-02 21:59:23','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=951',0,'class','',0),(952,4,'2014-06-02 00:06:20','2014-06-02 07:06:20','<h1>Playing The Lead<br /> 1-Day; Aug. 22<br /> Friday, 10:00 AM - 6:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>SOLD-OUT; CLICK ON \"SIGN UP\" BUTTON TO ADD TO WAIT LIST </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Friday, August 22, 2014<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Tuition: $149<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p>In improvised long-form stories, we often find ourselves in the \"Lead\" role. Just like that, we are the \"Star\" of the story! How can we do this, convincingly, bravely, honestly, and with passion? How can we fill the roles that famous movie stars across the decades have played? In this intensive, we\'ll explore what playing the lead means to YOU, and discover ways that you can rise to this great challenge and opportunity!</p>','Summer 2014 - Playing The Lead with Tim Orr','','publish','open','open','','summer-2014-playing-the-lead-with-tim-orr','','','2014-07-02 14:57:33','2014-07-02 21:57:33','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=952',0,'class','',0),(953,4,'2014-06-02 00:25:30','2014-06-02 07:25:30','<h1>Exploring Emotion<br /> 1-Day; Aug. 21<br /> Thursday, 10:00 AM - 6:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>SOLD-OUT; CLICK ON \"SIGN UP\" BUTTON TO ADD TO WAIT LIST </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Thursday, August 21, 2014<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Tuition: $149</strong></p>\r\n<p>A story progresses through the emotional changes the characters experience.  Learn the freedom, excitement and narrative thrust of going where the story leads you, with no emotion off limits.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Summer 2014 - Exploring Emotion with Rafe Chase','','publish','open','open','','summer-2014-exploring-emotion-with-rafe-chase','','','2014-07-08 14:14:32','2014-07-08 21:14:32','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=953',0,'class','',0),(954,4,'2014-06-02 00:27:05','2014-06-02 07:27:05','<h1>Foundation 1 Intensive<br /> 3-Days; Aug. 15-17<br />Friday, 10:00 AM - 5:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>SOLD OUT; CLICK ON \"SIGN UP\" TO ADD TO WAIT LIST</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Fri-Sun, August 15-17, 2014</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Tuition: $325<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule:</strong> 3 day-long sessions<br /> <strong>Class Times:</strong> 10am-5pm, with a 1-hour lunch break<br /> <strong>Class size:</strong> 16 students maximum<br /> <strong>Class length:</strong> 6 hours of instruction per day (18 hours total)<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> None</p>\r\n<p>Foundation 1 is our fun introduction to the joys and thrills of improvisation and the BATS-style of improvised theatre. This intensive covers all of the content of the 6-week Foundation 1 class over three days.</p>\r\n<p>Students learn improv concepts and vocabulary, practice new skills, and perform in a safe, friendly atmosphere. Through games and exercises, you\'ll play, explore, and experiment with creating characters and scenes, guided by our seasoned coaches. Foundation 1 is all about unleashing your innate skill. Are you human? Then you have all the experience necessary to excel!</p>','Summer 2014 - Foundation 1 Intensive with Chris Sams and Jenny Rosen','','publish','open','open','','summer-2014-foundation-1-intensive-with-chris-sams-and-jenny-rosen','','','2014-08-01 13:39:32','2014-08-01 20:39:32','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=954',0,'class','',0),(957,4,'2014-06-02 00:47:26','2014-06-02 07:47:26','<h1>Elements of Long Form<br /> 3-Days; Aug. 15-17<br /> Fri, Sat, Sun, 10:00 AM - 5:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Fri-Sun, August 15-17, 2014<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Tuition: $359<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule:</strong> 3 day-long sessions<br /> <strong>Class Times:</strong> 10am-5pm, with a 1-hour lunch break<br /> <strong>Class size:</strong> 14 students maximum<br /> <strong>Class length:</strong> 18 total hours of instruction; three six-hour days.<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Prior improv performance necessary. If you have any questions about your registration eligibity, please contact Dean Regina Saisi at <a href=\"mailto:regina@improv.org\">regina@improv.org</a></p>\r\n<p>In this 3-day intensive course you\'ll develop an appreciation for long-form improvisation in its many forms and some of the basic skills that go into doing it! Dave Dennison and John Remak will guide you through exercises and games that look at and work on:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Taking your time and paying attention</li>\r\n<li>Narrative, especially establishing a strong foundation</li>\r\n<li>Acting</li>\r\n<li>Ensemble</li>\r\n<li>Improvising in genres</li>\r\n<li>Transitions between scenes</li>\r\n<li>Locations/activities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>This class is for students who have prior improv experience in scene work but have little or no long-form experience. A perfect way to get some serious long-form chops and familiarity.</p>','Summer 2014 - Elements of Long Form with Dave Dennison and John Remak','','publish','open','open','','summer-2014-elements-of-long-form-with-dave-dennison-and-john-remak','','','2014-06-02 12:48:55','2014-06-02 19:48:55','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=957',0,'class','',0),(958,4,'2014-06-02 01:16:44','2014-06-02 08:16:44','<h1>The Truth<br /> 3 Half-Days; Aug. 8-10<br /> Fri, Sat, Sun, 10:00 AM - 1:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>SOLD OUT; CLICK ON \"SIGN UP\" BUTTON TO ADD TO WAIT LIST</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Fri-Sun, August 8-10, 2014<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Tuition: $189<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule:</strong> 10am-1pm, Friday, Saturday, and Sunday, August 8-10<br /> <strong>Class size:</strong> 12 students maximum<br /> <strong>Class length:</strong> 3 hours  daily, 9 hours of instruction total<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Foundation 3 and above. <em>If you have any questions about your registration eligibility, please contact Regina Saisi at <a href=\"mailto:regina@improv.org\">regina@improv.org</a>.</em></p>\r\n<p>Get real, go deep, and find your truth on stage in this exciting course that will transform your improvisational acting. This class is designed for the improviser that is ready to jump into the deep end! Theatrical acting techniques will be explored along with intense improvisational scene work. Find a solid base that will translate into any genre or format.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Summer 2014 - The Truth with Zoe Galvez','','publish','open','open','','summer-2014-the-truth-with-zoe-galvez','','','2014-07-14 10:51:57','2014-07-14 17:51:57','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=958',0,'class','',0),(959,4,'2014-06-02 01:28:30','2014-06-02 08:28:30','<h1>Improv for Everybody: the Ethics of Playing Together<br /> 4 Half-Days; Aug. 7-10<br /> Fri, Sat, Sun, 2:00 PM - 5:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong></strong><strong>SOLD-OUT; CLICK ON \"SIGN UP\" BUTTON TO ADD TO WAIT LIST </strong><br /><br />Thurs-Sun, August 7-10, 2014<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</p>\r\n<p><strong>Tuition: $309<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule:</strong> 2pm - 5pm daily<br /> <strong>Class size:</strong> 24 students maximum<br /> <strong>Class length:</strong> 3 hours daily (12 hours total instruction)<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> None</p>\r\n<p>In line with her popular book, IMPROV WISDOM, Patricia takes a fresh look at the key elements that make improv possible: an agreeable nature, an ability to suspend investment in any particular outcome, a willingness to shift focus from self to others, and the cultivation of awareness of all that we are being given.</p>\r\n<p>From her perspective, the study of improvisation is an ethical system.  Improv games can teach us all how to be kinder, more attentive and more willing to take a chance.  She will be improvising her way with the group using exercises and games that are time honored as well as some invented on the spot to solve a problem.</p>\r\n<p>Come join the founder of the Stanford Improvisers and Esalen faculty in four days (12 hours) of fun and reflection.  Play games that teach life lessons we all need to learn.  Practice how to raise someone else\'s status.</p>\r\n<p>Patricia\'s approach involves teaching the fundamentals of improv with an eye toward how these principles rise above the improv stage.  While some of the games and exercises she will lead involve \"performance\" the emphasis in this workshop will not be on improving your stage skills.  But, if you are eager to become a better listener, a more generous partner and a more appreciative player, this may be the class for you.</p>\r\n<p>Your class tuition includes a copy of IMPROV WISDOM.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Summer 2014 - Improv for Everybody: the Ethics of Playing Together with Patricia Ryan Madson','','publish','open','open','','summer-2014-improv-for-everybody-the-ethics-of-playing-together-with-patricia-ryan-madson','','','2014-07-01 13:32:52','2014-07-01 20:32:52','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=959',0,'class','',0),(961,4,'2014-06-02 01:28:50','2014-06-02 08:28:50','<h1>Effortless Story<br /> 4 Days; Jul 31 - Aug. 3<br /> Thurs, 6:00 - 9:00 PM<br />Fri, Sat, 10:00 AM - 5:00 PM<br />Sun, 12:00 - 5:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Bayfront Theater, San Francisco<br /> Tuition: $379</strong></p>\r\n<p>Creating story can be completely effortless. This course offers a deep dive into YOUR stories. Unleash your imagination with a series of activities both solo and with partners. Demystify the narrative process for short and long stories. Explore co-creating stories with this liberating, challenging, and rewarding experience. This work will enhance your story telling voice, as well as increase your confidence with narrative. Building your awareness of story through this approach will enrich the practice of the experienced improviser and inspire the beginner.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Summer 2014 - Effortless Story with William Hall and Rebecca Stockley','','publish','open','open','','summer-2014-effortless-story-with-william-hall-and-rebecca-stockley','','','2014-08-01 13:42:17','2014-08-01 20:42:17','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=961',0,'class','',0),(962,4,'2014-06-02 01:46:28','2014-06-02 08:46:28','<h1>Patricia Ryan Madson</h1>\r\n<p>Patricia Ryan Madson is the author of  IMPROV WISDOM: DON’T PREPARE, JUST SHOW UP. (Bell Tower, 2005) and a professor Emerita from Stanford University where she taught since 1977. In their Drama Department she served as the head of the undergraduate acting program and developed the improvisation program. In 1998 she was the winner of the Lloyd W. Dinkelspiel Award for Outstanding Innovation in Undergraduate Education at Stanford.</p>\r\n<p>She founded and coached the Stanford Improvisors and taught beginning and advanced level courses in Improvisation for undergraduate as well as adults in Stanford\'s Continuing Studies Program. In 1996 she founded the Creativity Initiative at Stanford, an interdisciplinary alliance of faculty who share the belief that creativity can be taught. Patricia has taught Design Improv for the School of Engineering, and is a guest lecturer for the Stanford Technology Ventures Program and for the Mayfield Fellows Program.</p>\r\n<p>She teaches regularly for the Esalen Institute, and has given workshops for the California Institute for Integral Studies, the Institute of Transpersonal Psychology, the National Association of Drama Therapists, the Western Psychological Association, Duke University East Asian Studies Center, Wellness in the Workplace for BC University and the Meaningful Life Therapy Association in Japan.</p>\r\n<p>Her corporate clients have included:  IDEO, Google, Gap Inc.\'s Executive Leadership Team, The Lucille and David Packard Foundation, the Banff Centre for Leadership, the National Collegiate Inventors &amp; Innovators Alliance (NCIIA), Hewlett Packard, Digital Impact, The Woods Institute for the Environment, the International Society for Performance Improvement (ISPI), the Santa Fe Leadership Center, the Association for YMCA Professionals (AYP), Sun Microsystems Japan Division, Extempo Systems, Apple Computers, Adobe Systems, the Piedmont School District, and Price Waterhouse.</p>\r\n<p>Patricia received a Bachelor of Arts in Philosophy from Westhampton College of the U. of Richmond, and a Massters of Arts in Theater from Wayne State University.</p>','Patricia Ryan Madson','','draft','open','open','','patricia-ryan-madson','','','2014-11-22 19:50:52','2014-11-23 03:50:52','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=actors&#038;p=962',40,'actors','',0),(963,4,'2014-06-02 01:50:24','2014-06-02 08:50:24','','patricia-madsen-236','','inherit','open','open','','patricia-madsen-236','','','2014-06-02 01:50:24','2014-06-02 08:50:24','',962,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/patricia-madsen-236.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(964,4,'2014-06-02 02:52:20','2014-06-02 09:52:20','<h1>Teen Improv Ensemble <br />(session 2)<br /> 5 Days; Jul 28 - Aug. 1<br /> Mon–Fri,  9:00 AM – 4:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>SOLD-OUT; CLICK ON \"SIGN UP\" BUTTON TO ADD TO WAIT LIST <br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Ages 14-17<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Mon-Fri, July 28 - Aug. 1<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco<br /> Tuition: $319</strong></p>\r\n<p>Come learn the art of improvisation with other creative teenagers.  Call the Bayfront Theater your home for a week as you practice your acting, storytelling and comedy skills by playing improv games on stage. Make it up, think on your feet, come up with wild stories and characters and learn to play well with others in creating improvised theater! Invite your family and friends to watch you perform on the last day. Discount available for enrolling in both sessions.</p>','Youth Summer 2014 - Teen Summer School: Improv Ensemble Session 2 with BATS Coaches','','publish','open','open','','youth-summer-2014-teen-summer-school-improv-ensemble-session-2-with-bats-coaches','','','2014-07-02 15:10:52','2014-07-02 22:10:52','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=964',0,'class','',0),(965,4,'2014-06-02 02:53:54','2014-06-02 09:53:54','<h1>Teen Improv Ensemble <br />(session 1)<br /> 5 Days; Jul. 21 - Jul. 25<br /> Mon – Fri,  9:00 AM – 4:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>SOLD-OUT; CLICK ON \"SIGN UP\" BUTTON TO ADD TO WAIT LIST <br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Ages 14-17<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Mon-Fri, July 21 - July 25<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco<br /> Tuition: $319</strong></p>\r\n<p>Come learn the art of improvisation with other creative teenagers.  Call the Bayfront Theater your home for a week as you practice your acting, storytelling and comedy skills by playing improv games on stage. Make it up, think on your feet, come up with wild stories and characters and learn to play well with others in creating improvised theater! Invite your family and friends to watch you perform on the last day. Discount available for enrolling in both sessions.</p>','Youth Summer 2014 - Teen Summer School: Improv Ensemble Session 1 with BATS Coaches','','publish','open','open','','youth-summer-2014-teen-summer-school-improv-ensemble-session-1-with-bats-coaches','','','2014-07-02 15:08:34','2014-07-02 22:08:34','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=965',0,'class','',0),(966,4,'2014-06-02 03:06:30','2014-06-02 10:06:30','<h1>Youth All-Stars (session 2)<br /> 5 Days; Jul. 14 - Jul. 18<br /> Mon – Fri,  9:00 AM – 2:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Ages 11-13<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Mon-Fri, July 14 - July 18<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><em><strong>Performance on Friday, July 18 at 12:00 PM</stron