13:32:30','2014-08-01 20:32:30','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1207',0,'class','',0),(1209,5,'2014-07-31 16:33:25','2014-07-31 23:33:25','<p><strong>Guest Coach</strong></p>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222;\">Mona Thompson is from Washington, DC and has been in the Bay Area since 2009. She began improvising in high school then spent 4 years in college studying, performing, and teaching improvisation with the Stanford Improvisors (SImps, for short). Mona took her first BATS classes in the summer of 2012 when she was living in San Francisco and studying the relationship between theatrical improvisors and the city for an Urban Studies research project.</div>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222;\"> </div>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222;\">Currently, Mona lives in San Francisco, coaches the improv team at San Mateo High School, teaches workshops all over the Bay Area, and performs with various San Francisco groups. She has been a Program Assistant at BATS Improv since 2013.</div>','Mona Thompson','','publish','open','open','','mona-thompson','','','2014-12-02 16:31:08','2014-12-03 00:31:08','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=actors&#038;p=1209',8,'actors','',0),(1211,4,'2014-07-31 17:44:51','2014-08-01 00:44:51','','abbey-newsletter','','inherit','open','open','','abbey-newsletter-2','','','2014-07-31 17:44:51','2014-08-01 00:44:51','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/abbey-newsletter1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1212,4,'2014-07-31 17:58:03','2014-08-01 00:58:03','','kgo-hot','','inherit','open','open','','kgo-hot','','','2014-07-31 17:58:03','2014-08-01 00:58:03','',108,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/kgo-hot.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1213,5,'2014-08-01 12:53:55','2014-08-01 19:53:55','<h1>Performing Improvised Movies</h1>\r\n<h1>Tuesdays, 7:00 - 10:00 pm</h1>\r\n<p><strong>August 12 - September 16, 2014<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Schedule:</strong> 6 sessions (once a week for 6 weeks), 2 performances<br /><strong>Class Time/Dates: </strong>7-10pm on Tuesdays August 12, 19, 26, September 2, 19, and 16<br /><strong>Performances:</strong> Two performances: Sunday, September 7 and Sunday, September 21<br /><strong>Class size:</strong> 12 students maximum <strong><br />Class length: </strong>3 hours (18 hours total of instruction)<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong>Studio Scene Work and above with prior long form performance workshop or experience<em><br /> </em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #222222; font-size: 13px;\">In this class you\'ll practice using an audience-generated title as inspiration for the creation of an improvised movie. Dive into your big, beautiful imagination and play any character, travel to any location, and transition artfully from scene to scene!</span></p>\r\n<p>The course will be focused on preparing for two performances (<span style=\"border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dashed; border-bottom-color: #cccccc; position: relative; top: -2px; z-index: 0; color: #222222; font-size: 13px;\" data-term=\"goog_862655619\">September 7 and 21</span><span style=\"color: #222222; font-size: 13px;\">). For each performance the twelve students will divide into two casts, and each cast will perform a 45 minute story for an invited audience. </span></p>','Performance - Performing Improvised Movies with Ben Johnson (#08-1989)','','publish','open','open','','performance-performing-improvised-movies-with-ben-johnson-08-1989','','','2014-08-08 11:35:24','2014-08-08 18:35:24','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1213',0,'class','',0),(1214,5,'2014-08-01 14:56:46','2014-08-01 21:56:46','<h1>Performance Workshop 1</h1>\r\n<h1>Thursdays, 7:00 - 10:00 pm</h1>\r\n<p><strong>September 4 - October 23, 2014<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Schedule:</strong> 8 sessions (once a week for 8 weeks), 2 performances<br /><strong>Class Time/Dates: </strong>7-10pm on Thursdays September 4, 11, 18, 25, October 2, 9, 16, and 23<br /><strong>Performances:</strong> Two performances: Thursday, September 25th and Thursday, October 23rd<br /><strong>Class size:</strong> 10 students maximum <strong><br />Class length: </strong>3 hours (24 hours total of instruction)<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong>Studio Scene Work<em><br /> </em></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">This 8-week workshop prepares you for your first performance in front of an audience by breaking down and covering these different core elements of performance:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Stage skills</li>\r\n<li>Shape of show</li>\r\n<li>Games (setting up, introducing, and playing)</li>\r\n<li>Scenes (setting up, starting, and ending)</li>\r\n<li>Audience interaction</li>\r\n<li>Ensemble-building</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You’ll learn new games and explore the balance between games and scenes for a well-crafted show.  The Workshop includes two performances: one is an open workshop for friends and guests and the second is a full show with a paid audience.</p>','Performance - Performance Workshop 1 with Dave Dennison (#09-1969)','','publish','open','open','','performance-performance-workshop-1-with-dave-dennison-09-1969','','','2014-08-01 15:01:50','2014-08-01 22:01:50','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1214',0,'class','',0),(1215,5,'2014-08-01 13:30:14','2014-08-01 20:30:14','','MonaHeadShot','','inherit','open','open','','monaheadshot','','','2014-08-01 13:30:14','2014-08-01 20:30:14','',1209,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/MonaHeadShot.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1219,4,'2014-08-05 00:19:30','2014-08-05 07:19:30','','share a secret','','inherit','open','open','','share','','','2014-08-05 00:19:30','2014-08-05 07:19:30','',894,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/share.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1221,5,'2014-08-06 12:26:41','2014-08-06 19:26:41','<h1>Thursdays,