,'<h1>Floyd VanBuskirk</h1>\r\n<p>Special Guest from <a href=\"http://improtheatre.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Impro Theatre, LA</a>.</p>','Floyd VanBuskirk, LA','','publish','open','open','','floyd-vanbuskirk','','','2015-07-23 13:16:54','2015-07-23 20:16:54','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=actors&#038;p=1235',38,'actors','',0),(1236,4,'2014-08-07 03:28:15','2014-08-07 10:28:15','','floyd-vanbuskirk','','inherit','open','open','','floyd-vanbuskirk','','','2014-08-07 03:28:15','2014-08-07 10:28:15','',1235,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/floyd-vanbuskirk.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1237,4,'2014-08-07 03:32:22','2014-08-07 10:32:22','<h1>Brian Lohmann</h1>\r\n<p>Special Guest from <a href=\"http://improtheatre.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Impro Theatre, LA</a>.</p>','Brian Lohmann, LA','','publish','open','open','','brian-lohmann','','','2015-07-23 13:14:37','2015-07-23 20:14:37','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=actors&#038;p=1237',37,'actors','',0),(1238,4,'2014-08-07 03:32:03','2014-08-07 10:32:03','','brian','','inherit','open','open','','brian','','','2014-08-07 03:32:03','2014-08-07 10:32:03','',1237,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/brian.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1239,4,'2014-08-07 03:56:29','2014-08-07 10:56:29','','SF Chronicle - Warp Speed Featured in 96 Hours','','publish','open','open','','sf-chronicle-warp-speed-featured-in-96-hours','','','2014-08-07 04:05:27','2014-08-07 11:05:27','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=news&#038;p=1239',0,'news','',0),(1242,4,'2014-08-07 04:27:15','2014-08-07 11:27:15','<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Shakespearean Newsletter</h1>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">The seventh day of August, 2014</h1>\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/queen1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1245\" src=\"http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/queen1-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"140\" height=\"140\" /></a><strong>Hark!</strong> The twentieth festival of live theatre which has not been written but shall instead be improvised before thy very eye continues amist much shock from Her Majesty, The Queen!</h2>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://www.improv.org/special/shakespeare/\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-1246\" src=\"http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/shakes-sepia-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"122\" height=\"120\" /></a>All citizens</strong> are herby requested to get thee to the theater <a title=\"Improvised Shakespeare\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/special/shakespeare/\">anon and the next day</a> for a play.  A play to be improvised in the style of in the style of His Bardship, William Shakespeare and to be called <a title=\"Improvised Shakespeare\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/special/shakespeare/\">Improvised Shakespeare</a>.  These two nights shall be in celebration of the first fully lengthed improvised play in the style of The Bard, some twenty-five years ago this very month.  <a title=\"Improvised Shakespeare\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/special/shakespeare/\">See thy merry band of actors for each eve</a> or <a href=\"https://www.vendini.com/ticket-software.html?t=tix&amp;e=69effe370e879db4b2af6fdc76e86b90\" target=\"_blank\">Cast your duckets now and purchase fine tickets here</a>.</p>\r\n<p><em> <strong>A query:</strong> Didst thou <a href=\"http://abc7news.com/entertainment/explore-where-you-live/110145/\" target=\"_blank\">watch us on screen</a> one week erstwhile? KGO-TV did speak of this very festival of improvisation as such that did truly have their esteem. Wisheth you to watch but yet waste not your time?  Skip then 0:51 in <a href=\"http://abc7news.com/entertainment/explore-where-you-live/110145/\" target=\"_blank\">yonder video</a>.</em></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.vendini.com/ticket-software.html?t=tix&amp;w=6e29496fad9f56feeb06317157a57973\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1250\" style=\"padding-right: 5px;\" src=\"http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/rogan-la1-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"145\" height=\"150\" /></a><strong>A  great friendship, a great battle!  </strong>One week hence, we welcome our kin from the south, the merry players of Impro Theater of the kingdom of Los Angeles – both friend and foe they be. For LA doeth return for two days of revelry.  First <a title=\"Spontaneous Broadway\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/special/spontaneous-broadway/\">a performance as friends in Broadway Spontaneous</a> – a spectacle in song and theatre. The day after there \'tis a challenge! <a title=\"SF vs. LA Theatresports™\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/special/annual-grudge-match/\">A match of theatre as sport</a> to settle many grudges between the great cities of San Francisco and Los Angeles.  Every year A crowd does gather to see this two night a spectacle, so take care to <a href=\"https://www.vendini.com/ticket-software.html?t=tix&amp;w=6e29496fad9f56feeb06317157a57973\" target=\"_blank\">reservest thou ticket</a> have your attendance guaranteed.!</p>\r\n<p>A challenge of photography upon social media has been issued!  <a title=\"Summer Photo Contest\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/summer-photo-contest/\">Read these details in modern English</a> to dispel all questions and discover how thou might win a free BATS shows for a moth!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The tutors of BATS do encourage you to unleash the skills and imagination thou hast kept bottled up inside and join us in merriment! <a title=\"Foundation 1\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-1/\">Declare your intention</a> to study theater of the improvised today!  Feel you unsure?  Try then our one-time <a title=\"3-hour Intro Workshops\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/3-hour-intro-workshops/\">3-hour introduction</a> to improvisation.</p>\r\n<p>Want you improvisation in thy school?  We have met in discussions with heads of institutions of education to form plans of trainings for instructors and lessons in the virtues of leadership with their pupils. And we continue to entertain many as well with our performances at all-school assemblies! Write a letter to Ceci at <a href=\"mailto:otg@improv.org\">otg@improv.org</a> to hatch a plan!</p>\r\n<p>This be the news from the land of BATS. A good day to you and yours.</p>\r\n<p>Theater Crier,<br />Kasey</p>','Shakespearean Newsletter','','publish','open','open','','shakespearean-newsletter','','','2014-08-07 12:54:12','2014-08-07 19:54:12','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?page_id=1242',6,'page','',0),(1244,4,'2014-08-07 04:46:41','2014-08-07 11:46:41','','queen','','inherit','open','open','','queen','','','2014-08-07 04:46:41','2014-08-07 11:46:41','',1242,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/queen.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1247,4,'2014-08-07 07:11:48','2014-08-07 14:11:48','','rogan-la','','inherit','open','open','','rogan-la','','','2014-08-07 07:11:48','2014-08-07 14:11:48','',1242,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/rogan-la.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1251,4,'2014-08-07 07:30:25','2014-08-07 14:30:25','<h1><strong>BATS Summer Photo Contest!<br />Aug. 7 - Sept. 21<br /></strong></h1>\r\n<h2><strong><a href=\"http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/summer-photo.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-1293 alignleft\" style=\"padding-right: 10px;\" src=\"http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/summer-photo.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"268\" height=\"236\" /></a>Enter on Instagram and/or Twitter!</strong></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>@BATSImprov </strong><br /><strong>#summerimprov</strong></h2>\r\n<p>The summer festival shows and summer session classes have started and we want your photos! Snap a photo or two (or three or four) <strong>related to your BATS summer experience</strong> and post them on Instagram, and/or Twitter (sorry, no Facebook entries this time around), tagging <strong>@BATSImprov</strong> and using the hashtag <strong>#summerimprov</strong>. We encouage photos snapped at our theater and even random photos with a message drawing the connection a BATS summer memory!</p>\r\n<p> All photos must be submitted by <strong>September 21, 2014</strong> to qualify. Three winners will be chosen by BATS\' staff.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>PRIZES<br /></strong></span><strong>1st prize: ONE MONTH of BATS shows for you + a friend!</strong> <strong>Two drinks per night included!  </strong>Choose any one month period in the next year and come to ANY show with a friend for FREE! This is up to a $160 value!</p>\r\n<p> <strong>2nd prize: 6 TICKETS and $30 WORTH OF CONCESSIONS for the night(s) you come!</strong> Why not have some of our delicious baked goods and beer (or soda or chips or candy) with your improv?</p>\r\n<p> <strong>3rd prize: 2 TICKETS to shows at BATS! </strong>Two shows for you or one show for you + a friend!</p>\r\n<p><em>Again - you must tag<strong> @batsimprov</strong> and use the hash tag <strong>#summerimprov</strong> and have your posts <strong>publicly viewable</strong> to enter.  Each photograph will count as one entry.</em></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Terms and conditions:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>All participants must ask permission before taking and before posting any photos of classmates or audience members.</li>\r\n<li>Be respectful! Please do not take photos in a way that would disrupt a class or show or make anyone feel self-conscious. Our first priority is creating a professional atmosphere at shows and a comfortable space in classes, and great photos are our second priority!</li>\r\n<li>In order to qualify, photos must be posted to Instagram or Twitter (no Facebook for this contest!) and tag @BATSImprov, use the hashtag #summerimprov, and be publicly viewable (if your Twitter or Instagram is set on private we won’t be able to see the photos)</li>\r\n<li>BATS reserves the rights to use all submitted photos in future publicity and marketing</li>\r\n<li>Prizes are not valid for “Special Guest” shows or shows designated as “no discounts or passes.” Any weekends with non-qualifying shows do not count towards the one-month time period.</li>\r\n<li>Free passes may not be re-sold. In order to qualify for the you + a friend deal you must be present at the show (but the friend can change every show!).</li>\r\n<li>1st place price of free month of shows must be redeemed by July 1st, 2015.</li>\r\n</ul>','Summer Photo Contest','','publish','open','open','','summer-photo-contest','','','2014-09-04 12:37:34','2014-09-04 19:37:34','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?page_id=1251',5,'page','',0),(1253,4,'2014-08-07 08:12:47','2014-08-07 15:12:47','','summer-keith','','inherit','open','open','','summer-keith','','','2014-08-07 08:12:47','2014-08-07 15:12:47','',1251,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/summer-keith.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1254,4,'2014-08-07 08:19:59','2014-08-07 15:19:59','','shakes-25-throwback','','inherit','open','open','','shakes-25-throwback','','','2014-08-07 08:19:59','2014-08-07 15:19:59','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/shakes-25-throwback.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1257,7,'2014-08-07 14:17:34','2014-08-07 21:17:34','','September','','publish','open','open','','september','','','2014-08-07 14:23:43','2014-08-07 21:23:43','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=sunday&#038;p=1257',8,'sunday','',0),(1259,5,'2014-08-07 15:24:15','2014-08-07 22:24:15','<h1>Foundation 1 Intensive<br /> 3-Days; Aug. 15-17<br />Friday, 10:00 AM - 5:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Fri-Sun, August 15-17, 2014</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>This second session just added!</em></p>\r\n<p><strong> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Tuition: $325<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule:</strong> 3 day-long sessions<br /> <strong>Class Times:</strong> 10am-5pm, with a 1-hour lunch break<br /> <strong>Class size:</strong> 16 students maximum<br /> <strong>Class length:</strong> 6 hours of instruction per day (18 hours total)<br /> <stron