le=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Schedule:</strong> 8 sessions (once a week for 8 weeks), 2 performances<br /><strong>Class Time/Dates: </strong>11am-2pm on Saturdays October 18, 25, November 1, 8, 15, 22, (skip 11/29 for Thanksgiving), December 6, and 13<br /><strong>Performances: </strong>2 performances: Saturday, <span data-term=\"goog_702905197\">November  22, 12-1pm</span>: open class for friends and guests, and Sunday <span data-term=\"goog_702905198\">December 7, 6-7pm</span>: performance with a paid audience at the Bayfront Theater<br /><strong>Class size:</strong> 10 students maximum <strong><br />Class length: </strong>3 hours (24 hours total of instruction)<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong>Studio Scene Work<em><br /> </em></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">This 8-week workshop prepares you for your first performance in front of an audience by breaking down and covering these different core elements of performance:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Stage skills</li>\r\n<li>Shape of show</li>\r\n<li>Games (setting up, introducing, and playing)</li>\r\n<li>Scenes (setting up, starting, and ending)</li>\r\n<li>Audience interaction</li>\r\n<li>Ensemble-building</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You’ll learn new games and explore the balance between games and scenes for a well-crafted show.  The Workshop includes two performances: one is an open workshop for friends and guests and the second is a full show with a paid audience.</p>','Performance - Performance Workshop 1 with John Remak (#10-2001)','','publish','open','open','','performance-performance-workshop-1-with-john-remak-10-2001','','','2014-09-18 15:42:01','2014-09-18 22:42:01','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1308',0,'class','',0),(1309,5,'2014-09-11 14:59:09','2014-09-11 21:59:09','<h1>4-Week Studio Scene Work <br />Tuesdays, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>October 7 – October 28, 2014<br /></strong><strong>Studio 210, San Francisco (the Mission)</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 4 sessions (o