ase contact regina@improv.org.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #222222;\">It\'s winter and the office is having its annual holiday party.  Come meet our cast of co-workers, and find out what happens when the drinks starts flowing and people start to speak freely about the job, their lives and their loves. You never know what\'s just below the surface. The ensemble will create a night of romance, heartache, tender moments and dysfunction, all in song. This workshop is designed for improvisors with a strong foundation and comfort in improvised singing. </span></p>','Performance - Office Holiday Musical with Lisa & Joshua (#11-2008)','','publish','open','open','','performance-office-holiday-musical-with-lisa-joshua-11-2008','','','2014-10-06 16:21:54','2014-10-06 23:21:54','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1331',0,'class','',0),(1332,5,'2014-09-24 17:40:59','2014-09-25 00:40:59','<h1>Advanced Performance Workshop, <br />Charles Dickens<br />Tuesdays &amp; Thursdays<br />December 2 – December 18, 2014</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Studio 210, San Francisco (The Mission) <br />+ Dress Rehearsal &amp; Performances at the Bayfront Theater<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 6 sessions (twice weekly for three weeks)<br /> <strong>Class Dates:</strong> December 2, 4, 9, 11, 16, and 18. Most classes will meet at Studio 210 in the Mission, December 18th will be a dress rehearsal at the Bayfront Theater.<br /><strong>Performances: </strong>Dress rehearsal on Thursday, December 18th at 7pm, show on Sunday, December 21st, tiume TBD<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (15 hours total instruction)<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $329<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Enrollment only with coaches\' and dean\'s approval; to confirm eligibility, please contact regina@improv.org. </p>\r\n<p>Dive into the Dickensian style of storytelling! In this twice-weekly workshop, we\'ll identify and play with the elements of Charles Dickens\' world of Victorian England, including:<br />- unique characterization <br />- social criticism<br />- accents <br />- manners and status during the 1800s</p>\r\n<p>This 15-hour intensive offers you a great opportunity to hone and practice your long-form skills, build ensemble, and study this genre. The class will culminate in two shows presented to family, friends, and audience who love a Dickensian tale.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"> </p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"> </p>','Performance - Dickens with Ben (#12-2013)','','publish','open','open','','performance-dickens-with-ben-12-2013','','','2014-10-01 15:58:10','2014-10-01 22:58:10','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1332',0,'class','',0),(1334,4,'2014-09-25 16:30:39','2014-09-25 23:30:39','','clap1','','inherit','open','open','','clap1','','','2014-09-25 16:30:39','2014-09-25 23:30:39','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/clap1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1337,5,'2014-09-29 14:22:09','2014-09-29 21:22:09','<h1>Intro to Improv<br />Thursday, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>November 6, 2014<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: One session<br /> <strong>Class date:</strong> November 6<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $45<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> None - everyone is welcome!</p>','Intro to Improv with William Hall (#11-2015)','','publish','open','open','','intro-to-improv-with-coach-tbd-11-2015','','','2014-10-16 14:41:35','2014-10-16 21:41:35','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1337',0,'class','',0),(1338,5,'2014-09-29 14:21:34','2014-09-29 21:21:34','','Coach TBD','','publish','open','open','','coach-tbd','','','2014-09-29 14:21:34','2014-09-29 21:21:34','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=actors&#038;p=1338',7,'actors','',0),(1341,7,'2014-09-30 14:42:50','2014-09-30 21:42:50','','October','','publish','closed','open','','october','','','2015-10-20 13:51:00','2015-10-20 20:51:00','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=sunday&#038;p=1341',7,'sunday','',0),(1342,7,'2014-09-30 14:55:02','2014-09-30 21:55:02','','November','','publish','closed','open','','november','','','2015-11-16 11:27:13','2015-11-16 19:27:13','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=sunday&#038;p=1342',9,'sunday','',0),(1343,7,'2014-09-30 15:04:09','2014-09-30 22:04:09','','December','','publish','closed','open','','december','','','2015-11-16 11:40:52','2015-11-16 19:40:52','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=sunday&#038;p=1343',11,'sunday','',0),(1344,5,'2014-10-01 15:30:34','2014-10-01 22:30:34','<h1>Performing Improvised Star Trek<br />Saturdays, 2:30 PM - 5:30 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>October 18 - November 8 <br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 4 sessions and one performance<br /> <strong>Class Dates:</strong> October 18, 25, November 1, and 8<br /><strong>Performance: </strong>6pm on Sunday, November 9<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (12 hours total instruction)<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $229<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Enrollment only with coach and dean approval; to confirm eligibility, please contact regina@improv.org.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Want to explore the universe of Star Trek and perform it in a long form?  Then beam on over, this class is for you!  In this class you will learn how to improvise long form Star Trek (with more of a focus on the Original Series) and have one performance. We will cover many aspects of Star Trek - life on board a starship and in the universe of Star Trek, ranks and relationships including comfortably portraying the Captain all the way down to Crewman #2, alien planets, ship battles, mastering the science and technology while feeling calm and confident, all while learning long form and storytelling in a safe, supportive and fun environment.  In this class, we\'ll Boldly Go Where No One Has Gone Before! </span></p>','Performance - Star Trek with Laura (#10-2016)','','publish','open','open','','performance-star-trek-with-laura-10-2016','','','2014-10-06 11:59:00','2014-10-06 18:59:00','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1344',0,'class','',0),(1345,5,'2014-10-01 15:46:28','2014-10-01 22:46:28','<h1>Performance Workshop 2 - Theatresports<br />Tuesdays, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>October 28 - December 16, 2014<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Schedule:</strong> 8 sessions (once a week for 8 weeks), 2 performances<br /><strong>Class Time/Dates: </strong>7-10pm on Tuesdays Oct. 28, Nov. 4, 11, 18, 25, December 2, 9, and 16<br /><strong>Performances: </strong>2 performances: dates TBD<br /><strong>Class size:</strong> 12 students maximum <strong><br />Class length: </strong>3 hours (24 hours total of instruction)<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong>Performance Workshop 1 or coach/dean approval. Contact regina@improv.org with any eligibility questions.<em><br /> </em></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span><span>This workshop is the next level in our performing series to prepare improvisers for performance.  This unique Johnstonian format, the ever-challenging and ever-entertaining Theatresports, helps you learn and practice multiple skills to provide a confident, fun, and entertaining performance.  </span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span>In this class, we\'ll develop ensemble, learning how best to interact with teammates, the opposing team, the judges, and the audience.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span>We\'ll also explore the logistics of learning, preparing, and playing Theatresports: creating team themes/personas, issuing challenges, learning new performance games, and adapting on the fly for the utmost variety  and interesting shape of show.</span></p>','Performance - Performance Workshop 2 (TS) with Laura (#10-2002)','','draft','open','open','','performance-performance-workshop-2-ts-with-laura-10-2002','','','2014-10-20 13:34:34','2014-10-20 20:34:34','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1345',0,'class','',0),(1347,4,'2014-10-03 12:54:25','2014-10-03 19:54:25','','twilight-313','','inherit','open','open','','twilight-313','','','2014-10-03 12:54:25','2014-10-03 19:54:25','',633,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/twilight-313.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1348,4,'2014-10-03 13:13:29','2014-10-03 20:13:29','','dead-web313','','inherit','open','open','','dead-web313','','','2014-10-03 13:13:29','2014-10-03 20:13:29','',903,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/dead-web313.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1352,5,'2014-10-09 16:02:20','2014-10-09 23:02:20','<h1>Mondays, 7:00 PM - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>November 3 – December 8, 2014<br /> Cubberley Community Center, Palo Alto<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 6 sessions (once a week for 6 weeks)<br /> <strong>Class Dates:</strong> November 3, 10, 17, 24, December 1, and 8<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (18 hours total instruction)<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $329<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> <a title=\"Foundation 1\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-1/\">Foundation 1</a></p>','F2 - Foundation 2 in Palo Alto with Chris Sams (#11-2016)','','publish','closed','open','','f2-foundation-2-in-palo-alto-with-chris-sams-11-2016','','','2014-10-09 16:02:20','2014-10-09 23:02:20','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1352',0,'class','',0),(1356,5,'2014-10-13 16:18:52','2014-10-13 23:18:52','<h1>Winter Break Teen Improv Ensemble<br />Tuesday, Wednesday, and Friday</h1>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule:</strong> Tuesday, December 30th; Wednesday, December 31st; and Friday, January 2nd, from 12pm-4pm each day<br /><st