hedule:</strong> 8 sessions (once a week for 8 weeks), 2 performances<br /><strong>Class Time/Dates: </strong>7-10pm on Thursdays February 12, 19, 26, March 5, 12, 19, 26, and April 2<br /><strong>Performances: </strong>2 performances: Thursday, March 19th  - open class/workshop at Cubberley Community Center, and Sunday, March 29th, exact time TBD at the Bayfront Theater, SF<br /><strong>Class size:</strong> 12 students maximum <strong><br />Class length: </strong>3 hours (24 hours total of instruction)<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong>Performance Workshop 1 or coach/dean approval. Contact regina@improv.org with any eligibility questions.<em><br /> </em></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0pt;\">This workshop is the next level in our performing series to prepare improvisers for performance.  This unique Johnstonian format, the ever-challenging and ever-entertaining Theatresports, helps you learn and practice multiple skills to provide a confident, fun, and entertaining performance.  </p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0pt;\">In this class, we\'ll develop ensemble, learning how best to interact with teammates, the opposing team, the judges, and the audience.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0pt;\">We\'ll also explore the logistics of learning, preparing, and playing Theatresports: creating team themes/personas, issuing challenges, learning new performance games, and adapting on the fly for the utmost variety  and interesting shape of show.</p>','Performance - Performance Workshop 2 (TS) with Kasey Klemm (#15-02-2077)','','publish','open','open','','performance-performance-workshop-2-ts-with-tbd-01-2038','','','2015-02-05 14:03:43','2015-02-05 22:03:43','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1393',0,'class','',0),(1396,4,'2014-11-11 12:39:03','2014-11-11 20:39:03','<p><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1398 \" style=\"margin-right: 10px;\" src=\"http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_3199-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_3199\" width=\"324\" height=\"216\" /></p>\r\n<h4><strong>Week of November 16 - 22, 2015<br /></strong>What\'s parking like at Fort Mason?</h4>\r\n<h4>Crowded all week (very crowded this weekend)</h4>\r\n<p><strong>Lean Startup Conference:</strong> 9am-8pm Monday, 9am-6pm Tuesday &amp; Wednesday (estimated attendance 1,500/day)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Pachamama:</strong> 12-3:30pm Thursday (estimated attendance 2,000)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Renegade Craft Fair:</strong> 11am-7pm Saturday &amp; Sunday (estimated attendance 7,000/day)</p>\r\n<p>Weekly events:<br />-<strong> Fort Mason Farmer\'s Market</strong>: Sundays 9:30am-1:30pm (est. attendance 1,000) </p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Options for Bad Parking Days</h3>\r\n<p>When there are big events at Fort Mason, we encourage you to take public transportation, carpool, and/or leave some extra time for parking before your classes.</p>\r\n<p>Depending on how large the event it, it is usually still a good idea to check the Fort Mason parking lots first, but we have also compiled a list of recommendations for days when parking is especially tough.</p>\r\n<h4>Other parking lots (all about a 15 min walk to BATS)</h4>\r\n<p>Lombard Street Garage - 2055 Lombard Street<br />Rates are between $1 and $3 per hour (depending on time of day).</p>\r\n<p>Hotel Del Sol - Hotel address is 3100 Webster st. and the parking lot entrance is just around the corner on Lombard St.<br />$10/day.</p>\r\n<p>Wells Fargo Lot - 2055 Chestnut Street <br />$2.50 each 15 min or $20 for 10 hours. $13 on Sundays.</p>\r\n<h4>Valet Parking apps</h4>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.luxevalet.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Luxe Valet</a> - avg. hourly rate of $5 and max of $15/day</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://zirx.com/\" target=\"_blank\">ZIRX</a> - $15/day (their coverage area does not go all the way to Fort Mason but you could call them near Ghirardelli square and walk the rest of the way)</p>\r\n<h4>Public Transportation</h4>\r\n<p>When parking is bad, the easiest way to get here is by public transportation! Several bus (MUNI) lines stop close to Fort Mason Center:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>10 Townsend (comes from the Financial District)</li>\r\n<li>22 Fillmore (comes from Potrero Hill, up along Fillmore, stopping just a few blocks away)</li>\r\n<li>28 – 19th Avenue (comes from SFSU and stops right outside the FMC gates)</li>\r\n<li>30 Stockton</li>\r\n<li>47 Van Ness (comes straight up Van Ness, stopping just a few blocks away)</li>\r\n<li>49 Van Ness/Mission (comes straight up Van Ness, stopping just a few blocks away)</li>\r\n<li>82x Presidio/Wharves Express</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Need more help? Try the Bay Area public transportation <a href=\"http://www.511.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Trip Planner</a> (511.org).</p>\r\n<p><strong>And don’t forget you can always take taxis, Lyft, Uber, etc!</strong> (If you’re a first time user to these apps, you can usually find a code for a free first use if you do a little Google searching.)</p>\r\n<p><em>None of these parking options are owned or operated by BATS Improv, and all parking is subject to availability. If you have any edits or tips to help us improve this list, please let us know at bats@improv.org.</em></p>','Alternate Fort Mason Parking Options','','publish','open','open','','parking','','','2015-11-16 11:47:39','2015-11-16 19:47:39','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?page_id=1396',4,'page','',0),(1397,7,'2015-11-16 11:47:22','2015-11-16 19:47:22','<p><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1398 \" style=\"margin-right: 10px;\" src=\"http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_3199-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_3199\" width=\"324\" height=\"216\" /></p>\n<h4><strong>Week of November 16 - 22, 2015<br /></strong>What\'s parking like at Fort Mason?</h4>\n<h4>Crowded all week (very crowded this weekend)</h4>\n<p><strong>Lean Startup Conference:</strong> 9am-8pm Monday, 9am-6pm Tuesday &amp; Wednesday (estimated attendance 1,500/day)</p>\n<p><strong>Pachamama:</strong> 12-3:30pm Thursday (estimated attendance 2,000)</p>\n<p><strong>Renegade Cr