li>Scenes (setting up, starting, and ending)</li>\r\n<li>Audience interaction</li>\r\n<li>Ensemble-building</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You’ll learn new games and explore the balance between games and scenes for a well-crafted show.  The Workshop includes two performances: one is an open workshop for friends and guests and the second is a full show with a paid audience.</p>','Performance - Performance Workshop 1 with John Remak (#02-2049)','','publish','open','open','','performance-performance-workshop-1-with-tbd-02-2049','','','2014-11-25 14:37:48','2014-11-25 22:37:48','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1411',0,'class','',0),(1412,5,'2014-11-12 13:47:00','2014-11-12 21:47:00','<h1>Intro to Improv at Fort Mason<br />Friday, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong></strong><strong>SOLD OUT - CLICK ON \"SIGN UP\" BUTTON TO ADD TO WAIT LIST</strong><br /><br />Friday, February 6th<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: One session<br /> <strong>Class date:</strong> February 6<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $45<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> None - everyone is welcome!</p>','I - Intro to Improv with Laura Derry (#02-2052)','','publish','open','open','','i-intro-to-improv-with-tbd-02-2052','','','2015-01-28 14:15:18','2015-01-28 22:15:18','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1412',0,'class','',0),(1427,4,'2014-11-21 18:53:57','2014-11-22 02:53:57','','stockley-headshot','','inherit','open','open','','stockley-headshot','','','2014-11-21 18:53:57','2014-11-22 02:53:57','',218,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/stockley-headshot.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1428,4,'2014-11-21 18:57:30','2014-11-22 02:57:30','','Rebecca-side-236','','inherit','open','open','','rebecca-side-236','','','2014-11-21 18:57:30','2014-11-22 02:57:30','',218,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Rebecca-side-236.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1429,4,'2