 Foundation 1, Ken Robertson (#03-2054)','','publish','open','open','','f1-foundation-1-ken-robertson-03-2054','','','2014-11-28 11:50:37','2014-11-28 19:50:37','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1440',0,'class','',0),(1441,5,'2014-11-28 11:48:13','2014-11-28 19:48:13','<h1>Improv Singing 101 <br />Sundays, 2:30 PM - 5:30 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>January 11, 2015 - February 15, 2015<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 6 sessions (once a week for 6 weeks)<br /> <strong>Class dates:</strong> January 11, 18, 25, February 1, 8, 15<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (18 hours total instruction)<br /> <strong>Class</strong> <strong>size:</strong> 16 students maximum<br /> <strong>Tuition:</strong> $299<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong>Foundation 1<br /><br />This 6-week workshop is designed to teach the essential principles of how to create improvised solos, duets, and choruses. We break down the challenge of singing a song into its basics - breathing, ear and voice training, rhyme and rhythm exercises. <br /><br />This is the perfect class for <em>anyone</em> interested in learning about the different elements of improvised songs. No previous singing training, performance, or experience is needed! All that\'s required is a healthy sense of curiosity and the knowledge of your improv basics!</p>','Improv Singing 101 with JRB (#01-2037)','','publish','open','open','','improv-singing-101-with-jrb-01-2037','','','2014-11-28 11:48:13','2014-11-28 19:48:13','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1441',0,'class','',0),(1442,7,'2014-12-01 13:33:48','2014-12-01 21:33:48','','20141025_141156','','inherit','open','open','','20141025_141156','','','2014-12-01 13:33:48','2014-12-01 21:33:48','',1343,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/20141025_141156.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1445,5,'2014-12-01 15:02:34','2014-12-01 23:02:34','<h1>6-Week Studio Scene Work:<br />Genre Specialty <br />Saturdays 11:00 AM - 2:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>January 10 – February 14, 2015<br /></strong><strong>Bayfront Theater, San Francisco </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 6 sessions (once a week for 6 weeks)<br /><strong>Class dates: </strong>January 10, 17, 24, 31, February 7, and 14 <em>(please note that on January 17th class will meet from <span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: small; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;\"><strong>11:30am - 2:30pm</strong></span>)</em><br /><strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (18 hours total)<br /><strong>Class size: </strong>10 students maximum<br /><strong>Tuition</strong>: $299 <br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong><a href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-3/\">Foundation 3</a></p>\r\n<p>This 6-week class is a great opportunity for you to build your individual scene skills in the context of learning about and exploring a variety of genres. Like other Studio Scenework classes, you\'ll focus on the core skills of character, space object, and narrative while getting individualized attention and feedback.  </p>\r\n<p>You\'ll <em>also</em> get the added bonus of playing in popular genres, including (but not limited to) western, film noir, and romance.  </p>\r\n<p>Whether you\'re looking for a fun introduction to genre, you love genre work and want to play in it more, or you just want to approach your scene skills in a new way, this class is for YOU! </p>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\"> </div>','SS - 6-Week Studio Scene Work - Genre with John Remak','','publish','open','open','','ss-6-week-studio-scene-work-genre-with-john-remak','','','2014-12-05 14:00:13','2014-12-05 22:00:13','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1445',0,'class','',0),(1447,5,'2014-12-01 16:25:47','2014-12-02 00:25:47','<h1>Performance Workshop 3 - <br />Elements of Long Form<br />Wednesdays, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>February 25 - April 15, 2015<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Schedule:</strong> 8 sessions (once a week for 8 weeks), 2 performances<br /><strong>Class Time/Dates: </strong>7-10pm on Wednesdays February 25, March 4, 11, 18, 25, April 1, 8, and 15<br /><strong>Performances: </strong>2 performances: Wednesday, March 25th, 7:30-9:30pm: open performance for friends and invited guests, and <br />Sunday, April 12th, time TBD, performance with a paid audience at the Bayfront Theater<br /><strong>Class size:</strong> 10 students maximum <strong><br />Class length: </strong>3 hours (24 hours total of instruction)<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong>Performance Workshop 1 and 2 or coach/dean approval. Contact regina@improv.org with any eligibility questions.<em><br /> </em></p>\r\n<p>This 8-week workshop, the third in our Performance Series, prepares you for your first<br /> Long-Form performance in front of an audience by breaking down and covering these different core elements of performance: </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Taking your time and paying attention</li>\r\n<li>Narrative, and establishing a strong foundation</li>\r\n<li>Acting</li>\r\n<li>Improvising in genre</li>\r\n<li>Transitions between scenes</li>\r\n<li>Ensemble acting</li>\r\n<li>Building locations and maintaining a space object world</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>This class will qualify you to be considered for more advanced work as it will give you a grounding in the essential elements of Long-Form improvisation as BATS practices it.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Performance - Performance Workshop 3 (ELF) with Regina Saisi (#02-2050)','','draft','open','open','','performance-performance-workshop-3-elf-with-regina-saisi-02-2050','','','2015-01-30 17:24:20','2015-01-31 01:24:20','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1447',0,'class','',0),(1448,5,'2014-12-01 17:20:06','2014-12-02 01:20:06','<h1>Teen Improv Ensemble<br />8 weeks, Fridays, 4:15 - 6:15 PM</h1>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule:</strong> Fridays, 4:15 – 6:15 pm  <br /><span style=\"color: #222222; font-size: 13px;\">January 23, 30, February 6, 13, 20, 27, March 6, and 13<br /></span><strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Attending High School, no prior improv experience necessary</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">Have you done some improv and are itching to do more?!  Always wanted to try but weren\'t sure how to?  Are you a natural performer or someone who wants to come out of your shell?  Improv has something for absolutely everyone! </p>\r\n<p>In our teen improv class teens will work together learning improv principles and growing  into an ensemble as they have fun, make friends, and play on stage.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">The classes will be held at the Bayfront Theater in Fort Mason Center.   This is an after school workshop and open to high school students. The workshop will run for 8 weeks total. </p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">As part of this class, students will receive 2-for-1 passes to use to shows on the same days as their classes.  Watching improv is a fantastic way to learn it and see the principles at work. </p>','Young Improvisers\'  Ensemble w/Laura Derry (#01-2036)','','publish','open','open','','young-improvisers-ensemble-wlaura-derry-01-2036','','','2014-12-01 17:20:43','2014-12-02 01:20:43','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1448',0,'class','',0),(1449,5,'2014-12-02 15:49:04','2014-12-02 23:49:04','<h1>Improv for Shy People<br />Tuesdays, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Tuesday, January 6 and Tuesday, January 13 <br />Studio 210, San Francisco (the Mission)</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 2 sessions (once a week for two weeks)<br /> <strong>Class dates and time:</strong> 7-10pm on January 6th and 13th<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (6 hours total)<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $90<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> None - everyone is welcome!</p>\r\n<p>Do you self-identify as shy or introverted? Are you unlikely to be the first to speak up in class or in a meeting? Do you find yourself overshadowed by your friends, family, or colleagues? Are you overwhelmed when you\'re in a big group of people? </p>\r\n<p>Signing up for an improv class may be the last thing on your mind if you consider yourself shy, but you\'d be surprised how safe and supportive the art form can be.  Focused on creating a comfortable and safe environment, Improv for Shy People introduces the basics of BATS-style improv in order to cultivate spontaneity, flexibility, and confidence.  Improv skills build trust and cooperation and tap into the imaginative and creative qualities that we all possess. This 2-week class will leave you with some real tools to apply to your life, and you\'ll have a tremendously fun time in the process of acquiring them!</p>','I - Improv for Shy People with Chris Sams (#02-2062)','','publish','open','open','','i-improv-for-shy-people-with-chris-sams-02-2062','','','2014-12-02 15:55:36','2014-12-02 23:55:36','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1449',0,'class','',0),(1450,5,'2014-12-02 16:03:25','2014-12-03 00:03:25','<h1>Youth Improv<br />6 weeks, Mondays, 4:30-6:30pm</h1>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule:</strong> Mondays, 4:30–6:30pm <br />April 13, 20, 27, May 4, 11, and 18 <br /><em>Final class on May 18th is an open showcase for family and friends</em><br /><strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Attending 5th or 6th grade (10-12 years old), no prior improv experience necessary</p>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222;\">Have you done some improv and are itching to do more?!  Always wanted to try but weren\'t sure how to?  Are you a natural performer or someone who feels nervous about being on a stage?  Improv has something for absolutely everyone! </div>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222;\"> </div>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222;\">In our youth improv class, students will work together learning improv principles and growing into an ensemble as they have fun, make friends, and play on stage. </div>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222;\"> </div>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222;\">The classes will be held at the Bayfront Theater in Fort Mason Center. This is an after school workshop and open to 5th and 6th grade students. The workshop will run for 6 weeks total.</div>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"> </p>','Spring  - Youth improv w/Mona Thompson','','publish','open','open','','winter-middle-school-improv-wmona-thompson','','','2015-04-10 14:56:02','2015-04-10 21:56:02','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1450',0,'class','',0),(1451,5,'2014-12-02 16:16:51','2014-12-03 00:16:51','<h1>Intro to Improv at Fort Mason<br />Sunday, 11:00 AM - 2:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>SOLD OUT - CLICK ON \"SIGN UP\" BUTTON TO ADD TO WAIT LIST</strong></p>\r\n<p>Sunday, February 15th<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: One session<br /> <strong>Class date:</strong> February 15<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $45<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> None - everyone is welcome!</p>','I - Intro to Improv with Rebecca Poretsky (#02-2051)','','publish','open','open','','i-intro-to-improv-with-rebecca-poretsky-02-2051','','','2015-01-28 14:14:03','2015-01-28 22:14:03','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1451',0,'class','',0),(1452,5,'2014-12-02 16:21:05','2014-12-03 00:21:05','','unnamed (1)','','inherit','open','open','','unnamed-1','','','2014-12-02 16:21:05','2014-12-03 00:21:05','',1209,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/unnamed-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1453,5,'2014-12-02 16:31:00','2014-12-03 00:31:00','','mona - small pic','','inherit','open','open','','mona-small-pic','','','2014-12-02 16:31:00','2014-12-03 00:31:00','',1209,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/mona-small-pic.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1454,5,'2014-12-02 16:42:13','2014-12-03 00:42:13','<h1>Improv Singing 101 <br />Sundays, 2:30 PM - 5:30 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>January 11, 2015 - February 15, 2015<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 6 sessions (once a week for 6 weeks)<br /> <strong>Class dates:</strong> January 11, 18, 25, February 1, 8, 15<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (18 hours total instruction)<br /> <strong>Class</strong> <strong>size:</strong> 16 students maximum<br /> <strong>Tuition:</strong> $299<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong>Foundation 1</p>\r\n<p>This 6-week workshop is designed to teach the essential principles of how to create improvised solos, duets, and choruses. We break down the challenge of singing a song into its basics - breathing, ear and voice training, rhyme and rhythm exercises. </p>\r\n<p>This is the perfect class for <em>anyone</em> interested in learning about the different elements of improvised songs. No previous singing training, performance, or experience is needed! All that\'s required is a healthy sense of curiosity and the knowledge of your improv basics!</p>','Improv Singing 101 with JRB (#01-2037)','','publish','open','open','','improv-singing-101-with-jrb-01-2037-2','','','2014-12-02 16:42:13','2014-12-03 00:42:13','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1454',0,'class','',0),(1455,5,'2014-12-02 16:51:54','2014-12-03 00:51:54','<h1>First Things First <br />Tuesdays, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>January 20 and January 27, 2015 <br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 2 sessions (once a week for 2 weeks)<br /> <strong>Class dates:</strong> January 20 and 27<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (6 hours total instruction)<br /> <strong>Class</strong> <strong>size:</strong> 10 students maximum<br /> <strong>Tuition:</strong> $90<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong>Foundation 3 and above<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>Making short-form scenes consistently shine can be one of the greatest challenges in improv, and it begins from the very first offer. In this 2-week scene-work intensive class, we’ll focus on jumping into short form with gusto and finding those early offers so you don’t feel lost in the scene. We’ll dig in on those offers and escalate the stakes to make your scenes feel tight, fresh and focused.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','First Things First with Ken Robertson (#01-2064)','','draft','open','open','','first-things-first-with-ken-robertson-01-2064','','','2015-01-19 10:17:34','2015-01-19 18:17:34','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1455',0,'class','',0),(1458,5,'2014-12-02 16:52:58','2014-12-03 00:52:58','<h1>First Things First <br />Tuesdays, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>January 20 and January 27, 2015 <br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 2 sessions (once a week for 2 weeks)<br /> <strong>Class dates:</strong> January 20 and 27<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (6 hours total instruction)<br /> <strong>Class</strong> <strong>size:</strong> 10 students maximum<br /> <strong>Tuition:</strong> $90<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong>Foundation 3 and above</p>\r\n<p>Making short-form scenes consistently shine can be one of the greatest challenges in improv, and it begins from the very first offer. In this 2-week scene-work intensive class, we’ll focus on jumping into short form with gusto and finding those early offers so you don’t feel lost in the scene. We’ll dig in on those offers and escalate the stakes to make your scenes feel tight, fresh and focused.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','First Things First with Ken Robertson (#01-2064)','','draft','open','open','','first-things-first-with-ken-robertson-01-2064-2','','','2015-01-19 10:17:44','2015-01-19 18:17:44','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1458',0,'class','',0),(1459,4,'2014-12-02 18:36:09','2014-12-03 02:36:09','<p>Gift yourself or a friend with six tickets to BATS. Come to six shows on your own, or bring a friend to three, or treat two-thirds of the Supreme Court to one, or (you get the picture.)</p>\r\n<p><em><strong>Six-pack tickets valid for all shows except NYE.</strong></em></p>','Show Six-Pack','','draft','open','open','','show-six-packs','','','2015-08-20 22:17:49','2015-08-21 05:17:49','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=special&#038;p=1459',13,'special','',0),(1460,4,'2014-12-02 18:40:53','2014-12-03 02:40:53','','6pack-web313','','inherit','open','open','','6pack-web313','','','2014-12-02 18:40:53','2014-12-03 02:40:53','',1459,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/6pack-web313.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1461,4,'2014-12-02 18:51:23','2014-12-03 02:51:23','<h2>Give a Gift Certificate in Any Amount</h2>\r\n<p>Gift Certificates can be used for shows, concessions, classes, and BATS merch!  Or, give one of these specific gift certificates:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>3-Hour Introductory Improv Workshop – $45</h2>\r\n<p>Offer a friend, co-worker, or that uptight clerk at the DMV a chance to dip their toe in the liberating waters of improv. <a title=\"3-hour Intro Workshops\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/school/3-hour-intro-workshops/\">Introduction to Improv</a> <em>and</em> <a title=\"3-hour Intro Workshops\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/school/3-hour-intro-workshops/\">Improv for Shy People</a> give students the basics behind improvised theatre. Your gift recipient will have fun exploring spontaneity, creativity, and flexibility by playing improv games, <em>and</em> meet new people — all in one safe, supportive 3-hour session. Enroll yourself, and buy a gift certificate for your buddy!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Foundation 1 Class – beginning at $299</h2>\r\n<p>Regardless of your lucky giftee’s experience, background, or training, she or he will benefit from studying improv at BATS. <a title=\"Foundation 1\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/school/foundation-1/\">Foundation 1</a> is where all beginners start the fun. Through games and exercises, students play, explore, and experiment with creating characters and scenes, guided by one of our seasoned coaches.</p>','Gift Certificates','','draft','open','open','','gift-certificates','','','2015-06-22 13:18:48','2015-06-22 20:18:48','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=special&#038;p=1461',14,'special','',0),(1462,4,'2014-12-02 18:51:15','2014-12-03 02:51:15','','gift-web313','','inherit','open','open','','gift-web313','','','2014-12-02 18:51:15','2014-12-03 02:51:15','',1461,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/gift-web313.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1464,4,'2014-12-04 16:00:28','2014-12-05 00:00:28','','holiday-web313','','inherit','open','open','','holiday-web313','','','2014-12-04 16:00:28','2014-12-05 00:00:28','',81,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/holiday-web313.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1465,4,'2014-12-04 16:06:34','2014-12-05 00:06:34','','6pack-white-web313','','inherit','open','open','','6pack-white-web313','','','2014-12-04 16:06:34','2014-12-05 00:06:34','',1459,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/6pack-white-web313.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1466,4,'2014-12-04 16:40:10','2014-12-05 00:40:10','','NYE-rebecca-web313','','inherit','open','open','','nye-rebecca-web313','','','2014-12-04 16:40:10','2014-12-05 00:40:10','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/NYE-rebecca-web313.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1467,4,'2014-12-04 16:45:50','2014-12-05 00:45:50','','see-show-paul','','inherit','open','open','','see-show-paul','','','2014-12-04 16:45:50','2014-12-05 00:45:50','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/see-show-paul.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1468,4,'2014-12-04 16:54:01','2014-12-05 00:54:01','','take-class-corey','','inherit','open','open','','take-class-corey','','','2014-12-04 16:54:01','2014-12-05 00