ong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 6 sessions (once a week for 6 weeks)<br /> <strong>Class dates:</strong> March 14, 21, 28, April 4, 11, and 18<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (18 hours total instruction)<br /> <strong>Class size:</strong> 12 students maximum<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $299<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> <a title=\"Foundation 2\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-2/\">Foundation 2</a></p>','F3 - Foundation 3 with Laura Derry (#03-2057)','','publish','open','open','','f3-foundation-3-with-laura-derry-03-2057','','','2014-12-05 14:07:12','2014-12-05 22:07:12','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1480',0,'class','',0),(1481,5,'2014-12-05 14:18:22','2014-12-05 22:18:22','<h1>Tuesdays, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>March 31 – May 5, 2015<br />Cubberley Community Center, Palo Alto<br /></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 6 sessions (once a week for 6 weeks)<br /> <strong>Class dates:</strong> March 31, April 7, 14, 21, 28, and May 5<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (18 hours total instruction)<br /> <strong>Class size:</strong> 12 students maximum<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $329<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> <a title=\"Foundation 2\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-2/\">Foundation 2</a></p>','F3 - Foundation 3 in PA with Kasey Klemm (#03-2058)','','publish','open','open','','f3-foundation-3-in-pa-with-kasey-klemm-03-2058','','','2014-12-05 14:19:44','2014-12-05 22:19:44','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1481',0,'class','',0),(1482,5,'2014-12-05 14:40:27','2014-12-05 22:40:27','<h1>4-Week Studio Scene Work <br />Tuesdays, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>March 17 – April 7, 2015<br /></strong><strong>Studio 210, San Francisco (the Mission)</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 4 sessions (once a week for 4 weeks)<br /><strong>Class dates: </strong>March 17, 24, 31, and April 7<br /><strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (12 hours total)<br /><strong>Class size: </strong>10 students maximum<br /><strong>Tuition</strong>: $180<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong><a href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-3/\">Foundation 3</a></p>','SS - March Studio Scene Work - 210 with Dave Dennison (#03-2059)','','publish','open','open','','ss-march-studio-scene-work-210-with-dave-dennison-03-2059','','','2014-12-05 14:40:27','2014-12-05 22:40:27','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1482',0,'class','',0),(1485,5,'2014-12-09 14:45:21','2014-12-09 22:45:21','<h1>Games<br />Sunday, 2:30 - 5:30 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Sunday, January 4, 1015<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: One session<br /> <strong>Class date: </strong>January 4<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $45<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Foundation 2 and above</p>\r\n<p>This class will allow you to dip your toe into the endless stream that is improv games!  Through this introduction to games, you will begin to apply what you\'ve learned about improvisation so far to some fun and playful improvised games/scenes.  We will focus on how to play the games while still telling a good story and keeping up characters.  </p>','I - Games with Kimberly MacLean (#01-2031)','','draft','open','open','','i-games-with-kimberly-maclean-01-2031','','','2015-01-02 14:38:18','2015-01-02 22:38:18','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1485',0,'class','',0),(1486,5,'2014-12-09 14:46:31','2014-12-09 22:46:31','<h1>Games!<br />Thursdays, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Thursdays December 3 and December 10<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: Two sessions; Thursdays December 3 (Chris Sams) and December 10 (John Remak)<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $90<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Foundation 3 and above</p>\r\n<p>Games, games games! Games in improv give us a chance to play with the tempo/pace of scenes and increase our ranges emotionally, narratively, and physically.  They help us take greater risks and learn to fail more gracefully.   </p>\r\n<div>In this two-week class, you\'ll play a huge assortment of fun improv performance games.  This class is both a great introduction to the classic canon of improv games and a nice refresher for the seasoned gamers out there. \r\n<div><br />Chris Sams and John Remak, masters of improv game-play will lead you through the cannon of BATS Improv games - the old stand-bys and new favorites that never fail to surprise and delight our audiences! Get the ins and outs, tips and tricks of dozens of classic improv games, including justification games and verbal restrictions.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','I - Games with Chris and John (#15-12-2214)','','publish','open','open','','i-games-with-kimberly-maclean-01-2031-2','','','2015-10-13 17:38:27','2015-10-14 00:38:27','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1486',0,'class','',0),(1494,4,'2014-12-10 23:37:42','2014-12-11 07:37:42','','awards2014','','inherit','open','open','','awards2014','','','2014-12-10 23:37:42','2014-12-11 07:37:42','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/awards2014.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1496,4,'2014-12-11 01:07:17','2014-12-11 09:07:17','<p>Welcome to BATS Improv, San Francisco\'s most highly acclaimed and longest-running improv company and school.</p>\r\n<p>Feed your imagination. Be surprised. Bust a gut.</p>\r\n<p>Join us this weekend and experience the one-of-a-kind blend of theatre, comedy, and spontaneity that is BATS Improv.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"about-us\">Learn more about BATS » </a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"shows\"> <img src=\"wp-content/themes/responsive/core/images/show-schedule-button.png\" alt=\"\" /> </a></p>','Welcome to BATS Improv - Dec. 2014','','publish','closed','closed','','welcome-to-bats-improv-dec-2014','','','2014-12-11 01