t is and have to make it up as you go. If that idea makes you nervous and excited, then this week is for you! Invite your family and friends to watch you perform on the last day. Discount available for enrolling in both sessions 1 and 2.</p>','Youth Summer 2015 - Youth improv (middle school) with Laura & Kim (session 1)','','publish','open','open','','youth-summer-2015-youth-all-stars-with-bats-coaches-session-1','','','2015-05-21 16:47:25','2015-05-21 23:47:25','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1539',0,'class','',0),(1540,5,'2014-12-22 12:44:53','2014-12-22 20:44:53','<h1>Summer Camp: Youth Improv (Middle School), Session 2<br /> 5 Days; July 6 – July 10<br /> Mon – Fri,  9:00 AM – 2:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Ages 11-13, rising 6-8 graders<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Mon-Fri, July 6 - July 10<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><em><strong>Performance on Friday, July 10 at 12:00 PM</strong></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Class Time/Dates:</strong> 9am-2pm, Monday-Friday<br /> <strong>Class size:</strong> 16 students maximum<br /> <strong>Class length:</strong> 5 hours per day (25 hours total instruction)<br /> <strong>Tuition: </strong>$299</p>\r\n<p>Come learn the art of improvisation. Practice your acting, storytelling and comedy skills by playing improv games on stage. Get ready to act in plays where you have no clue what your part is and have to make it up as you go. If that idea makes you nervous and excited, then this week is for you! Invite your family and friends to watch you perform on the last day. Discount available for enrolling in both sessions 1 and 2.</p>','Youth Summer 2015 - Youth Improv (middle school) with Laura & Chris (session 2)','','publish','open','open','','youth-summer-2015-youth-all-stars-with-bats-coaches-session-2','','','2015-05-26 12:15:07','2015-05-26 19:15:07','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1540',0,'class','',0),(1541,5,'2014-12-22 12:51:38','2014-12-22 20:51:38','<h1>Summer Camp: Teen Improv Ensemble, Session 1 <br /> 5 Days; July 13 - July 17<br /> Mon – Fri,  9:00 AM – 4:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Ages 14-17<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Mon-Fri, July 13 - July 17<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco<br /> Tuition: $319</strong></p>\r\n<p>Come learn the art of improvisation with other creative teenagers.  Call the Bayfront Theater your home for a week as you practice your acting, storytelling and comedy skills by playing improv games on stage. Make it up, think on your feet, come up with wild stories and characters and learn to play well with others in creating improvised theater! Invite your family and friends to watch you perform on the last day. Discount available for enrolling in both sessions.</p>','Youth Summer 2015 - Teen Summer School: Improv Ensemble Session 1 with Laura & Chris','','publish','open','open','','youth-summer-2015-teen-summer-school-improv-ensemble-session-1-with-bats-coaches','','','2015-07-01 15:52:26','2015-07-01 22:52:26','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1541',0,'class','',0),(1542,5,'2014-12-22 12:55:48','2014-12-22 20:55:48','<h1>Summer Camp: Teen Improv Ensemble, Session 2 <br /> 5 Days; July 20 - July 24<br /> Mon – Fri,  9:00 AM – 4:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Ages 14-17 (rising high school students)<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Mon-Fri, July 20 - July 24<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco<br /> Tuition: $319</strong></p>\r\n<p>Come learn the art of improvisation with other creative teenagers.  Call the Bayfront Theater your home for a week as you practice your acting, storytelling and comedy skills by playing improv games on stage. Make it up, think on your feet, come up with wild stories and characters and learn to play well with others in creating improvised theater! Invite your family and friends to watch you perform on the last day. Discount available for enrolling in both sessions.</p>','Youth Summer 2015 - Teen Summer School: Improv Ensemble Session 2 with BATS Coaches','','publish','open','open','','youth-summer-2015-teen-summer-school-improv-ensemble-session-2-with-bats-coaches','','','2015-05-12 14:13:52','2015-05-12 21:13:52','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1542',0,'class','',0),(1543,5,'2014-12-22 13:03:43','2014-12-22 21:03:43','<h1>Summer Camp: Advanced Teen Improv Ensemble <br /> 5 Days; July 20 - July 24<br /> Mon – Fri,  9:00 AM – 4:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Ages 14-17 (rising high school students)<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Mon-Fri, July 20 - July 24<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco<br /> Tuition: $319</strong></p>\r\n<p>Do you already have experience taking improv classes, on an improv team at your school, or performing improvisation? Are you adept at saying “Yes and,” have the skills to build a positive platform, along with telling stories and playing characters? Do you have some knowledge of improv games and feel comfortable doing an open scene?</p>\r\n<p>This class will be building on previous improv experience. We’ll be going for a more intense experience and playing around with open scenes and long form (along with shaking things up with performance games). This is <strong>not</strong> a class for beginners. We will hit the ground running, building an ensemble in a positive encouraging environment where we will laugh, feel free to fail and succeed, and have a wonderful time together, culminating in a performance.</p>','Youth Summer 2015 - Teen Summer School: Advanced Improv Ensemble with Laura Derry (07-2069(','','publish','open','open','','youth-summer-2015-teen-summer-school-advanced-improv-ensemble-with-laura-derry-07-2069','','','2015-03-25 14:59:23','2015-03-25 21:59:23','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1543',0,'class','',0),(1545,5,'2014-12-22 17:05:01','2014-12-23 01:05:01','<h1>Drop-In Improv<br />Sunday, 6:00 PM - 8:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Sunday, January 4th<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: One session<b