 lives. Ask anyone who\'s taken a BATS class, performed on our stage or seen our shows. That core belief drives our key ambitions:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Open the improv experience to all audiences by keeping our show and class prices accessible </li>\r\n<li>Deliver performing arts education programs in public schools </li>\r\n<li>Offer improv classes to people living with chronic illness</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Over the last 27 years, BATS Improv has earned a loyal base of audience members and students that drives our earned income to more than 70 percent of our operating budget. However, we must rely on the generosity of financial supporters like you to subsidize the balance of our programming and community outreach.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again! </p>\r\n<p>If you would prefer to donate by check (payable to \"BATS Improv\"), please send to:<br /> <br />BATS Improv<br />Fort Mason Center<br /> 2 Marina Blvd, Bldg. B<br /> San Francisco, California 94123<br /> <br />If you have any questions, please call our office at (415) 474-6776 and ask for Chet!</p>\r\n<hr />','THANK YOU!','','publish','open','closed','','thank-you-giving','','','2014-12-29 17:55:29','2014-12-30 01:55:29','',15,'http://www.improv.org/?page_id=1572',2,'page','',0),(1574,4,'2014-12-30 05:40:46','2014-12-30 13:40:46','','NYE','','inherit','open','open','','nye-2','','','2014-12-30 05:40:46','2014-12-30 13:40:46','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/NYE.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1576,4,'2015-01-01 08:36:15','2015-01-01 16:36:15','','theatresports-web313','','inherit','open','open','','theatresports-web313','','','2015-01-01 08:36:15','2015-01-01 16:36:15','',1563,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/theatresports-web313.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1577,4,'2015-01-01 09:04:09','2015-01-01 17:04:09','<p>Improbable situations, larger than life characters, fill the fast paced world of this classic comedic genre.  Each night a new set of spirited characters will be c