ion)<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $299<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> <a title=\"Foundation 1\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-1/\">Foundation 1</a></p>','F2 - Foundation 2 with Laura Derry  (#15-03-2117)','','publish','open','open','','f2-foundation-2-with-laura-derry-15-03-2117','','','2015-03-05 14:36:05','2015-03-05 22:36:05','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1688',0,'class','',0),(1689,5,'2015-03-05 15:59:12','2015-03-05 23:59:12','<h1>Performance Workshop 1<br />Tuesdays, 7:00 PM - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>May 12 - June 30, 2015<br />Cubberley Community Center, Palo Alto<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Schedule:</strong> 8 sessions (once a week for 8 weeks), 2 performances<br /><strong>Class Time/Dates: </strong>7-10pm on Tuesdays May 12, 19, 26, June 2, 9, 16, 23, and 30<br /><strong>Performances: </strong>2 performances - one open workshop at the Cubberley Community Center on Tuesday, June 23rd, and one performance at the Bayfront Theater in SF on Sunday, June 28<br /><strong>Class size:</strong> 10 students maximum <strong><br />Class length: </strong>3 hours (24 hours total of instruction)<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong>Studio Scene Work<em><br /> </em></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">This 8-week workshop prepares you for your first performance in front of an audience by breaking down and covering these different core elements of performance:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Stage skills</li>\r\n<li>Shape of show</li>\r\n<li>Games (setting up, introducing, and playing)</li>\r\n<li>Scenes (setting up, starting, and ending)</li>\r\n<li>Audience interaction</li>\r\n<li>Ensemble-building</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You’ll learn new games and explore the balance between games and scenes for a well-crafted show.  The Workshop includes two performances: one is an open workshop for friends and guests and the second is a full show with a paid audience.</p>','Performance - Performance Workshop 1 in PA with John Remak (#15-04-2095)','','draft','open','open','','performance-performance-workshop-1-in-pa-with-john-remak-15-04-2095','','','2015-05-04 14:28:20','2015-05-04 21:28:20','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1689',0,'class','',0),(1690,5,'2015-03-05 16:11:31','2015-03-06 00:11:31','<h1>Performance Workshop 2 - Theatresports<br />Saturdays, 11:00 AM - 2:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>April 25 - June 27, 2015<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Schedule:</strong> 8 sessions (once a week for 8 weeks), 2 performances<br /><strong>Class Time/Dates: </strong>11am - 2pm on Saturdays April 25, May 2, 9, 16 (skipping May 23 for Memorial Day weekend), 30, June 6, 13, (skipping June 20), and 27<br /><strong>Performances: </strong>Two performances: one open workshop during class on Tuesday, May 30th and one performance on Sunday, June 14th <br /><strong>Class size:</strong> 12 students maximum <strong><br />Class length: </strong>3 hours (24 hours total of instruction)<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong>Performance Workshop 1 or coach/dean approval. Contact regina@improv.org with any eligibility questions.<em><br /> </em></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0pt;\">This workshop is the next level in our performing series to prepare improvisers for performance.  This unique Johnstonian format, the ever-challenging and ever-entertaining Theatresports, helps you learn and practice multiple skills to provide a confident, fun, and entertaining performance.  </p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0pt;\">In this class, we\'ll develop ensemble, learning how best to interact with teammates, the opposing team, the judges, and the audience.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0pt;\">We\'ll also explore the logistics of learning, preparing, and playing Theatresports: creating team themes/personas, issuing challenges, learning new performance games, and adapting on the fly for the utmost variety  and interesting shape of show.</p>','Performance - Performance Workshop 2 (TS) with Laura Derry (#15-04-2096)','','publish','open','open','','performance-performance-workshop-2-ts-with-laura-derry-15-04-2096','','','2015-03-16 11:51:11','2015-03-16 18:51:11','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1690',0,'class','',0),(1691,4,'2015-03-06 16:24:24','2015-03-07 00:24:24','','Email-logo-huffington','','inherit','open','open','','email-logo-huffington-2','','','2015-03-06 16:24:24','2015-03-07 00:24:24','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Email-logo-huffington.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1692,4,'2015-03-06 16:24:25','2015-03-07 00:24:25','','Farce-web313','','inherit','open','open','','farce-web313-2','','','2015-03-06 16:24:25','2015-03-07 00:24:25','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Farce-web313.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1693,4,'2015-03-06 16:24:25','2015-03-07 00:24:25','','signature-email1','','inherit','open','open','','signature-email1','','','2015-03-06 16:24:25','2015-03-07 00:24:25','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/signature-email1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1694,4,'2015-03-06 16:24:26','2015-03-07 00:24:26','','TS-web313','','inherit','open','open','','ts-web313','','','2015-03-06 16:24:26','2015-03-07 00:24:26','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/TS-web313.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1695,4,'2015-03-06 16:24:52','2015-03-07 00:24:52','','annex-600','','inherit','open','open','','annex-600','','','2015-03-06 16:24:52','2015-03-07 00:24:52','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/annex-600.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1696,4,'2015-03-06 16:24:53','2015-03-07 00:24:53','','Email-logo-huffington','','inherit','open','open','','email-logo-huffington-3','','','2015-03-06 16:24:53','2015-03-07 00:24:53','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Email-logo-huffington1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1697,4,'2015-03-06 16:24:54',