p><strong>April 8 – May 13, 2015</strong><br /><strong>Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 6 sessions <br /> <strong>Class Dates:</strong> April 8, 15, 22, 29, May 6, and 13<br /><strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (18 hours total instruction)<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $299<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> <a title=\"Foundation 1\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-1/\">Foundation 1</a></p>','F2 - Foundation 2 with Regina Saisi (#15-04-2120)','','publish','open','open','','f2-foundation-2-with-regina-saisi-15-03-2120','','','2015-03-25 17:04:37','2015-03-26 00:04:37','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1725',0,'class','',0),(1726,5,'2015-03-12 11:59:16','2015-03-12 18:59:16','<h1>Thursdays, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>April 9, 2015 - May 14, 2015</strong><br /><strong>Studio 210, San Francisco (the Mission)</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 6 sessions (once a week for 6 weeks)<br /> <strong>Class dates:</strong> April 9, 16, 23, 30, May 7, and 14<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (18 hours total instruction)<br /> <strong>Class</strong> <strong>size:</strong> 16 students maximum<br /> <strong>Tuition:</strong> $299</p>','F1 - Foundation 1 in the Mission, Chris Sams (#15-04-2119)','','publish','open','open','','f1-foundation-1-in-the-mission-chris-sams-15-04-2119','','','2015-03-12 11:59:16','2015-03-12 18:59:16','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1726',0,'class','',0),(1727,4,'2015-03-15 23:40:39','2015-03-16 06:40:39','<p>In Director’s Cut! improv directors do battle to bring their passion to life. To do so, they’ll need to get the work they want from their fellow improvisers by directing them – live in the moment. Actors can even be tossed out of a scene and replaced! If the director succeeds and creates a “hit,” you, the audience, can reward them with a star, but if they “flop,” you get to demand better by punishing them on the spot (no, really – a recent punishment required a director to give their cell number to the entire audience so that they could text him to shape up). This is not just theatre, it’s theatre with consequences</p>','Director\'s Cut!','','draft','open','open','','directors-cut','','','2015-08-20 12:41:39','2015-08-20 19:41:39','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=friday&#038;p=1727',6,'friday','',0),(1730,5,'2015-03-17 13:16:04','2015-03-17 20:16:04','<p><strong>Guest Coach</strong></p>\r\n<p>Basel Al-Naffouri began his theater journey at MIT where he took his first acting classes. While there, he performed in MIT\'s productions of \'Seven Menus\' and \'The Elephant, Your Majesty\'.</p>\r\n<p>After moving to the Bay Area, he was introduced to improv by taking his first class at BATS in 2005. Soon after, Basel was invited to perform with the BATS Sunday Players and was a founding member of Double Entendre and Out of Line. He has also produced, directed and acted in “Improvised Arabian Nights”, an improvised show in the style of “A Thousand and One Nights”.</p>\r\n<p>In addition to performing improvisational theater, Basel has appeared in numerous scripted shows. He played the role of Adnan in the Stanford Summer Theater production of Betrayed. Basel has also performed in Golden Thread’s ‘No Such Cold Thing’, which was featured in American Theater Magazine.</p>\r\n<p>Basel has taught improv workshops both locally and internationally. He had led trainings with organizations such as Google and Aswat, improv troupes like Double Entendre and Audible Clique and internationally at KAUST University in Saudi Arabia and Laban in Lebanon.</p>','Basel Al-Naffouri','','publish','open','open','','basel-al-naffouri','','','2015-03-17 13:20:07','2015-03-17 20:20:07','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=actors&#038;p=1730',6,'actors','',0),(1731,5,'2015-03-17 13:15:43','2015-03-17 20:15:43','','basel coach photo','','inherit','open','open','','basel-coach-photo','','','2015-03-17 13:15:43','2015-03-17 20:15:43','',1730,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/basel-coach-photo.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1733,5,'2015-03-17 13:27:01','2015-03-17 20:27:01','<p><strong>Guest Coach</strong></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"il\">Kristian</span> has been making things up since she was a little girl. Imagine her excitement when she took a class in 1997 and learned she could call it improv! Since then she\'s studied at ImprovWorks and BATS and has performed with Flash Family, Improvalicious and Fosse Posse. Now she performs with Secret Improv Society, is still making things up (like freestyle rapping) and loving every minute of it. </p>','Kristian Ruggieri','','publish','open','open','','kristian-ruggieri','','','2015-03-17 13:27:01','2015-03-17 20:27:01','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=actors&#038;p=1733',5,'actors','',0),(1734,5,'2015-03-17 13:23:12','2015-03-17 20:23:12','','Kristian Ruggieri','','inherit','open','open','','kristian-ruggieri','','','2015-03-17 13:23:12','2015-03-17 20:23:12','',1733,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Kristian-Ruggieri.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1735,5,'2015-03-17 14:03:54','2015-03-17 21:03:54','<h1>4-Week Studio Scene Work <br />Thursdays 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>April 2 – April 23, 2015<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 4 sessions (once a week for 4 weeks)<br /><strong>Class dates: </strong>April 2, 9, 16, and 23<br /><strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (12 hours total)<br /><strong>Class size: </strong>10 students maximum<br /><strong>Tuition</strong>: $180<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong><a href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-3/\">Foundation 3</a></p>','SS - Scene Work - FMC with John (#15-04-2121)','','publish','open','open','','ss-scene-work-fmc-with-john-15-04-2121','','','2015-03-17 14:03:54','2015-03-17 21:03:54','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1735',0,'class','',0),(1736,5,'2015-03-17 14:11:49','2015-03-17 21:11:49','<h1>Sundays, 11:00 AM - 2:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>May 3, 2015 - June 14, 2015<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 6 sessions (once a week for 6 weeks)<br /> <strong>Class dates:</strong> May 3, 10, 17, 31, June 7, and 14 (skipping May 24 for Memorial Day weekend)<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (18 hours total instruction)<br /> <strong>Class</strong> <strong>size:</strong> 16 students maximum<br /> <strong>Tuition:</strong> $299</p>','F1 - Foundation 1 with Basel (#15-05-2097','','publish','open','open','','f1-foundation-1-with-basel-15-05-2097','','','2015-03-17 14:11:49','2015-03-17 21:11:49','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1736',0,'class','',0),(1737,5,'2015-03-17 14:37:22','2015-03-17 21:37:22','<h1>Improvised Rap with Guest Coach<br />Kristian Ruggieri<br />Saturdays 2:30 - 5:30 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>April 18 – May 9, 2015<br /></strong><strong>Bayfront Theater, San Francisco </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 4 sessions (once a week for 4 weeks)<br /><strong>Class dates: </strong>April 18, 25, May 2, and 9<br /><strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (12 hours total)<br /><strong>Class size: </strong>10 students maximum<br /><strong>Tuition</strong>: $180 <br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong><a href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-3/\">Foundation </a>2</p>\r\n<p>Afraid your rap is wack?  Learn to flow like a pro in this class!  We\'ll create rap personas and play games that focus on rhyming and telling stories to a beat before we start rapping solo, in groups and in head-to-head rap battles. By the end of class you\'ll have the skills, attitude and confidence you need to spit  mad rhymes, drop the mic, and exit stage left.</p>\r\n<div style=\"color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\"> </div>','Improvised Rap - Kristian Ruggieri (15-04-2122)','','publish','open','open','','improvised-rap-kristian-ruggieri-15-04-2122','','','2015-03-20 10:48:16','2015-03-20 17:48:16','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1737',0,'class','',0),(1739,5,'2015-03-19 12:29:01','2015-03-19 19:29:01','<h1>4-Week Studio Scene Work <br />Tuesdays, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>March 31 – April 21, 2015<br /></strong><strong>Cubberley Community Center, Palo Alto</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 4 sessions (once a week for 6 weeks)<br /><strong>Class dates: </strong>March 31, April 7, 14, and 21<br /><strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (12 hours total)<br /><strong>Class size: </strong>10 students maximum<br /><strong>Tuition</strong>: $219<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong><a href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-3/\">Foundation 3</a></p>','SS - 4-week Studio Scene Work in PA with Chris (#15-03-2123)','','draft','open','open','','ss-4-week-studio-scene-work-in-pa-with-chris-15-03-2123','','','2015-03-31 11:12:48','2015-03-31 18:12:48','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1739',0,'class','',0),(1742,4,'2015-03-20 12:35:13','2015-03-20 19:35:13','<p>Shakespeare didn’t write these stories — but you’ll think he did! Every night a completely new, feature-length story improvised in the style and language of The Bard.  Starting with a title chosen by you, the audience, our merry band of improvisers create a rich night of improvised Shakespearean theatre. What are you waiting for? Get thee to the theater and experience the magic that is BATS\' Improvised Shakespeare.</p>','Improvised Shakespeare','','draft','open','open','','shakes2015','','','2015-08-20 20:59:46','2015-08-21 03:59:46','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=saturday&#038;p=1742',6,'saturday','',0),(1750,4,'2015-03-21 14:25:36','2015-03-21 21:25:36','<p>Our newest show is back by popular demand! Strike it rich with this fast-paced night of improvised scenes as we leave it all up to chance as randomized slot machine reels choose key variables for each scene. Nobody knows what\'s coming next in this thrill ride of an improv show.  Randomized variables for scenes include: the starting players, the style <em>(genre/time period)</em>, locations, and single words.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Come early for your chance to win during the show!</strong></span><br />Come early and participate in pre-show festivities where we\'ll be collecting all of the suggestions that will be used throughout the night.  If your suggestion comes up during a \"Jackpot!\" round, you\'ll win a prize!</p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"color: #d9541e;\"><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Group Tickets\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/groups/\"><strong>Group tickets</strong> start at just $14 each!</a><br /><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Gift Certificates\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/gift-certificates/\">You can also give this show as a gift with a </a><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Gift Certificates\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/gift-certificates/\"><strong>BATS Gift Certific</strong><strong>ate</strong>.</a> </span></em></p>','Jackpot!','','draft','open','open','','jackpot','','','2015-09-27 01:47:39','2015-09-27 08:47:39','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=friday&#038;p=1750',5,'friday','',0),(1751,4,'2015-03-21 14:24:57','2015-03-21 21:24:57','','web313-jackpot','','inherit','open','open','','web313-jackpot','','','2015-03-21 14:24:57','2015-03-21 21:24:57','',1750,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/web313-jackpot.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1752,4,'2015-03-21 15:19:17','2015-03-21 22:19:17','<p>Theatresports is a fast-paced, exciting, and highly interactive night of improvised theatre competition, complete with Olympic-style judges. Each night two teams of <a title=\"Company Members &amp; Coaches\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/company-members-coaches/\" target=\"_blank\">BATS Company members</a> face off by performing completely improvised scenes, songs, and games – all inspired by your suggestions. Expect lots of variety and lots of audience interaction in every Theatresports show.  </p>\r\n<p>In our King of the Hill tournament, the winning team returns each week to face a new challenger.  The winner of the final match on July 24 will be declared the tournament Champions and will advance to represent BATS in our annual grudge match against LA during our Summer Improv Festival in August.</p>','Championship Match','','draft','open','open','','theatresportstradeking-of-the-hill','','','2015-07-25 00:31:19','2015-07-25 07:31:19','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=friday&#038;p=1752',3,'friday','',0),(1753,4,'2015-03-21 15:19:11','2015-03-21 22:19:11','','web313-king-hill','','inherit','open','open','','web313-king-hill','','','2015-03-21 15:19:11','2015-03-21 22:19:11','',1752,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/web313-king-hill.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1754,4,'2015-03-22 06:03:28','2015-03-22 13:03:28','<p>Enter a world where people are more beautiful, sex is a lethal weapon, comas are common, and your evil twin just might be your brother’s husband’s wife… dun-dun-dun!</p>\r\n<p>You\'ll help us create our idyllic fictional town filled with passionate characters who are entangled in relationships,  jam packed with moral and emotional conflicts, and who love to throw drinks, slap faces (and buy shoulder pads). </p>\r\n<p>This is our first-ever feature length Soap Opera and, as always, everything will be improvised live on the spot and inspired by your suggestions!</p>','Improvised Soap Opera','','draft','open','open','','improvised-soap-opera','','','2015-08-20 20:59:36','2015-08-21 03:59:36','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=saturday&#038;p=1754',5,'saturday','',0),(1755,4,'2015-03-22 05:59:44','2015-03-22 12:59:44','','web313-soap','','inherit','open','open','','web313-soap','','','2015-03-22 05:59:44','2015-03-22 12:59:44','',1754,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/web313-soap.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1756,4,'2015-03-22 06:57:16','2015-03-22 13:57:16','<p>For <strong>three nights only</strong> in July, we\'re celebrating summer with our most ambitious improvised musical(s) ever.  Each night your suggestions will inspire three unique and distinct musical stories that will play out simultaneously in this one-of-a-kind musical triptych!</p>','Summer Musical Triptych','','draft','closed','open','','summer-musical','','','2015-07-26 01:41:19','2015-07-26 08:41:19','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=saturday&#038;p=1756',4,'saturday','',0),(1757,4,'2015-03-22 06:56:28','2015-03-22 13:56:28','','web313-Summer','','inherit','open','open','','web313-summer','','','2015-03-22 06:56:28','2015-03-22 13:56:28','',1756,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/web313-Summer.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1758,4,'2015-03-22 07:01:16','2015-03-22 14:01:16','','web313-king-hill','','inherit','open','open','','web313-king-hill-2','','','2015-03-22 07:01:16','2015-03-22 14:01:16','',1752,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/web313-king-hill1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1759,4,'2015-03-22 07:01:59','2015-03-22 14:01:59','','web313-king-hill','','inherit','open','open','','web313-king-hill-3','','','2015-03-22 07:01:59','2015-03-22 14:01:59','',1752,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/web313-king-hill2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1761,4,'2015-03-22 07:07:22','2015-03-22 14:07:22','','web313-shakes-logo','','inherit','open','open','','web313-shakes-logo-2','','','2015-03-22 07:07:22','2015-03-22 14:07:22','',1742,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/web313-shakes-logo1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1763,4,'2015-03-22 12:20:12','2015-03-22 19:20:12','','web313-Summer','','inherit','open','open','','web313-summer-2','','','2015-03-22 12:20:12','2015-03-22 19:20:12','',1756,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/web313-Summer1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1764,4,'2015-03-22 17:36:06','2015-03-23 00:36:06','','web313-Summer','','inherit','open','open','','web313-summer-3','','','2015-03-22 17:36:06','2015-03-23 00:36:06','',1756,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/web313-Summer2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1767,4,'2015-03-23 17:34:07','2015-03-24 00:34:07','','zoe3-new','','inherit','open','open','','zoe3-new','','','2015-03-23 17:34:07','2015-03-24 00:34:07','',31,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/zoe3-new.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1769,4,'2015-03-23 19:17:44','2015-03-24 02:17:44','','web313-king-hill','','inherit','open','open','','web313-king-hill-4','','','2015-03-23 19:17:44','2015-03-24 02:17:44','',1752,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/web313-king-hill3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1771,5,'2015-03-24 11:30:14','2015-03-24 18:30:14','<h1>Summer Camp: Kids Improv <br />(4th and 5th Grade)<br /> 5 Days; July 13 – July 17<br /> Mon – Fri,  9:00 AM – 2:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Ages 9-10 (rising 4th and 5th graders)<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Mon-Fri, July 13 - July 17<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><em><strong>Open class performance on Friday, July 17 at 1:00 PM</strong></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Class Time/Dates:</strong> 9am-2pm, Monday-Friday<br /> <strong>Class size:</strong> 16 students maximum<br /> <strong>Class length:</strong> 5 hours per day (25 hours total instruction)<br /> <strong>Tuition: </strong>$299</p>\r\n<p>Come learn the art of improvisation! Practice your acting, storytelling and comedy skills by playing improv games on stage. Get ready to act in plays where you have no clue what your part is and have to make it up as you go. If that idea makes you nervous and excited, then this week is for you! Invite your family and friends to watch you perform on the last day. </p>','Youth Summer 2015 - 4th & 5th Grade with Chris & Mona (15-07-2131_','','draft','open','open','','youth-summer-2015-4th-5th-grade-with-chris-mona-15-07-2131_','','','2015-06-29 12:50:10','2015-06-29 19:50:10','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1771',0,'class','',0),(1776,4,'2015-03-26 13:16:26','2015-03-26 20:16:26','','Shakespeareimgfornewsletter','','inherit','open','open','','shakespeareimgfornewsletter-3','','','2015-03-26 13:16:26','2015-03-26 20:16:26','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Shakespeareimgfornewsletter2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1777,4,'2015-03-26 13:26:59','2015-03-26 20:26:59','','OTGimagefornewsletter','','inherit','open','open','','otgimagefornewsletter','','','2015-03-26 13:26:59','2015-03-26 20:26:59','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/OTGimagefornewsletter.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1779,5,'2015-03-27 11:48:11','2015-03-27 18:48:11','<h1>Advanced Shakespeare Intensive</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Bayfront Theater, San Francisco<br /></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule: </strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Wed, August 5, 7-10pm </li>\r\n<li>Thurs, August 6, 7-10pm</li>\r\n<li>Fri, August 7, 10am-5pm (with a 1-hour lunch break from 1-2pm)</li>\r\n<li>Sat, August 8, 10am-5pm (with a 1-hour lunch break from 1-2pm)</li>\r\n<li>Sun, August 9, 10am-1pm </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Performances: Two performances on Sunday, August 9, 2-4pm and 5-7pm  </p>\r\n<p><strong>Class size: </strong>12 students maximum<br /><strong>Class hours:</strong> 21 hours of instruction total, see above schedule for a breakdown of hours each day<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong> Prior improv training and performance experience, including long-form experience. Please contact Regina Saisi, Dean, with any questions about prerequisites or your eligibility at regina@improv.org or 415-474-6776.<br /> </p>\r\n<p>The Advanced Shakespeare Intensive will take a deep dive into the magical world of Improvised Shakespeare.  It is intended for students who already have a basic understanding and comfort with Improvised Shakespeare and are looking to play more fully with the theatricality, emotions, playfulness and poetry of the Bard. </p>\r\n<p>Having covered basics of language, storytelling and themes in basic Improvised Shakespeare, this workshop will go deeper, encouraging students to push past their comfort zones, access new shades of character, emotionality, and energetic tones to create a full and magical story.  We\'ll cover topics of theatrical stage picture and movement, committed emotion, truthful acting, character variety, and connected storytelling in a cohesive ensemble.  </p>\r\n<p>Priority will be given to those who have completed an Improvised Shakespeare Workshop. <br /> </p>\r\n<p><strong>**Register before June 1st to take advantage of our early registration rate of $419. After June 1st class price increases to $449.**</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Summer 2015 - Advanced Shakes 15-08-2124','','publish','open','open','','summer-2015-advanced-shakes-15-08-2124','','','2015-05-19 17:12:05','2015-05-20 00:12:05','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1779',0,'class','',0),(1781,5,'2015-03-27 11:56:57','2015-03-27 18:56:57','<h1>Stage Combat and Intimacy</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<div><strong>Schedule:</strong> Monday, August 10, 10am-6pm (with a 1-hour lunch break from 1:30-2:30pm)</div>\r\n<div><strong>Class size:</strong> 12 students maximum<br /><strong>Class hours:</strong> 7 hours of instruction total<br />Prerequisite:  Foundation 3 and above. Please contact Regina Saisi, Dean, with any questions about prerequisites or your eligibility at regina@improv.org or 415-474-6776.<br /> </div>\r\n<p>Two of the most powerful yet challenging areas in Improvisation are Stage Combat and Intimacy.  Since we are the director, actor and choreographer simultaneously when improvising, our protective instincts can make us back away from the very moments that would knock the socks off the audience.  Practice pushing into these areas with confidence, awareness and skill.  What makes a gun fight work?  What types of romantic scenes have the audience on the edge of their seat?  This class provides powerful tools for making Improvisation a more commanding form of art. <br /> </p>\r\n<div><strong>**Register before June 1st to take advantage of our early registration rate of $129. After June 1st class price increases to $149.**</strong></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Summer 2015 - Combat & Intimacy 15-08-2127','','publish','open','open','','summer-2015-combat-intimacy-15-08-2127','','','2015-03-27 12:09:27','2015-03-27 19:09:27','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1781',0,'class','',0),(1782,5,'2015-03-27 11:59:51','2015-03-27 18:59:51','<h1>Straight Man/Clowning</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>Schedule:</strong> Tuesday, August 11, 10am-6pm (with a 1-hour lunch break from 1:30-2:30pm)</div>\r\n<div><strong>Class size:</strong> 12 students maximum<br /><strong>Class hours:</strong> 7 hours of instruction total<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong> Foundation 3 and above. Please contact Regina Saisi, Dean, with any questions about prerequisites or your eligibility at regina@improv.org or 415-474-6776.<br /> <br />This is a class that will delve deeper into games, scenes and long-form using advanced acting techniques and awareness of roles to bring out the best comic scene possible.   We\'ll study traditional Straight Man/Clown techniques, comedic character work and use of physical space to create comic scenes with heart, depth and power.   We\'ll also study the balance between Comedy and Drama and how to offset one with the other to enhance the depth of any scene.</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><strong>**Register before June 1st to take advantage of our early registration rate of $129. After June 1st class price increases to $149.**</strong></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Summer 2015 - Straight/Clown 15-08-2128','','publish','open','open','','summer-2015-straightclown-15-08-2128','','','2015-03-27 12:09:06','2015-03-27 19:09:06','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1782',0,'class','',0),(1783,5,'2015-03-27 12:03:53','2015-03-27 19:03:53','<h1>Song Improv 101</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>Schedule: </strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Thurs, August 13, 7-10pm</li>\r\n<li>Fri, August 14, 10am-5pm (with a 1-hour lunch break from 1-2pm)</li>\r\n<li>Sat, August 15, 10am-5pm (with a 1-hour lunch break from 1-2pm)</li>\r\n<li>Sun, August 16, 10am-1pm</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Performance Showcase:</strong> Sunday, August 16, 2-4pm  <br /><strong>Class size: </strong>12 students maximum<br /><strong>Class hours:</strong> 18 hours of instruction total, see above schedule for a breakdown of hours each day<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong> Foundation 1 or equivalent. Please contact Regina Saisi, Dean, with any questions about prerequisites or your eligibility at regina@improv.org or 415-474-6776.<br /><br /></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>This 3-day intensive workshop is designed to teach the essential principles of how to create improvised solos, duets, and choruses. We break down the challenge of singing a song into its basics - breathing, ear and voice training, rhyme and rhythm exercises. </p>\r\n<p>This is the perfect class for anyone interested in learning about the different elements of improvised songs. No previous singing training, performance, or experience is needed! All that\'s required is a healthy sense of curiosity and the knowledge of your improv basics!</p>\r\n<p>It\'s also the perfect class for people who are scared of ANY kind of singing, whether improvised or not. Take it and surprise yourself. </p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><strong>**Register before June 1st to take advantage of our early registration rate of $359. After June 1st class price increases to $389.**</strong></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Summer 2015 - Song 101 15-08-2125','','publish','open','open','','summer-2015-song-101-15-08-2125','','','2015-03-27 12:04:57','2015-03-27 19:04:57','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1783',0,'class','',0),(1784,5,'2015-03-27 12:08:19','2015-03-27 19:08:19','<h1>45-Minute Cinematic Long Form</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>Schedule:</strong> 10am-5pm (with a 1-hour lunch break from 1-2pm) daily, <br />Tuesday through Saturday, August 18-22<br /><strong>Performances: </strong>Three 45-minute performances on Sunday, August 23, 3-6pm</div>\r\n<div><strong>Class size:</strong> 12 students maximum<br /><strong>Class hours: </strong>6 hours of instruction daily for 5 days for a total of 30 hours <br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong> Prior improv training and performance experience required. Please contact Regina Saisi, Dean, with any questions about prerequisites or your eligibility at regina@improv.org or 415-474-6776.</div>\r\n<div>Learn and experience single story long form improv at its purest and most exciting! Four players get a title from the audience and collaboratively create a \"movie\" utilizing filmic techniques to progress the narrative. There is no predetermined genre and no mid-show break to catch your breath. This five day intensive training will focus on the skills necessary to be prepared for the final day\'s performances, including: acting, character, ensemble and narrative.</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><strong>**Register before June 1st to take advantage of our early registration rate of $579. After June 1st class price increases to $599.**</strong></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Summer 2015 - Cine Long Form 15-08-2126','','publish','open','open','','summer-2015-cine-long-form-15-08-2126','','','2015-03-27 13:04:30','2015-03-27 20:04:30','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1784',0,'class','',0),(1785,5,'2015-03-27 12:18:13','2015-03-27 19:18:13','<h1>Masks</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>Schedule: </strong><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Mon, August 24, 10am-6pm (with a 1-hour lunch break from 1:3-2:30pm) </li>\r\n<li>Tues, August 25, 10am-6pm (with a 1-hour lunch break from 1:3-2:30pm) </li>\r\n<li>Wed, August 26, 10am-6pm (with a 1-hour lunch break from 1:3-2:30pm) </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Performances: </strong>Wednesday, August 26, time TBD  </div>\r\n<div><strong>Class size:</strong> 12 students maximum<br /><strong>Class hours:</strong> 21 hours of instruction total, see above schedule for a breakdown of hours each day<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong> Foundation 3 and above. Please contact Regina Saisi, Dean, with any questions about prerequisites or your eligibility at regina@improv.org or 415-474-6776.<br /> </div>\r\n<p>How do masks transform the theatrical space?  How do masks transform the performer?  How can we bring masks and mask work into improv?  This class will explore the mysterious, powerful impact masks can have on a performer and his or her play.  No experience is necessary, just come with your face, ready to play.  William Hall will bring his extensive collection of masks to this workshop and will lead you through lots of work on your feet, so you can experience first-hand what a difference a mask makes.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><strong>**Register before June 1st to take advantage of our early registration rate of $419. After June 1st class price increases to $449.**</strong></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Summer 2015 - Masks 15-08-2129','','publish','open','open','','summer-2015-masks-15-08-2129','','','2015-03-27 12:18:13','2015-03-27 19:18:13','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1785',0,'class','',0),(1786,5,'2015-03-27 12:33:32','2015-03-27 19:33:32','<h1>Super Scene</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>Schedule: </strong><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Thurs, August 27, 10am-5pm (with a 1-hour lunch break from 1-2pm) </li>\r\n<li>Fri, August 28, 10am-5pm (with a 1-hour lunch break from 1-2pm)</li>\r\n<li>Sat, August 29, 10am-5pm (with a 1-hour lunch break from 1-2pm)</li>\r\n<li>Sun, August 30, 10am-1pm </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Performances: </strong>Two performances on Sunday, August 30, 2-3:30pm and 4-5:30pm  </div>\r\n<div><strong>Class size: </strong>10 students maximum<br /><strong>Class hours: </strong>21 hours of instruction total, see above schedule for a breakdown of hours each day<br /><strong>Prerequisite:  </strong>Prior improv training and performance experience, including long-form experience. Please contact Regina Saisi, Dean, with any questions about prerequisites or your eligibility at regina@improv.org or 415-474-6776.<br /><br />In this four day intensive with two performances, Rebecca Stockley, William Hall, Paul Killam, and Rebecca Poretsky guide the participants in mastery of the format Super Scene. The coaches share their vision and provide a variety of approaches to the skills required in Super Scene. Gain experience in identifying your vision, bringing it to life, and adapting to the realization of your creation. In this intensive, you will direct your peers, explore actor/director interactions, pitch stories, create great shape of show, and tell your story in 5 scenes. <br /><br />*Super Scene is a fun-filled format in which five directors with five separate visions or story styles direct scenes in rounds. After each round of scenes, the audience votes to select their favorites, and one by one, the stories are eliminated until only one remains. The surviving story concludes the show with the Super Scene.</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><strong>**Register before June 1st to take advantage of our early registration rate of $449. After June 1st class price increases to $479.**</strong></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Summer 2015 - Super Scene15-08-2126','','publish','open','open','','summer-2015-super-scene15-08-2126','','','2015-03-27 12:33:32','2015-03-27 19:33:32','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1786',0,'class','',0),(1790,4,'2015-03-29 22:46:23','2015-03-30 05:46:23','','directors-cut-2015','','inherit','open','open','','directors-cut-2015','','','2015-03-29 22:46:23','2015-03-30 05:46:23','',1727,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/directors-cut-2015.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1795,5,'2015-03-30 21:54:13','2015-03-31 04:54:13','<h1>4-Week Studio Scene Work <br />Tuesdays, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>June 9 – June 30, 2015<br /></strong><strong>Studio 210, San Francisco (the Mission)</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 4 sessions (once a week for 4 weeks)<br /><strong>Class dates: </strong>June 9, 16, 23, and 30<br /><strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (12 hours total)<br /><strong>Class size: </strong>10 students maximum<br /><strong>Tuition</strong>: $180<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong><a href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-3/\">Foundation 3</a></p>','SS - June Studio Scene Work - 210 with Regina (#15-06-2132)','','publish','open','open','','ss-june-studio-scene-work-210-with-regina-15-06-2132','','','2015-03-30 21:54:13','2015-03-31 04:54:13','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1795',0,'class','',0),(1796,4,'2015-03-30 22:13:42','2015-03-31 05:13:42','','To be announced','','draft','open','open','','to-be-announced','','','2015-03-30 22:14:39','2015-03-31 05:14:39','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=actors&#038;p=1796',4,'actors','',0),(1802,4,'2015-04-08 16:59:25','2015-04-08 23:59:25','','bring-group','','inherit','open','open','','bring-group','','','2015-04-08 16:59:25','2015-04-08 23:59:25','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/bring-group.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1803,7,'2015-04-10 14:39:52','2015-04-10 21:39:52','<h1>Tuesdays &amp; Thursdays, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>May 12, 2015 - May 28, 2015</strong><br /><strong>Studio 204, San Francisco (the Mission)</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 6 sessions (twice a week for 3 weeks)<br /> <strong>Class dates:</strong> May 12, 14, 19, 21, 26, 28<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (18 hours total instruction)<br /> <strong>Class</strong> <strong>size:</strong> 16 students maximum<br /> <strong>Tuition:</strong> $299</p>','F1 - Foundation 1 in the Mission, Jenny Rosen (#15-05-2132)','','publish','open','open','','f1-foundation-1-in-the-mission-jenny-rosen-15-05-2132','','','2015-04-10 14:41:14','2015-04-10 21:41:14','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1803',0,'class','',0),(1805,5,'2015-04-15 13:19:16','2015-04-15 20:19:16','<h1><a id=\"F1\"></a>3-Day Foundation 1 Intensive</h1>\r\n<p><strong>July 30  - August 1, 2015<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 3-day intensive<br /> <strong>Class dates:</strong> July 30, July 31, and August 1st, 10am-5pm daily<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 18 hours total instruction<br /> <strong>Class</strong> <strong>size:</strong> 16 students maximum</p>\r\n<p>Foundation 1 is our fun introduction to the joys and thrills of improvisation and the BATS-style of improvised theatre. This intensive covers all of the content of the 6-week Foundation 1 class over three days.</p>\r\n<p>Students learn improv concepts and vocabulary, practice new skills, and perform in a safe, friendly atmosphere. Through games and exercises, you\'ll play, explore, and experiment with creating characters and scenes, guided by our seasoned coaches. Foundation 1 is all about unleashing your innate skill. Are you human? Then you have all the experience necessary to excel!</p>\r\n<p><strong><br />**Register before June 1st to take advantage of our early registration rate of $299. After June 1st class price increases to $325.**</strong></p>','Summer 2015 - F1 Intensive - (#15-07-2133)','','publish','open','open','','summer-2015-f1-intensive-15-07-2133','','','2015-04-24 15:25:11','2015-04-24 22:25:11','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1805',0,'class','',0),(1806,5,'2015-04-15 13:46:31','2015-04-15 20:46:31','<h1>3-Day Foundation 2 Intensive</h1>\r\n<p><strong>August 3 - August 5, 2015<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 3-day intensive<br /> <strong>Class Dates:</strong> August 3, 4, and 5<br /><strong>Class length</strong>: 18 hours total instruction<br /><strong>Class size</strong>: 14 students maximum<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> <a title=\"Foundation 1\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-1/\">Foundation 1</a> or equivalent. Please contact Regina Saisi, Dean, with any questions about prerequisites or your eligibility at regina@improv.org or 415-474-6776.</p>\r\n<p>Foundation 2 focuses on refining your improv knowledge and skill set, reinforcing the concepts you learned in Foundation 1 through games, play, and exercises.</p>\r\n<p>This course covers all of the content of the 6-week Foundation 2 class over three days.</p>\r\n<p>While the emphasis is still on fun, course content also explores more conceptual and technical information and helps you build the skills you need to perform in front of an audience.</p>\r\n<p>Students in Foundation 2 are required to read one of the definitive texts on improv: <em>IMPRO</em> by Keith Johnstone. Johnstone invented Theatresports, one of the core improv formats we play at BATS. <a href=\"http://improbook.eventbrite.com/\">BATS sells the book for $25;</a> it is also available from a variety of retail outlets. When enrolling, please indicate whether or not you would like to purchase the book from BATS. If so, you can pay for it at time of registration and pick up their book on your first day of class.</p>\r\n<p>At the conclusion, everyone \"passes\" and can move on to Foundation 3, but you can also take Foundation 2 as many times as you would like.</p>\r\n<p><strong>**Register before June 1st to take advantage of our early registration rate of $299. After June 1st class price increases to $325.**</strong> </p>','Summer 2015 - 3-Day Foundation 2 Intensive  (#15-08-2134)','','publish','open','open','','summer-2015-3-day-foundation-2-intensive-15-08-2134','','','2015-04-24 14:10:58','2015-04-24 21:10:58','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1806',0,'class','',0),(1808,4,'2015-04-15 18:25:24','2015-04-16 01:25:24','','summer-at-bats','','inherit','open','open','','summer-at-bats','','','2015-04-15 18:25:24','2015-04-16 01:25:24','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/summer-at-bats.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1809,5,'2015-04-16 14:07:23','2015-04-16 21:07:23','<h1>Performance Workshop 3 - <br />Elements of Long Form<br />Wednesdays, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>April 29 - June 17, 2015<br />Cubberley Community Center, Palo Alto<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Schedule:</strong> 8 sessions; 2 performances<br /><strong>Class Time/Dates: </strong>7-10pm on Wednesdays<br />April 29, May 6, 13, 20, 27, June 3, 10, and 17<br /><strong>Performances: </strong>Two performances: Wednesday, June 10th, open class performance for friends and invited guests at Cubberley Community Center<br />Sunday, June 14th, time TBD, performance with a paid audience at the Bayfront Theater<br /><strong>Class size:</strong> 10 students maximum<br /><strong>Class length:</strong> 3 hours (24 hours total of instruction) <br /><strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Performance Workshops 1 and 2, or coach/dean approval. Please contact regina@improv.org with any eligibility questions.</p>\r\n<p>This 8-week workshop, the third in our Performance Series, prepares you for your first<br /> Long-Form performance in front of an audience by breaking down and covering these different core elements of performance: </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Taking your time and paying attention</li>\r\n<li>Narrative, and establishing a strong foundation</li>\r\n<li>Acting</li>\r\n<li>Improvising in genre</li>\r\n<li>Transitions between scenes</li>\r\n<li>Ensemble acting</li>\r\n<li>Building locations and maintaining a space object world</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>This class will qualify you to be considered for more advanced work as it will give you a grounding in the essential elements of Long-Form improvisation as BATS practices it.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Performance - Performance Workshop 3 (ELF) in PA with Laura (#15-04-2136)','','publish','open','open','','performance-performance-workshop-3-elf-in-pa-with-laura-15-04-2136','','','2015-04-16 14:08:27','2015-04-16 21:08:27','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1809',0,'class','',0),(1810,4,'2015-04-17 15:56:56','2015-04-17 22:56:56','','3fa-web313','','inherit','open','open','','3fa-web313','','','2015-04-17 15:56:56','2015-04-17 22:56:56','',898,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/3fa-web313.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1812,5,'2015-04-20 15:12:39','2015-04-20 22:12:39','<h1>Impro Intensive with Keith Johnstone</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Schedule: 9am-3pm, Thursday, Friday, and Saturday August 6, 7, and 8\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>9am-10am with Zoe Galvez</li>\r\n<li>10:15am-12:15pm with Keith Johnstone via Skype</li>\r\n<li>12:15-1pm, Lunch</li>\r\n<li>1-3pm with Kasey Klemm </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>Class size: 12 students maximum for the full program, and unlimited audience-only attendees for the 10:15am-12:15pm sessions with Keith Johnstone on all three days. <br />Class hours: 15 hours of instruction total for participants. 6 hours total for audience.<br />Prerequisite:  None<br /> </div>\r\n<p>Join legendary improv innovator <a href=\"http://www.keithjohnstone.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Keith Johnstone</a>, author of Impro and Improv for Storytellers and creator of Theatresports, Micetro, Gorilla Theatre, Life Game, and other performance formats, in this three-day improv exploration via Skype. </p>\r\n<p>Each day starts off with an hour of bonding and risk-taking, led by Zoe Galvez, preparing students for the next two hours improvising scenes on the BATS stage directed by Keith in Calgary, Canada via Skype. The day finishes off with a two-hour on-your-feet play session with Kasey Klemm. Kasey and Zoe, BATS coaches, are longtime students, colleagues and friends of Johnstone\'s.  </p>\r\n<p>Topics include story, status, spontaneity, acting, and comedy (but each day is influenced by student interests, so bring your questions!) This intensive is open to improvisers of all experience levels. </p>\r\n<p>Participants are limited to 12 students, but we are also offering unlimited spots for attendees to participate as audience members only during the Keith Johnstone portion of this class (2 hours each day, 10:15am-12:15pm for three days.) This is a unique opportunity to watch a master at work: directing and guiding scenes and speaking about both the philosophy and practice of improvisation. You\'re sure to find it educational and inspirational, whatever level of improviser you are and wherever you are in your training! Audience spots are available for $60 for all three days. </p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>**Register before June 1st to take advantage of our early registration rate of $319. After June 1st class price increases to $349.**\r\n<p> Audience spots are available for $60 for all three days.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"font-family: TimesNewRomanPSMT;\"><span style=\"font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: small;\"> </span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Summer 2015 - Keith Johnstone Skype! 15-08-2135','','publish','open','open','','summer-2015-keith-johnstone-skype-15-08-2135','','','2015-04-21 16:36:51','2015-04-21 23:36:51','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1812',0,'class','',0),(1814,5,'2015-04-20 15:09:12','2015-04-20 22:09:12','<p><strong>Guest Coach</strong></p>\r\n<div>Keith Johnstone is one of the few internationally recognized authorities in the field of improvisation, great chunks of which he created, including improvisation forms that include Theatresports™, Maestro Impro© </div>\r\n<div>(or Micetro©  Impro), Gorilla Theatre™, and The Life Game©. Keith has written two best selling books about his Theatre and Improvisation theories and practices, in addition to several plays and short stories.</div>\r\n<div><br />Theatresports™ is known worldwide. The Life Game©  was produced by London’s Improbable Theatre Co. (directed by Phelim McDermott). It toured Great Britain and the USA to great reviews.\r\n<div>His books Impro, and Impro For Storytellers, have been translated into many languages. His plays are produced world wide.</div>\r\n<p>Keith’s ideas about improvisation, behaviour and performance appeal to a wide variety of groups.  From Actors to Psychotherapists, Improvisation companies to Theatre Schools and Companies, Business and Management training specialists and Humanities Research Institutes, Universities and Film Production Companies have invited him to come to teach them about his ideas, and how they might apply them.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>He founded the Theatre Machine Improvisation group in England in the 1960’s, touring Europe and North America , was the Co-founder and Artistic Director of The Loose Moose Theatre Company in Calgary, Canada in the 1970’s, 80’s and 90’s. He founded<a href=\"http://www.theatresports.com/\" target=\"_blank\">The International Theatresports™ Institute</a> in 1998.</div>','Keith Johnstone','','publish','open','open','','keith-johnstone','','','2015-04-20 15:11:53','2015-04-20 22:11:53','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=actors&#038;p=1814',3,'actors','',0),(1815,5,'2015-04-20 15:08:57','2015-04-20 22:08:57','','Keith Johnstone','','inherit','open','open','','keith-johnstone','','','2015-04-20 15:08:57','2015-04-20 22:08:57','',1814,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Keith-Johnstone.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1819,5,'2015-04-24 14:16:54','2015-04-24 21:16:54','<h1>GameSceneGameScene! Intensive</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule:</strong> 2 day-long sessions <br /><strong>Class Time/Dates: </strong>Saturday, August 1, 10am-5pm with a 1-hour lunch break <br />Sunday, August 2, 1:30pm-4:30pm (one hour break, 4:30-5:30pm), then show preparation and performance, 5:30-7pm<br /><strong>Performance:</strong> One performance on Sunday, August 2nd, 6-7pm<br /><strong>Class size:</strong> 12 students maximum<br /><strong>Class length:</strong> 11.5 hours total of instruction and performance<br /><strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Foundation 3 and above. Please contact Regina Saisi, Dean, with any questions about prerequisites or your eligibility at regina@improv.org or 415-474-6776.<br /> </p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Here it is, gang! Your chance to build your scene skills AND learn a variety of solid improv games, THEN put it all together in one unforgettable performance.\r\n<div> </div>\r\n<div>In just two days we\'ll cover an astounding variety of improv skills, starting with the fundamentals of scene work and focusing on what it takes to instantly create short, yet meaningful and imaginative stories out of thin air.  <br /> </div>\r\n<div>We will also cover imaginative and dramatic stage techniques designed to enhance and enrich scenes, such as split focus, flashbacks, montages, and more.<br /> </div>\r\n<div>You\'ll also be introduced to many of the best tried and true improv games and learn the tips and tricks to perform them successfully. <br /> </div>\r\n<div>Finally, you\'ll build essential stage skills, including creating a playful ensemble and lively interaction with the audience.<br /> </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>This is sure to be a full and fun experience for any improviser interested in performing, and especially for those of you who are just starting to get on stage!</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>**Register before June 1st to take advantage of our early registration rate of $179. After June 1st class price increases to $199.**</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div> </div>\r\n<div> </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Summer 2015 - GameSceneGameScene! 15-08-2138','','publish','open','open','','summer-2015-gamescenegamescene-15-08-2138','','','2015-06-25 14:00:21','2015-06-25 21:00:21','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1819',0,'class','',0),(1820,4,'2015-04-27 02:09:24','2015-04-27 09:09:24','','web313-jackpot','','inherit','open','open','','web313-jackpot-2','','','2015-04-27 02:09:24','2015-04-27 09:09:24','',1750,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/web313-jackpot1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1822,4,'2015-04-27 02:21:14','2015-04-27 09:21:14','','web313-shakes-may','','inherit','open','open','','web313-shakes-may','','','2015-04-27 02:21:14','2015-04-27 09:21:14','',1742,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/web313-shakes-may.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1823,5,'2015-04-27 16:32:57','2015-04-27 23:32:57','<h1>Genre Intensive</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule:</strong> 4 sessions of 6 hours, each day focusing on a different genre. Sign up for as few or as many as you want. If you sign up for all 4 sessions, save $50! </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Monday, August 3rd - <strong>Film Noir</strong></li>\r\n<li>Monday, August 10th - <strong>Western</strong></li>\r\n<li>Monday, August 17th - <strong>Victorian/Jane Austen</strong></li>\r\n<li>Sunday, August 23rd - <strong>Tennessee Williams</strong><br /> </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Class Time/Dates:</strong> 2pm-9pm with a 45 minute dinner break from 5-5:45pm on Mondays August 3, 10, 17, and <em>Sunday</em>, August 23.<br /><strong>Performance:</strong> One performance on Monday, August 24th at 7pm. **Performance priority will be given to students who take all or most of these genre classes.**<br /><strong>Class size:</strong> 10 students maximum<br /><strong>Class length:</strong> 6 hours of instruction in each genre, 24 hours total of instruction for all four sessions.<br /><strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Studio Scene Work and above. Please contact Regina Saisi, Dean, with any questions about prerequisites or your eligibility at regina@improv.org or 415-474-6776.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>This workshop will explore the rich world of genres -- books, plays, and movies and how to adapt them to the improv stage.  Specifically, we will be looking at the requirements for creating improvised 45 minute long-form stories in these genres.   Rather than skimming the tops of many genres, this class will delve more deeply into one genre per day. Enroll in one, two, three, or four genres and meet each week to immerse in specific characters, locations and situations.  Before the workshop begins you will be asked to watch original source material in a given genre.  There will be a performance for students on <span data-term=\"goog_439117616\">Monday August 24th, 7pm</span>  with preference given to students who take all or most of the classes.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>**Register before June 1st to take advantage of our early registration rate of $119 per session. After June 1st class price increases to $129 per session. Save $50 by signing up for all 4 sessions for $426! **</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div> </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Summer 2015 - Genre Intensive 15-08-2137','','publish','open','open','','summer-2015-genre-intensive-15-08-2137','','','2015-08-03 15:06:54','2015-08-03 22:06:54','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1823',0,'class','',0),(1828,4,'2015-05-01 16:18:24','2015-05-01 23:18:24','','3FA-BATS-313x210-Bitches','','inherit','open','open','','3fa-bats-313x210-bitches','','','2015-05-01 16:18:24','2015-05-01 23:18:24','',898,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/3FA-BATS-313x210-Bitches.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1831,5,'2015-05-06 13:16:00','2015-05-06 20:16:00','<h1>Performance Workshop 1<br />Saturdays, 11:00 AM - 2:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>May 30 - July 25, 2015<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Schedule:</strong> 8 sessions (once a week for 8 weeks), 2 performances<br /><strong>Class Time/Dates: </strong>11am-2pm on Saturdays May 30, June 6, 13, 20, 27, July 11, 18, and 25 (skipping Saturday, July 4th)<br /><strong>Performances: </strong>2 performances, one open class performance, date TBD. One performance on the Bayfront Theater stage, Sunday, July 26th, time TBD.<br /><strong>Class size:</strong> 10 students maximum <strong><br />Class length: </strong>3 hours (24 hours total of instruction)<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong>Studio Scene Work<em><br /> </em></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">This 8-week workshop prepares you for your first performance in front of an audience by breaking down and covering these different core elements of performance:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Stage skills</li>\r\n<li>Shape of show</li>\r\n<li>Games (setting up, introducing, and playing)</li>\r\n<li>Scenes (setting up, starting, and ending)</li>\r\n<li>Audience interaction</li>\r\n<li>Ensemble-building</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>You’ll learn new games and explore the balance between games and scenes for a well-crafted show.  The Workshop includes two performances: one is an open workshop for friends and guests and the second is a full show with a paid audience.</p>','Performance - Performance Workshop 1 with John Remak (#15-05-2139)','','publish','open','open','','performance-performance-workshop-1-with-john-remak-15-05-2139','','','2015-05-06 13:16:00','2015-05-06 20:16:00','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1831',0,'class','',0),(1832,5,'2015-05-06 16:36:53','2015-05-06 23:36:53','<h1>Saturdays, 2:30 - 5:30 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>June 6 – July 18, 2015<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 6 sessions (once a week for 6 weeks, skipping one week for July 4th)<br /> <strong>Class dates:</strong> June 6, 13, 20, 27, July 11, and 18<br /><strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (18 hours total instruction)<br /> <strong>Class size:</strong> 12 students maximum<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $299<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> <a title=\"Foundation 2\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-2/\">Foundation 2</a></p>','F3 - Foundation 3 with Dave Dennison (#15-06-2140)','','publish','open','open','','f3-foundation-3-with-dave-dennison-15-06-2140','','','2015-05-06 16:36:53','2015-05-06 23:36:53','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1832',0,'class','',0),(1835,5,'2015-05-11 13:54:20','2015-05-11 20:54:20','<h1>Improv for Shy People in the Mission<br />Thursday, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>May 21, 2015<br />Studio 210, San Francisco (the Mission)</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: One session<br /> <strong>Class date:</strong> May 21st<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $45<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> None - everyone is welcome!<br /><br />Do you self-identify as shy or introverted? Are you unlikely to be the first to speak up in class or in a meeting? Do you find yourself overshadowed by your friends, family, or colleagues? Are you overwhelmed when you\'re in a big group of people? <br /><br />Signing up for an improv class may be the last thing on your mind if you consider yourself shy, but you\'d be surprised how safe and supportive the art form can be.  Focused on creating a comfortable and safe environment, Imp