rg/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/trip.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1943,5,'2015-07-09 15:20:53','2015-07-09 22:20:53','<h1>Improv for Shy People<br />Tuesday, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Tuesday, August 18th<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 1 session<br /> <strong>Class dates and time:</strong> 7-10pm on August 18th<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours <br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $45<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> None - everyone is welcome!</p>\r\n<p>Do you self-identify as shy or introverted? Are you unlikely to be the first to speak up in class or in a meeting? Do you find yourself overshadowed by your friends, family, or colleagues? Are you overwhelmed when you\'re in a big group of people? </p>\r\n<p>Signing up for an improv class may be the last thing on your mind if you consider yourself shy, but you\'d be surprised how safe and supportive the art form can be.  Focused on creating a comfortable and safe environment, Improv for Shy People introduces the basics of BATS-style improv in order to cultivate spontaneity, flexibility, and confidence.  Improv skills build trust and cooperation and tap into the imaginative and creative qualities that we all possess. This class will leave you with some real tools to apply to your life, and you\'ll have a tremendously fun time in the process of acquiring them!</p>','I - Improv for Shy People with Chris Sams (#15-08-2180)','','publish','open','open','','i-improv-for-shy-people-with-chris-sams-15-08-2180','','','2015-08-17 13:10:09','2015-08-17 20:10:09','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1943',0,'class','',0),(1944,5,'2015-07-09 16:13:02','2015-07-09 23:13:02','<h1>Teen Improv Ensemble<br />8 weeks, Fridays, 4:00 - 6:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule:</strong> Fridays, 4:00 – 6:00 pm  <br />September 18, 25, October 2, 9, 16, 23, 30, and November 6<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong>Attending High School, no prior improv experience necessary</p>\r\n<p>Have you done some improv and are itching to do more?!  Always wanted to try but weren\'t sure how to?  Are you a natural performer or someone who wants to come out of your shell?  Improv has something for absolutely everyone! </p>\r\n<p>In our teen improv class teens will work together learning improv principles and growing  into an ensemble as they have fun, make friends, and play on stage.</p>\r\n<p>The classes will be held at the Bayfront Theater in Fort Mason Center.   This is an after school workshop and open to high school students. The workshop will run for 8 weeks total. </p>\r\n<p>As part of this class, students will receive 2-for-1 passes to use to shows on the same days as their classes.  Watching improv is a fantastic way to learn it and see the principles at work. </p>','Teen Improv Ensemble w/Laura Derry (#15-09-2181)','','publish','open','open','','teen-improv-ensemble-wlaura-derry-15-09-2181','','','2015-07-09 16:13:02','2015-07-09 23:13:02','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1944',0,'class','',0),(1945,4,'2015-07-15 02:42:54','2015-07-15 09:42:54','<p>content for EU Tour information here.</p>','BATS 2015 EU Tour','','publish','closed','open','','eutour','','','2015-07-15 02:43:36','2015-07-15 09:43:36','',14,'http://www.improv.org/?page_id=1945',1,'page','',0),(1949,4,'2015-07-16 15:39:11','2015-07-16 22:39:11','','school-selling','','inherit','closed','open','','school-selling','','','2015-07-16 15:39:11','2015-07-16 22:39:11','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/school-selling.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1950,5,'2015-07-16 16:41:18','2015-07-16 23:41:18','<h1>Saturdays, 11:00 AM - 2:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>August 15 – September 26, 2015<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 6 sessions (once a week for 6 weeks, skipping one week for Labor Day weekend)<br /> <strong>Class dates:</strong> August 15, 22, 29, (skipping September 5), September 12, 19, and 26<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (18 hours total instruction)<br /> <strong>Class size:</strong> 12 students maximum<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $299<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> <a title=\"Foundation 2\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-2/\">Foundation 2</a></p>','F3 - Foundation 3 with Laura Derry (#15-08-2159)','','publish','open','open','','f3-foundation-3-with-laura-derry-15-08-2159','','','2015-07-16 21:02:54','2015-07-17 04:02:54','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1950',0,'class','',0),(1951,5,'2015-07-18 14:59:57','2015-07-18 21:59:57','<h1><a id=\"F1\"></a>3-Day Foundation 1 Intensive</h1>\r\n<p><strong>July 30  - August 1, 2015<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 3-day intensive<br /> <strong>Class dates:</strong> July 30, July 31, and August 1st, 10am-5pm daily<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 18 hours total instruction<br /> <strong>Class</strong> <strong>size:</strong> 16 students maximum</p>\r\n<p>Foundation 1 is our fun introduction to the joys and thrills of improvisation and the BATS-style of improvised theatre. This intensive covers all of the content of the 6-week Foundation 1 class over three days.</p>\r\n<p>Students learn improv concepts and vocabulary, practice new skills, and perform in a safe, friendly atmosphere. Through games and exercises, you\'ll play, explore, and experiment with creating characters and scenes, guided by our seasoned coaches. Foundation 1 is all about unleashing your innate skill. Are you human? Then you have all the experience necessary to excel!</p>\r\n<p><strong><br />**Please note - tuition is a bit higher for this class - $325 vs. $299 - as it\'s part of our Summer School program.**</strong></p>','Summer 2015 - F1 Intensive - (#15-07-2133)','','publish','open','open','','summer-2015-f1-intensive-15-07-2133-2','','','2015-07-18 14:59:57','2015-07-18 21:59:57','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1951',0,'class','',0),(1952,5,'2015-07-18 15:01:43','2015-07-18 22:01:43','<h1>3-Day Foundation 2 Intensive</h1>\r\n<p><strong>August 3 - August 5, 2015<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 3-day intensive<br /> <strong>Class Dates:</strong> August 3, 4, and 5<br /><strong>Class length</strong>: 18 hours total instruction<br /><strong>Class size</strong>: 14 students maximum<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> <a title=\"Foundation 1\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-1/\">Foundation 1</a> or equivalent. Please contact Regina Saisi, Dean, with any questions about prerequisites or your eligibility at regina@improv.org or 415-474-6776.</p>\r\n<p>Foundation 2 focuses on refining your improv knowledge and skill set, reinforcing the concepts you learned in Foundation 1 through games, play, and exercises.</p>\r\n<p>This course covers all of the content of the 6-week Foundation 2 class over three days.</p>\r\n<p>While the emphasis is still on fun, course content also explores more conceptual and technical information and helps you build the skills you need to perform in front of an audience.</p>\r\n<p>Students in Foundation 2 are required to read one of the definitive texts on improv: <em>IMPRO</em> by Keith Johnstone. Johnstone invented Theatresports, one of the core improv formats we play at BATS. <a href=\"http://improbook.eventbrite.com/\">BATS sells the book for $25;</a> it is also available from a variety of retail outlets. When enrolling, please indicate whether or not you would like to purchase the book from BATS. If so, you can pay for it at time of registration and pick up their book on your first day of class.</p>\r\n<p>At the conclusion, everyone \"passes\" and can move on to Foundation 3, but you can also take Foundation 2 as many times as you would like.</p>\r\n<p><strong><br />**Please note - tuition is a bit higher for this class - $325 vs. $299 - as it\'s part of our Summer School program.**</strong></p>','Summer 2015 - 3-Day Foundation 2 Intensive  (#15-08-2134)','','publish','open','open','','summer-2015-3-day-foundation-2-intensive-15-08-2134-2','','','2015-07-18 15:01:43','2015-07-18 22:01:43','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1952',0,'class','',0),(1953,7,'2015-07-23 13:07:53','2015-07-23 20:07:53','<h1>Paul Hungerford</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Special Guest from <a href=\"http://improtheatre.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Impro Theatre, LA</a>.</strong></p>','Paul Hungerford, LA','','publish','open','open','','paul-hungerford-la','','','2015-07-23 13:12:48','2015-07-23 20:12:48','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=actors&#038;p=1953',36,'actors','',0),(1954,7,'2015-07-23 13:05:48','2015-07-23 20:05:48','','Paul-Hungerford-236x236','','inherit','closed','open','','paul-hungerford-236x236','','','2015-07-23 13:05:48','2015-07-23 20:05:48','',1953,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Paul-Hungerford-236x236.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1963,7,'2015-07-30 14:48:11','2015-07-30 21:48:11','','classpic','','inherit','closed','open','','classpic','','','2015-07-30 14:48:11','2015-07-30 21:48:11','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/classpic.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1969,5,'2015-08-12 14:57:31','2015-08-12 21:57:31','<h1>Improv for Dating<br />Sunday, 6-9 PM and Monday, 7-10 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Sunday and Monday, August 23rd and 24th<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: Two 3-hour sessions<br /> <strong>Class dates and time:</strong> 6-9pm on August 23rd and 7-10pm on August 24th<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours; 6 hours total<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $90<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> None - everyone is welcome!</p>\r\n<div>Want to go on more dates?  Want to have more fun on those dates?\r\n<p>Listen, respond, think on your feet and take risks! These are important skills for an improviser AND they\'re also invaluable in the dating world. Come learn new skills that will help you flourish in the unpredictable dating scene, meet new people and have more FUN!</p>\r\n<p>This class teaches singles practical improv skills and approaches that will enhance your personal dating experience.  <br /> </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>Tuition includes a field trip to a BATS show on August 28 or <span data-term=\"goog_897658762\">29 - </span> 30\'s Romantic Comedy!</div>','Improv for Dating with Chris & Ceci (#15-08-2183)','','publish','open','open','','improv-for-dating-with-chris-ceci-15-08-2183','','','2015-08-21 17:24:58','2015-08-22 00:24:58','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1969',0,'class','',0),(1971,5,'2015-08-12 14:56:48','2015-08-12 21:56:48','<p>Guest Coach Ceci Walken</p>','Ceci Walken','','publish','closed','open','','ceci-walken','','','2015-08-12 14:56:48','2015-08-12 21:56:48','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=actors&#038;p=1971',2,'actors','',0),(1972,5,'2015-08-14 12:16:13','2015-08-14 19:16:13','<h1>Performance Workshop 1<br />Mondays, 7:00 PM - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>September 14 - November 2, 2015<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Schedule:</strong> 8 sessions (once a week for 8 weeks), 2 performances<br /><strong>Class Time/Dates: </strong>7-10pm on Mondays September 14, 21, 28, October 5, 12, 19, 26, and November 2<br /><strong>Performances: </strong>2 performances, TBD.<br /><strong>Class size:</strong> 10 students maximum <strong><br />Class length: </strong>3 hours (24 hours total of instruction)<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong>Studio Scene Work<em><br /> </em></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\">This 8-week workshop prepares you for your first performance in front of an audience by breaking down and covering these different core elements of performance:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Stage skills</l