break each day) <br /> <strong>Class dates:</strong> September 11, 12, and 13<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 18 hours total instruction<br /> <strong>Class</strong> <strong>size:</strong> 16 students maximum<br /> <strong>Tuition:</strong> $299</p>','F1 Intensive - Foundation 1 - B. Johnson & A. Sarouhan (#15-09-2186)','','publish','open','open','','f1-intensive-foundation-1-b-johnson-a-sarouhan-15-09-2186','','','2015-09-08 16:31:24','2015-09-08 23:31:24','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1975',0,'class','',0),(1976,5,'2015-08-14 16:21:26','2015-08-14 23:21:26','<h1>Performance Workshop 3 - <br />Elements of Long Form<br />Saturdays, 11:00 AM - 2:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>September 12 - October 31, 2015<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Schedule:</strong> 8 sessions; 2 performances<br /><strong>Class Time/Dates: </strong>11am-2pm on Saturdays<br />September 12, 19, 26, October 3, 10, 17, 24, and 31<br /><strong>Performances: </strong>Two performances: Dates and times TBD<br /><strong>Class size:</strong> 10 students maximum<br /><strong>Class length:</strong> 3 hours (24 hours total of instruction) <br /><strong>Prerequisite:</strong> ***<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Performance Workshops 1 and 2, or coach/dean approval. Please contact regina@improv.org with any eligibility questions.**</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>This 8-week workshop, the third in our Performance Series, prepares you for your first<br /> Long-Form performance in front of an audience by breaking down and covering these different core elements of performance: </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Taking your time and paying attention</li>\r\n<li>Narrative, and establishing a strong foundation</li>\r\n<li>Acting</li>\r\n<li>Improvising in genre</li>\r\n<li>Transitions between scenes</li>\r\n<li>Ensemble acting</li>\r\n<li>Building locations and maintaining a space object world</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>This class will qualify you to be considered for more advanced work as it will give you a grounding in the essential elements of Long-Form improvisation as BATS practices it.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Performance - Performance Workshop 3 (ELF) with Ken (#15-09-2185)','','publish','open','open','','performance-performance-workshop-3-elf-with-ken-15-09-2185','','','2015-08-24 18:28:59','2015-08-25 01:28:59','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=1976',0,'class','',0),(1978,4,'2015-08-17 23:12:17','2015-08-18 06:12:17','<p>Set in a fictional small town, this Courtroom Drama extends well beyond the walls of the courtroom.  First, our talented cast of actors will use your suggestions to create an idyllic small town.  You\'ll meet a cast of completely improvised characters and discover their many relationships.  After characters and relationships are established, you\'ll reveal their shocking courtroom positions.  Are the opposing attorneys married?  Was the victim having an affair with the judge?  You\'ll witness the trial, you\'ll even participate in the trial as counsel calls audience witnesses to the stand.</p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"color: #d9541e;\"><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Group Tickets\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/groups/\"><strong>Group tickets</strong> start at just $14 each!</a><br /><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Gift Certificates\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/gift-certificates/\">You can also give this show as a gift with a </a><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Gift Certificates\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/gift-certificates/\"><strong>BATS Gift Certific</strong><strong>ate</strong>.</a> </span></em></p>','Courtroom Drama','','draft','closed','open','','courtroom-drama','','','2015-09-27 01:49:25','2015-09-27 08:49:25','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=saturday&#038;p=1978',2,'saturday','',0),(1979,4,'2015-08-17 23:12:41','2015-08-18 06:12:41','','313-courtroom-drama','','inherit','closed','open','','313-courtroom-dr