vember 10, 17, 24, December 1, 8, and 15<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (18 hours total instruction)<br /> <strong>Class size:</strong> 12 students maximum<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $329<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> <a title=\"Foundation 2\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-2/\">Foundation 2</a></p>','F3 - Foundation 3 in PA with Kasey Klemm (#15-11-2218)','','publish','open','open','','f3-foundation-3-in-pa-with-kasey-klemm-15-11-2218','','','2015-09-16 13:39:48','2015-09-16 20:39:48','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=2050',0,'class','',0),(2051,5,'2015-09-17 15:37:36','2015-09-17 22:37:36','<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">Advanced Performance Workshop:<br />Improvised Downton Abbey<br /><br />Saturdays, 2:30 - 5:30 PM<br /><br /></h1>\r\n<p><strong>November 14 - December 12, 2015<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco<br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Schedule:</strong> 4 sessions (once a week for 4 weeks), 1 performance<br /><strong>Class Time/Dates: </strong>2:30-5:30pm on Saturdays November 14, 21, (skipping Nov. 28th for Thanksgiving weekend), December 5, and 12<br /><strong>Performances: </strong>One performance, Sunday, December 13th, 6pm<br /><strong>Class size:</strong> 8 students maximum <strong><br />Class length: </strong>3 hours (12 hours total of instruction)<br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong>Previous long-form experience along with coach and dean approval. Contact regina@improv.org to confirm eligibility before signing up.<em><br /> <br /></em>Come play in the wildly popular style of Downton Abbey!  In this 4-week advanced performance workshop, you\'ll learn how to portray a variety of characters who live and work in a turn of the century English Manor.  Play fully-realized characters who are high or low status, from the Second Footman to the Dowager Countess, where proper Victorian manners rule the day. <br />Inhabitants of this world also get to explore deeper emotional feelings and desire for social change that live hidden beneath the surface, but which can occasionally bubble up with shattering consequences.  <br /><br />This workshop and performance is primarily designed for experienced improvisers interested in focusing on character, status, and sustaining an emotionally-driven narrative in a rich and vibrant early 20th century setting.<br /> <em><br /></em></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0pt;\"> </p>','Performance - Downton Abbey with John Remak (#15-11-2210)','','publish','open','open','','performance-downton-abbey-with-john-remak-15-11-2210','','','2015-10-19 14:16:46','2015-10-19 21:16:46','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=2051',0,'class','',0),(2053,5,'2015-09-21 15:04:05','2015-09-21 22:04:05','<h1>Intro to Improv in Palo Alto<br />Wednesday, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Wednesday, September 23rd</strong><br /><strong> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: One session<br /> <strong>Class date:</strong> September 23rd<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $50<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> None - everyone is welcome!</p>','I - Intro to Improv in Palo Alto with John  -  (#15-09-2219)','','publish','open','open','','i-intro-to-improv-in-palo-alto-with-john-15-09-2219','','','2015-09-23 13:14:35','2015-09-23 20:14:35','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=2053',0,'class','',0),(2055,7,'2015-09-23 13:58:10','2015-09-23 20:58:10','<h1>Andy Sarouhan</h1>\n<p><strong>Coach</strong> since 2015</p>\n<p>Andy Sarouhan is a Bay Area native. His improvisation training began in 1992, when he joined his high school improvisation team. That event started a chain reaction that eventually resulted in a BA in Theatre from UC San Diego and an MFA in Creative Writing from UC Riverside.</p>\n<p>Since 2003, Andy has improvised professionally with Flash Family and the Un-Scripted Theater Company, where he had the opportunity to train and perform in both shortform and narrative longform shows.</p>\n<p>He has been a busy improvisation coach since 2001, leading courses for ImprovWorks, UC Riverside, American Conservatory Theater, Cal Shakes, Un-Scripted Theater Company, and BATS Improv. Some of his most rewarding work has been with young people in San Mateo, where he is a coach of two high school improvisation teams, including the team with which he first performed as a teenager.</p>','Andy Sarouhan','','inherit','closed','closed','','729-autosave-v1','','','2015-09-23 13:58:10','2015-09-23 20:58:10','',729,'http://www.improv.org/729-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2057,4,'2015-09-27 02:12:21','2015-09-27 09:12:21','','313-noir-web-updated','','inherit','closed','closed','','313-noir-web-updated','','','2015-09-27 02:12:21','2015-09-27 09:12:21','',1994,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/313-noir-web-updated.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2060,7,'2015-09-28 16:36:58','2015-09-28 23:36:58','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-492\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/group1.jpg\" alt=\"group1\" width=\"332\" height=\"236\" />Group Tickets</h1>\r\n<p>What do birthday parties, family reunions, conventions,  co-worker cliques, corporate morale building, sports teams, youth groups, bachelorette parties, and marching bands have in common?</p>\r\n<p>Someone who makes a duck face while taking a selfie? <em>Maybe.</em></p>\r\n<p>They love group outings to a BATS Improv show? <em>Definitely.</em></p>\r\n<p>A BATS performance is a terrific outing for any group of folks who want to have fun, and we’ve happily hosted every kind of group you can think of at one time or another. If you’re looking for a dysfunctional family stress-fest or corporate PowerPoint snoozapalooza, try elsewhere. At BATS, everyone gets to enjoy themselves while doing things they rarely have the opportunity or freedom to do. Whoever said “you can’t please everyone” never booked a group event at BATS.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-493\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/group2.jpg\" alt=\"group2\" width=\"127\" height=\"134\" />Buy Six Tickets and Save</h3>\r\n<p>Purchase a six-pack of tickets for $90 (a savings of $30 over door price). Come to six shows on your own, or bring a friend to three, or treat two-thirds of the Supreme Court to one, or (you get the picture).</p>\r\n<p>Available at the Bayfront Theater box office or <a title=\"Gift Certificates\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/school/gift-certificates/\">online</a>.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-494\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/group3.jpg\" alt=\"group3\" width=\"215\" height=\"155\" />Groups of 10-200</h3>\r\n<p>Tickets for groups of 10 or more start at just $14 each. When you purchase 10+ tickets through our website, you will automatically receive a group discount.</p>\r\n<p>BATS\' <a title=\"Bayfront Theater Rentals\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/bats-on-the-go/bayfront-theater-rentals/\">Bayfront Theater</a> can accommodate groups of 10 to 200.  For more information about group rates or if you have a particularly large group attending a show, please email <a href=\"mailto:shows@improv.org\">shows@improv.org</a> or call (415) 474-6776.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-495\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/group4.jpg\" alt=\"group4\" width=\"215\" height=\"155\" />Groups of 200+</h3>\r\n<p>For groups of more than 200 people, <a title=\"BATS On-the-Go\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/bats-on-the-go/\">BATS On-the-Go</a> specializes in custom off-site performances. Our custom entertainment is the antidote for bad cover bands, awkward icebreaker games, and other event fails. Inspired by your group’s ideas, our improv professionals will create a personalized show that turns your party into an engaging, unforgettable occasion.</p>\r\n<p>We\'ll work with you to develop the perfect program for your group — from short scenes, stories, and songs to a complete improvised murder mystery to Theatresports<sup>TM</sup>, our knock-down-drag-out improv rumble!</p>\r\n<p>All of our shows are 100% unscripted and unplanned. Whatever the theme, the show is a journey that brings people together through shared fun, laughter, and creativity.</p>\r\n<p>Please email <a href=\"mailto:otg@improv.org\">otg@improv.org</a> or call (415) 474-6776 to learn more about the custom entertainment we can provide your group.</p>\r\n<hr />','Group Tickets','','inherit','closed','closed','','111-autosave-v1','','','2015-09-28 16:36:58','2015-09-28 23:36:58','',111,'http://www.improv.org/111-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2061,5,'2015-09-29 15:34:14','2015-09-29 22:34:14','<h1>6-Week Studio Scene Work <br />Saturdays, 2:30 - 5:30 PM <br />(first 2 weeks)<br />Saturdays, 11:00 AM - 2:00 PM <br />(final 4 weeks)</h1>\r\n<p><strong>October 24 – December 5, 2015<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule:</strong> 6 sessions; once a week for six weeks <br /><strong>Class Time/Dates: <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Please note there are 2 different times for this class - 2:30-5:30 on the first two weeks, and 11am-2pm for the 4 final sessions! </span></strong><br />2:30-5:30pm on Saturdays October 24 and 31<br />11am-2pm on Saturdays November 7, 14, 21 (skipping Nov. 28 for Thanksgiving holiday weekend), and December 5<br /><strong>Class size: </strong>10 students maximum <br /><strong>Class length:</strong> 3 hours (18 hours total) <br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong>Foundation 3</p>','SS - Scene Work - FMC with Chris (#15-10-2221)','','publish','open','open','','ss-scene-work-fmc-with-chris-15-10-2221','','','2015-09-29 15:35:21','2015-09-29 22:35:21','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=2061',0,'class','',0),(2062,5,'2015-09-29 16:02:56','2015-09-29 23:02:56','<h1>Improvised Rap with Guest Coach<br />Kristian Ruggieri<br />Thursdays, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>October 22 – November 12, 2015<br /></strong><strong>Bayfront Theater, San Francisco </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 4 sessions (once a week for 4 weeks)<br /><strong>Class dates: </strong>October 22, 29, November 5, and 12<br /><strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (12 hours total)<br /><strong>Class size: </strong>10 students maximum<br /><strong>Tuition</strong>: $180 <br /><strong>Prerequisite:<a href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-2/\"> </a></strong><a href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-2/\">Foundation 2</a></p>\r\n<p>Afraid your rap is wack?  Learn to flow like a pro in this class!  We\'ll create rap personas and play games that focus on rhyming and telling stories to a beat before we start rapping solo, in groups and in head-to-head rap battles. By the end of class you\'ll have the skills, attitude and confidence you need to spit  mad rhymes, drop the mic, and exit stage left.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>Guest Coach Kristian Ruggieri taught this class in April, and here\'s some of what those participants said about the class:</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\"I loved Kristian\'s style: laid back and flexible, but she had something fun and exciting planned for every minute of the class. We all grew and improved as improvisers exponentially in this class- by the end I was doing something I never thought I\'d be able to do!\"</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\"I started out a little tentative, thinking how incredibly hard to teach people how to rap, but I felt this was soooo valuable, as I\'m very jazzed up about improvising music and I feel this was kind of the rap jelly to the singing peanut butter. This class really rocked my world. I rap in my head on the way to work now.\"</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\"It\'s been awhile since I\'ve been nervous in a class, but I was nervous going into this class. Kristian did a great job of structuring the class in a way that eased us into it and built the skills we needed. We were all kind of amazed yesterday in our last class that we\'re good at this now. I can us this on the stage immediately.\"</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div> </div>','Improvised Rap - Kristian Ruggieri (15-10-2222)','','publish','open','open','','improvised-rap-kristian-ruggieri-15-10-2222','','','2015-09-29 16:03:46','2015-09-29 23:03:46','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=2062',0,'class','',0),(2063,5,'2015-09-29 16:04:39','2015-09-29 23:04:39','<h1>Improvised Rap with Guest Coach<br />Kristian Ruggieri<br />Thursdays, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>October 22 – November 12, 2015<br /></strong><strong>Bayfront Theater, San Francisco </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 4 sessions (once a week for 4 weeks)<br /><strong>Class dates: </strong>October 22, 29, November 5, and 12<br /><strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours (12 hours total)<br /><strong>Class size: </strong>10 students maximum<br /><strong>Tuition</strong>: $180 <br /><strong>Prerequisite:<a href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-2/\"> </a></strong><a href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-2/\">Foundation 2</a></p>\r\n<p>Afraid your rap is wack?  Learn to flow like a pro in this class!  We\'ll create rap personas and play games that focus on rhyming and telling stories to a beat before we start rapping solo, in groups and in head-to-head rap battles. By the end of class you\'ll have the skills, attitude and confidence you need to spit  mad rhymes, drop the mic, and exit stage left.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>Guest Coach Kristian Ruggieri taught this class in April, and here\'s some of what those participants said about the class:</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\"I loved Kristian\'s style: laid back and flexible, but she had something fun and exciting planned for every minute of the class. We all grew and improved as improvisers exponentially in this class- by the end I was doing something I never thought I\'d be able to do!\"</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\"I started out a little tentative, thinking how incredibly hard to teach people how to rap, but I felt this was soooo valuable, as I\'m very jazzed up about improvising music and I feel this was kind of the rap jelly to the singing peanut butter. This class really rocked my world. I rap in my head on the way to work now.\"</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\"It\'s been awhile since I\'ve been nervous in a class, but I was nervous going into this class. Kristian did a great job of structuring the class in a way that eased us into it and built the skills we needed. We were all kind of amazed yesterday in our last class that we\'re good at this now. I can us this on the stage immediately.\"</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div> </div>','Improvised Rap - Kristian Ruggieri (15-10-2222)','','publish','open','open','','improvised-rap-kristian-ruggieri-15-10-2222-2','','','2015-09-29 16:04:39','2015-09-29 23:04:39','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=2063',0,'class','',0),(2064,4,'2015-10-02 02:33:46','2015-10-02 09:33:46','<h4><strong>Map &amp; Nearby</strong></h4>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/place/BATS+Improv+Theatre/@37.8067722,-122.4317803,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m2!3m1!1s0x808580de5d16d545:0x48b36832e74af2b7\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-252 size-full\" src=\"http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/map_restaurants_214x2141.jpg\" alt=\"map_restaurants_214x214\" width=\"214\" height=\"214\" /><br /><em>click for Google map</em><br /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>At Fort Mason Center: <br /><a href=\"https://longnow.org/interval/\" target=\"_blank\">The Interval</a> </strong>(bar w/ snacks)<strong><br /></strong><strong><a href=\"http://www.greensrestaurant.com\" target=\"_blank\">Greens</a></strong> (upscale vegetarian)<br /><strong><a href=