ours total instruction)<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $329<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> <a title=\"Foundation 1\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/school/foundation-1/\">Foundation 1</a></p>','F2 - Foundation 2 in Palo Alto with K. Klemm (#15-10-2223)','','publish','closed','open','','f2-foundation-2-in-palo-alto-with-k-klemm-15-10-2223','','','2015-10-06 17:48:52','2015-10-07 00:48:52','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=2069',0,'class','',0),(2071,4,'2015-10-08 20:36:06','2015-10-09 03:36:06','','Scary Stories campfire','','inherit','closed','closed','','scary1','','','2015-10-08 20:36:28','2015-10-09 03:36:28','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/scary1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2073,4,'2015-10-08 20:36:08','2015-10-09 03:36:08','','SF Noir leads Oct 3','','inherit','closed','closed','','noir2','','','2015-10-08 20:37:54','2015-10-09 03:37:54','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/noir2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2074,4,'2015-10-08 20:36:09','2015-10-09 03:36:09','','SF Noir Oct 3','','inherit','closed','closed','','noir1','','','2015-10-08 20:39:20','2015-10-09 03:39:20','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/noir1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2075,4,'2015-10-08 20:36:10','2015-10-09 03:36:10','','Yelp from Oct 3','','inherit','closed','closed','','screen-shot-2015-10-08-at-8-23-38-pm','','','2015-10-08 20:37:20','2015-10-09 03:37:20','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Screen-Shot-2015-10-08-at-8.23.38-PM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2076,4,'2015-10-08 20:36:11','2015-10-09 03:36:11','','Yelp Oct 6','','inherit','closed','closed','','screen-shot-2015-10-08-at-8-23-43-pm','','','2015-10-08 20:38:54','2015-10-09 03:38:54','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Screen-Shot-2015-10-08-at-8.23.43-PM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2080,5,'2015-10-13 17:40:05','2015-10-14 00:40:05','<h1>Games!<br />Thursdays, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Thursdays December 3 and December 10<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: Two sessions; Thursdays December 3 (Chris Sams) and December 10 (John Remak)<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $90<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Foundation 3 and above</p>\r\n<p>Games, games games! Games in improv give us a chance to play with the tempo/pace of scenes and increase our ranges emotionally, narratively, and physically.  They help us take greater risks and learn to fail more gracefully.   </p>\r\n<div>In this two-week class, you\'ll play a huge assortment of fun improv performance games.  This class is both a great introduction to the classic canon of improv games and a nice refresher for the seasoned gamers out there. \r\n<div><br />Chris Sams and John Remak, masters of improv game-play will lead you through the cannon of BATS Improv games - the old stand-bys and new favorites that never fail to surprise and delight our audiences! Get the ins and outs, tips and tricks of dozens of classic improv games, including justification games and verbal restrictions.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','I - Games with Chris and John (#15-12-2214)','','publish','open','open','','i-games-with-chris-and-john-15-12-2214','','','2015-10-13 17:40:05','2015-10-14 00:40:05','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=2080',0,'class','',0),(2082,5,'2015-10-19 14:08:23','2015-10-19 21:08:23','<h1>Relationships Through Status<br />Thursday, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Thursday, November 5th<br />Studio 210 (The Mission), San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: One session - Thursday, November 5th, 7-10pm<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $45<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Foundation 3 and above</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>\"The audience will always be held when a status is being modified.\"* </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Every interaction involves status and power….either consciously or unconsciously.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Creating and shifting the power dynamic in relationships is a powerful tool for playwrights and actors. <br /><br />In this 3-hour workshop, we will leverage the tools of status to create engaging characters and dynamic relationships.  This is a wonderful chance to dig into the status tool box and bring those skills to your work on stage.<br /><br /></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><em>*Impro chapter on Status, Keith Johnstone</em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div> </div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','I - Relationships through Status with William  (#15-11-2225)','','publish','open','open','','i-relationships-through-status-with-william-15-11-2225','','','2015-10-19 14:08:23','2015-10-19 21:08:23','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=2082',0,'class','',0),(2083,5,'2015-10-19 14:10:01','2015-10-19 21:10:01','<h1>Relationships Through Status<br />Thursday, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Thursday, November 5th<br />Studio 210 (The Mission), San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: One session - Thursday, November 5th, 7-10pm<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $45<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Foundation 3 and above</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>\"The audience will always be held when a status is being modified.\"* </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Every interaction involves status and power….either consciously or unconsciously.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Creating and shifting the power dynamic in relationships is a powerful tool for playwrights and actors. <br /><br />In this 3-hour workshop, we will leverage the tools of status to create engaging characters and dynamic relationships.  This is a wonderful chance to dig into the status tool box and bring those skills to your work on stage.<br /><br /></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><em>*Impro chapter on Status, Keith Johnstone</em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div> </div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','I - Relationships through Status with William  (#15-11-2225)','','publish','open','open','','i-relationships-through-status-with-william-15-11-2225-2','','','2015-10-19 14:10:01','2015-10-19 21:10:01','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=2083',0,'class','',0),(2084,5,'2015-10-19 15:15:18','2015-10-19 22:15:18','<h1>Improv Dance: The Ultimate in Making Your Partner Look Good<br />Wednesdays, 7:30 - 9:30 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Wednesdays December 2 and December 9<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: Two sessions; Wednesdays December 2 and 9, 7:30 - 9:30pm<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 2 hours each session, for a total of 4 hours of class<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $60<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Foundation 2 and above</p>\r\n<p>What is the basic step for the waltz? Or the American tango? How do you hold your frame? If you are an improviser, you should be able to answer these questions! Aren\'t you tired of bumping into each other in a ballroom scene? </p>\r\n<div>Partner dancing requires highly nuanced \"give and take.\" Bring that same level of sensitivity to your improvisation. Become an improviser who moves fluidly on the stage. <br /><br /></div>\r\n<div>In this class you will learn the basics of partner dancing, a few basic steps you should know and how it can apply to your improv work. This class will improve your movement, your connection to your fellow players and your body awareness for character work. <br /><br />This 2-hour class for 2 weeks will be sure to be both highly energizing and informative. </div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','I - Improv Dance with Zoe (#15-12-2226)','','publish','open','open','','i-improv-dance-with-zoe-15-12-2226','','','2015-10-19 15:15:18','2015-10-19 22:15:18','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=2084',0,'class','',0),(2085,5,'2015-10-19 15:16:03','2015-10-19 22:16:03','<h1>Improv Dance: The Ultimate in Making Your Partner Look Good<br />Wednesdays, 7:30 - 9:30 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Wednesdays December 2 and December 9<br /> Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: Two sessions; Wednesdays December 2 and 9, 7:30 - 9:30pm<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 2 hours each session, for a total of 4 hours of class<br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $60<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Foundation 2 and above</p>\r\n<p>What is the basic step for the waltz? Or the American tango? How do you hold your frame? If you are an improviser, you should be able to answer these questions! Aren\'t you tired of bumping into each other in a ballroom scene? </p>\r\n<div>Partner dancing requires highly nuanced \"give and take.\" Bring that same level of sensitivity to your improvisation. Become an improviser who moves fluidly on the stage. <br /><br /></div>\r\n<div>In this class you will learn the basics of partner dancing, a few basic steps you should know and how it can apply to your improv work. This class will improve your movement, your connection to your fellow players and your body awareness for character work. <br /><br />This 2-hour class for 2 weeks will be sure to be both highly energizing and informative. </div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','I - Improv Dance with Zoe (#15-12-2226)','','publish','open','open','','i-improv-dance-with-zoe-15-12-2226-2','','','2015-10-19 15:16:03','2015-10-19 22:16:03','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=2085',0,'class','',0),(2086,5,'2015-10-19 17:07:56','2015-10-20 00:07:56','<h1>Improv for Shy People at Fort Mason<br />Monday, 7:00 - 10:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Monday, November 2nd<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 1 session<br /> <strong>Class dates and time:</strong> 7-10pm on November 2nd<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 3 hours <br /> <strong>Tuition</strong>: $45<br /> <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> None - everyone is welcome!</p>\r\n<p>Do you self-identify as shy or introverted? Are you unlikely to be the first to speak up in class or in a meeting? Do you find yourself overshadowed by your friends, family, or colleagues? Are you overwhelmed when you\'re in a big group of people? </p>\r\n<p>Signing up for an improv class may be the last thing on your mind if you consider yourself shy, but you\'d be surprised how safe and supportive the art form can be.  Focused on creating a comfortable and safe environment, Improv for Shy People introduces the basics of BATS-style improv in order to cultivate spontaneity, flexibility, and confidence.  Improv skills build trust and cooperation and tap into the imaginative and creative qualities that we all possess. This class will leave you with some real tools to apply to your life, and you\'ll have a tremendously fun time in the process of acquiring them!</p>','I - Improv for Shy People with Mona (#15-11-2227)','','publish','open','open','','i-improv-for-shy-people-with-mona-15-11-2227','','','2015-10-19 17:08:40','2015-10-20 00:08:40','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=2086',0,'class','',0),(2088,7,'2015-10-20 13:50:10','2015-10-20 20:50:10','','October','','inherit','closed','closed','','1341-autosave-v1','','','2015-10-20 13:50:10','2015-10-20 20:50:10','',1341,'http://www.improv.org/1341-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2090,5,'2015-10-22 14:30:20','2015-10-22 21:30:20','<h1>Friday, 6:00 - 10:00 PM<br />Saturday, 10:00 AM - 5:00 PM<br />Sunday, 10:00 AM - 5:00 PM</h1>\r\n<p><strong>December 11  - December 13, 2015<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule</strong>: 3-day intensive: 4 hours (6-10pm on Friday) and 6 hours each on Saturday and Sunday (10am-5pm on Saturday and Sunday, with a one-hour lunch break each day) <br /> <strong>Class dates: </strong>December 11, 12, and 13<br /> <strong>Class length</strong>: 15 hours total instruction<br /> <strong>Class</strong> <strong>size:</strong> 16 students maximum<br /> <strong>Tuition:</strong> $269</p>','F1 Intensive - Foundation 1 - D. Dennison & R. Stockley (#15-12-2228)','','publish','open','open','','f1-intensive-foundation-1-d-dennison-r-stockley-15-12-2228','','','2015-10-22 14:31:10','2015-10-22 21:31:10','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=2090',0,'class','',0),(2092,4,'2015-10-22 18:32:23','2015-10-23 01:32:23','','img_class_pic1','','inherit','closed','closed','','img_class_pic1','','','2015-10-22 18:32:23','2015-10-23 01:32:23','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/img_class_pic1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2094,7,'2015-10-26 11:54:00','2015-10-26 18:54:00','<p>Celebrate Halloween with our annual, completely improvised, frightfully-delightful, feature-length musical!  Things may start out normal enough, but soon emotions will run high and everything will become a matter of life and death!  As always, everything will be made up on the spot - our talented cast of actors will take inspiration from your suggestions, as well as classic horror films like Alien, Poltergeist, and The Exorcist.  </p>\r\n<p><strong>Come in costume and get a free non-alcoholic beverage from concessions!</strong></p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"color: #d9541e;\"><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Group Tickets\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/groups/\"><strong>Group tickets</strong> start at just $14 each!</a><br /><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Gift Certificates\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/gift-certificates/\">You can also give this show as a gift with a </a><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Gift Certificates\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/gift-certificates/\"><strong>BATS Gift Certific</strong><strong>ate</strong>.</a> </span></em></p>','Halloween Horror Musical','','inherit','closed','closed','','906-autosave-v1','','','2015-10-26 11:54:00','2015-10-26 18:54:00','',906,'http://www.improv.org/906-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2095,4,'2015-10-28 02:07:10','2015-10-28 09:07:10','','313-web-superscene','','inherit','closed','closed','','313-web-superscene-2','','','2015-10-28 02:07:10','2015-10-28 09:07:10','',2002,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/313-web-superscene1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2097,4,'2015-10-30 03:00:27','2015-10-30 10:00:27','','IMG_2817','','inherit','closed','closed','','img_2817','','','2015-10-30 03:00:27','2015-10-30 10:00:27','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/IMG_2817.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2098,4,'2015-10-30 03:00:30','2015-10-30 10:00:30','','IMG_2817','','inherit','closed','closed','','img_2817-2','','','2015-10-30 03:00:30','2015-10-30 10:00:30','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/IMG_28171.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2099,7,'2015-10-30 16:51:55','2015-10-30 23:51:55','','January','','publish','closed','open','','january','','','2015-10-30 16:51:55','2015-10-30 23:51:55','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=sunday&#038;p=2099',10,'sunday','',0),(2100,4,'2015-11-01 02:49:38','2015-11-01 10:49:38','<h1><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-773\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/otg-1.jpg\" alt=\"otg-1\" width=\"332\" height=\"221\" />Private Entertainment &amp; Holiday Events</h1>\n<p>By definition, improvisation <em>is</em> custom entertainment. It cannot be reproduced, no matter how often our audiences may suspect something we perform is scripted. BATS Improv provides entertainment that is customized for YOU, and allows YOUR TEAM to share the spotlight! Our cast can incorporate your employees, family members, friends, colleagues — any willing volunteers, that is — into the show to make it a memorable experience for everyone.</p>\n<p>BATS Improv provides customized, hilarious, interactive entertainment for holiday parties, too. Contact us for more information or to book a BATS ensemble and secure the date of your choice, any day of the week.</p>\n<hr />\n<h3>Some of our most popular formats include</h3>\n<p><strong>BATS Improv Trio<br /></strong>Amaze the people at your gathering with a one-of-a-kind improv performance — just for them!</p>\n<ul>\n<li>3 performers</li>\n<li>30-minutes to 1 hour of short scenes, stories, and songs inspired by audience suggestions</li>\n<li>Lots of audience participation and variety<br /><br /></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Theatresports™ Main Event<br /></strong>Two teams compete in a full-length performance of <a title=\"About Improvised Theatre\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/shows/about-improvised-theatre/#shortform\">Theatresports</a>, our signature format.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>6 performers</li>\n<li>90-minutes to 2 hours, with intermission, of short scenes, stories, and songs based on audience suggestions</li>\n<li>Lots of audience participation and variety<br /><br /></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-774\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/otg-2.jpg\" alt=\"otg-2\" width=\"215\" height=\"143\" />Theatresports™</strong> <strong>Shorts<br /></strong>Two teams compete in an abridged version of <a title=\"About Improvised Theatre\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/shows/about-improvised-theatre/#shortform\">Theatresports</a>, our signature format.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>6 performers</li>\n<li>30 minutes to 1 hour of short scenes, stories, and songs based on audience suggestions</li>\n<li>Lots of audience participation and variety<br /><br /></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><br /></strong>Our world-fgenre shows will make your group ask \"How much of that was actually improvised?!\" The answer is always \"All of it!”</p>\n<ul>\n<li>We offer completely improvised musicals and plays in the style of Shakespeare, Westerns, Film Noir, Science Fiction, and many other genres. Content can be personalized to include references to your event, guest of honor, industry, personnel, and more. And all formats incorporate suggestions and ideas that are generated by your audience.</li>\n<li>Number of performers and length vary</li>\n<li>Starting at $2,700</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Each program is individually created and custom designed for each client. Performance pricing will vary based on length and complexity of show, number of performers, and distance from San Francisco city limits. </em></p>\n<hr />\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-776\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/otg-3.jpg\" alt=\"otg-3\" width=\"332\" height=\"221\" />Add a Training Component</h3>\n<p>Improv is about more than making people laugh -- it’s about collaboration, listening, unlocking creativity, spontaneity, intelligent risk taking, and focus. You can add a workshop component to any of our shows to help your group strengthen these skills while having a great time. BATS On-the-Go will create a <a title=\"Training Programs\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/onthego/training-programs/\">group training</a> fully customized to your event. </p>\n<p>And you can even be your own party’s entertainment! Our <strong>Improv Class &amp; Team Performance </strong>workshop prepares your team to perform an improv show of your own after just one day\'s training.  <a title=\"Workshops &amp; Pricing\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/onthego/workshops-pricing/\">See more workshop options »</a></p>\n<hr />\n<h3>We’d love to collaborate with you to create an entertaining, unique, unforgettable event!</h3>\n<p>Contact us to learn how BATS On-the-Go’s programs can be customized for your needs. Don’t worry if you’re not sure what you want or what show might work best -- we’re happy to walk you through all the options, and brainstorm a couple more. Improvising fun solutions is what we do best!</p>\n<p><strong>BATS On-the-Go</strong><br /><strong><a href=\"mailto:OTG@improv.org\">OTG@improv.org<br /></a></strong>(415) 474-6776</p>','Custom Entertainment & Holiday Events','','inherit','closed','closed','','349-autosave-v1','','','2015-11-01 02:49:38','2015-11-01 10:49:38','',349,'http://www.improv.org/349-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2101,4,'2015-11-01 03:08:40','2015-11-01 11:08:40','<h1><img class=\"alignright wp-image-1029 size-full\" src=\"http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/OTG_IMG_4684_332x178.jpg\" alt=\"OTG_IMG_4684_332x178\" width=\"332\" height=\"178\" />Improv @ Work</h1>\n<p>Through Improv @ Work BATS\' provides Group Training Programs and Custom Entertainment, your place or ours — from collaboration, communication, and team-building workshops to an on-site improvised show tailored just for you.</p>\n<h3>Why Improv @ Work?</h3>\n<p><em>Because improv skills are life skills, and work skills. </em>Whether you work for a Fortune 500, a tech startup, or a social justice nonprofit, your team must be able to <strong>adapt, create, communicate, and collaborate.</strong> Unlike traditional corporate training programs, improv embraces the uniqueness of every participant while creating meaningful bonds through shared success. Plus, it’s fun!</p>\n<p>And for special events, parties, or just to provide some stress relief in the office, no entertainment is more personal and involving than improv. Your group’s suggestions will inspire our show.</p>\n<p>[content_block id=345]</p>\n<hr />\n<h3><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-318\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/otg2.jpg\" alt=\"otg2\" width=\"215\" height=\"155\" />Group Training</h3>\n<p>Since 1986, BATS On-the-Go has brought the power of improvised theatre to businesses and organizations to improve team effectiveness, unlock creativity and innovation, and build morale.</p>\n<p>We believe that humans are most receptive to learning when they’re enjoying themselves. Our improv professionals create engaging, no-pressure learning environments that bring out the best in your people and your company. Our world-class training can take place in your office, at our theater, or wherever works best for your group.</p>\n<p>Provide your team with experience in successful collaboration with BATS On-the-Go. Pixar, Kaiser Permanente, YouTube, and many others have. <a title=\"What Our Clients Say\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/bats-on-the-go/what-our-clients-say/\">See what they had to say</a>.</p>\n<p><a title=\"Group Training\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/onthego/group-training/\">Tell me more about Group Training »</a></p>\n<hr />\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-319\" src=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/otg3.jpg\" alt=\"otg3\" width=\"215\" height=\"322\" />Custom Entertainment</h3>\n<p>BATS‘ custom entertainment is the antidote for bad cover bands, awkward icebreaker games, and other event fails. Inspired by your group’s ideas, our improv professionals will create a personalized show that turns your party into an engaging, unforgettable occasion.</p>\n<p>We\'ll work with you to develop the perfect program for your group — from short scenes, stories, and songs to a complete improvised murder mystery to Theatresports<sup>TM</sup>, our knock-down-drag-out improv rumble!</p>\n<p>All of our shows are 100% unscripted and unplanned. Whatever the theme, the show is a journey that brings people together through shared fun, laughter, and creativity.</p>\n<p>And don’t worry about putting your people “on the spot.” Guest participation is encouraged, but no one is badgered or dragged onstage. We only take volunteers who actually volunteer! (Seriously, we’re not about making anyone uncomfortable. Click <a title=\"About Us\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/about-us/\">here</a> for more about us and our style of performance.)</p>\n<p><a title=\"Custom Entertainment &amp; Holiday Events\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/bats-on-the-go/custom-entertainment-holiday-events/\">Tell me more about Custom Entertainment »</a></p>\n<hr />\n<h3>Can’t Decide? Want Both?</h3>\n<p>If you can’t decide which program would be best for your group — or if you’ve already realized that all things improv are wonderful — you can <strong>combine training and entertainment</strong> by adding a workshop to a performance or vice versa.</p>\n<p>Contact us to learn more: <a href=\"mailto:otg@improv.org\">otg@improv.org</a>  415.474.6776</p>\n<hr />\n<h3>Holiday Events</h3>\n<p>Planning a holiday party? BATS On-the-Go offers <strong>Holiday Events packages</strong> that will add fun and excitement to any gathering.</p>\n<p><a title=\"Custom Entertainment &amp; Holiday Events\" href=\"http://bats.wpengine.com/bats-on-the-go/custom-entertainment-holiday-events/\">Tell me more about Holiday Events »</a></p>','Improv @ Work','','inherit','closed','closed','','13-autosave-v1','','','2015-11-01 03:08:40','2015-11-01 11:08:40','',13,'http://www.improv.org/13-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2102,4,'2015-11-01 12:49:27','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<p>Super Scene is a fast-paced, directed-improv, theater competition.  Each show starts with five stories - each unique in genre, tone, and style.  Each story is directed by one our five cast members, who are improvising live in the moment to get exactly what they want from their fellow actors.  The stories unfold round by round. After each round, the audience chooses which stories continue and which is eliminated.  After the final vote, only one story remains and the <strong>Super Scene</strong> is performed! It\'s a fun, hilarious, and completely delightful night of improvisation full of variety and audience interaction.</p>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"color: #d9541e;\"><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Group Tickets\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/groups/\"><strong>Group tickets</strong> start at just $14 each!</a><br /><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Gift Certificates\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/gift-certificates/\">You can also give this show as a gift with a </a><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Gift Certificates\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/gift-certificates/\"><strong>BATS Gift Certific</strong><strong>ate</strong>.</a> </span></em></p>','Super Scene','','draft','closed','open','','','','','2015-11-01 12:49:27','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=friday&p=2102',2,'friday','',0),(2103,4,'2015-11-01 13:00:51','2015-11-01 21:00:51','<p>Every Super Scene show is jam-packed with genre!  Each night, we\'ll tell five different stories in five different genres.  You might see an musical right after a horror story, or a stage play right after an intergalactic space adventure.</p>\n<p>As the night goes  </p>\n<p><em><span style=\"color: #d9541e;\"><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Group Tickets\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/groups/\"><strong>Group tickets</strong> start at just $14 each!</a><br /><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Gift Certificates\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/gift-certificates/\">You can also give this show as a gift with a </a><a style=\"color: #d9541e;\" title=\"Gift Certificates\" href=\"http://www.improv.org/shows/gift-certificates/\"><strong>BATS Gift Certific</strong><strong>ate</strong>.</a> </span></em></p>','Super Scene','','inherit','closed','closed','','2002-autosave-v1','','','2015-11-01 13:00:51','2015-11-01 21:00:51','',2002,'http://www.improv.org/2002-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2106,5,'2015-11-04 16:05:09','2015-11-05 00:05:09','<h1>4-Week Studio Scene Work <br />Saturdays, 2:30 - 5:30 PM </h1>\r\n<p><strong>November 21 – December 19, 2015<br />Bayfront Theater, San Francisco</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule:</strong> 4 sessions; once a week for four weeks <br /><strong>Class Time/Dates: </strong>2:30-5:30pm on Saturdays November 21 (skip November 28 for Thanksgiving holiday weekend), December 5, 12, and 19<br /><strong>Class size: </strong>10 students maximum <br /><strong>Class length:</strong> 3 hours (12 hours total) <br /><strong>Prerequisite: </strong>Foundation 3</p>','SS - Scene Work - FMC with Laura (#15-11-2229)','','publish','open','open','','ss-scene-work-fmc-with-laura-15-11-2229','','','2015-11-04 16:05:09','2015-11-05 00:05:09','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=2106',0,'class','',0),(2107,5,'2015-11-04 16:25:20','2015-11-05 00:25:20','<h1>Youth Improv (ages 9-11) in Palo Alto<br />2 weeks, Thursdays, 3:45-5pm</h1>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Cubberley Community Center, Palo Alto</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Schedule:</strong> Thursdays, 3:45-5:00pm <br />December 3rd and 10th<br /><strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Ages 9-11, no prior improv experience necessary</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Have you done some improv and are itching to do more?!  Always wanted to try but weren\'t sure how to?  Do you like to use your imagination to create worlds to play in?  If yes, this youth class is for you!<br /> </div>\r\n<div>In our youth improv class, students will work together learning improv principles to have fun, make friends, and play. </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style=\"color: #000000;\"> </p>','Youth improv in Palo Alto - Beth Turnidge - (#12-15-2230)','','publish','open','open','','youth-improv-in-palo-alto-beth-turndige-12-15-2230','','','2015-11-04 16:26:44','2015-11-05 00:26:44','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=class&#038;p=2107',0,'class','',0),(2108,5,'2015-11-04 16:26:17','2015-11-05 00:26:17','','Beth Turnidge','','publish','closed','closed','','beth-turnidge','','','2015-11-04 16:26:17','2015-11-05 00:26:17','',0,'http://www.improv.org/?post_type=actors&#038;p=2108',1,'actors','',0),(2109,4,'2015-11-05 17:26:12','2015-11-06 01:26:12','','otg_john','','inherit','closed','closed','','otg_john','','','2015-11-05 17:26:12','2015-11-06 01:26:12','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/otg_john.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2110,4,'2015-11-05 17:26:17','2015-11-06 01:26:17','','img_foundation_1','','inherit','closed','closed','','img_foundation_1','','','2015-11-05 17:26:17','2015-11-06 01:26:17','',0,'http://www.improv.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/img_foundation_1.jpg',0,'attachment'